column13: Free Entry with RSVP on Do512!|On Friday, March 15 and Saturday, March 16, Austin’s Eye in the Sky Collective and Chicago app startup eevzdrop will take over Shiner’s Saloon in the heart of downtown Austin for the third annual Future of Music Showcase, an unofficial party happening during SXSW presented in partnership with T. Cannon Media, Ditto Music, ATX Music Mag, and Push Music. Food and drink will be provided. Featuring 25+ bands playing from noon-2am each day, this year’s lineup highlights rising Texas stars like Shakey Graves and The Tontons with a selectively curated mix of acts ranging from Chicago hip-hop to Danish psychedelic folk. It will also feature a special performance from the legendary BP Fallon and the Bandits (Third Man Records), featuring Rock and Roll Hall of Famers Clem Burke and Nigel Harrison (Blondie). More headliners will be announced in the coming weeks. See below for a list of confirmed acts so far. Curated by Eye in The Sky co-founder and “Vision Quest Executive” Anthony Erickson, The Future of Music Showcase has become a bellwether for predicting SXSW’s next breakout artists. Previous performers have since performed on Jimmy Kimmel Live and Anthony Bourdain’s “No Reservations,” been featured on MTV’s “Buzzworthy” and NPR Music and topped the popularity lists of Hype Machine and Reddit.|Friday Lineup: > 12pm Les Rav|> 1pm Folk Family Revival|> 2pm Wild Child|> 3pm Hello Caller|> 4pm BP Fallon and the Bandits|> 5pm Shakey Graves|> 6pm Smoke and Feathers|> 7pm Walker Lukens|> 8pm Ditto Music contest winner|> 9pm The Migrant|> 10pm New York City Queens|> 11pm Hydra Melody|> 12am The Hanna Barbarians|> 1am Megafauna| For a preview of 2013’s artists, stream The Future of Music artist sampler here: https://soundcloud.com/eyeintheskycollective/sets/future-of-music-showcase-2013/s-jX01K
column14:
Free Entry with RSVP on Do512!


On Friday, March 15 and Saturday, March 16, Austin’s Eye in the Sky Collective and Chicago app startup eevzdrop will take over Shiner’s Saloon in the heart of downtown Austin for the third annual Future of Music Showcase, an unofficial party happening during SXSW presented in partnership with T. Cannon Media, Ditto Music, ATX Music Mag, and Push Music. Food and drink will be provided.

Featuring 25+ bands playing from noon-2am each day, this year’s lineup highlights rising Texas stars like Shakey Graves and The Tontons with a selectively curated mix of acts ranging from Chicago hip-hop to Danish psychedelic folk. It will also feature a special performance from the legendary BP Fallon and the Bandits (Third Man Records), featuring Rock and Roll Hall of Famers Clem Burke and Nigel Harrison (Blondie). More headliners will be announced in the coming weeks. See below for a list of confirmed acts so far.

Curated by Eye in The Sky co-founder and “Vision Quest Executive” Anthony Erickson, The Future of Music Showcase has become a bellwether for predicting SXSW’s next breakout artists. Previous performers have since performed on Jimmy Kimmel Live and Anthony Bourdain’s “No Reservations,” been featured on MTV’s “Buzzworthy” and NPR Music and topped the popularity lists of Hype Machine and Reddit.


Friday Lineup:

> 12pm Les Rav
> 1pm Folk Family Revival
> 2pm Wild Child
> 3pm Hello Caller
> 4pm BP Fallon and the Bandits
> 5pm Shakey Graves
> 6pm Smoke and Feathers
> 7pm Walker Lukens
> 8pm Ditto Music contest winner
> 9pm The Migrant
> 10pm New York City Queens
> 11pm Hydra Melody
> 12am The Hanna Barbarians
> 1am Megafauna

For a preview of 2013’s artists, stream The Future of Music artist sampler here: https://soundcloud.com/eyeintheskycollective/sets/future-of-music-showcase-2013/s-jX01K

The Midwest Music Foundation is proud to present the fourth annual MidCoast Takeover, March 13th – 16th at Shangri-La in Austin, TX.


This event promises four days of music, mayhem, and general debauchery — the definitive Midwestern musical throw down. MidCoast Takeover will showcase bands from Kansas City, Lawrence, and the Midwest region on the national stage during South by Southwest.

column14:
THE OUTLAW ROADSHOW is produced by Ryan Spaulding (Creator of rslblog.com and Producer and Host of The Bubbler on myTV38 in New England) and Adam Duritz (of Counting Crows and Producer of the new comedy Freeloaders). The Outlaw returns to Austin, TX this March for 2 SHOWS... Sat, March 9th and Sat, March 16th in Downtown Austin at Rusty's - the best live music venue in the city.

THE OUTLAW ROADSHOW is a thrill ride for the music fan: 3 stages featuring bright emerging bands who deserve some time in your headphones in 2013.

SATURDAY MARCH 16
NOON - Rusty's at 405 East 7th
Austin, TX

NO BADGES REQUIRED

FREE RSVP TO ATTEND!
19 LIVE BANDS


Both sessions of The Outlaw Roadshow 2013 are presented by ZAZOO. Zazoo has introduced a revolutionary new web application that embeds an artist's unique ‘Mini App’ onto each music video, wherever it is watched. Zazoo provides fans with a live, engaging viewing experience – sing along, play along, access lyrics, peak backstage, get special offers and interact with artists who can now reach the broadest audience possible and gain an edge in a fiercely competitive market.

Last year's showcase was attended by thousands and this year we expect the same. Our foremost concern is that everyone is enriched by this process. That means the bands, the fans, the venue, the sound people - in the hope that we'll be able to do this for years to come. The Outlaw Roadshow is all about music and you.


ADDITIONAL EVENT DETAILS
EVENT HISTORY
BUNCH OF OTHER STUFF

* Legal ID and 21+
Admittance requires Free RSVP.
Venue is limited to legal capacity.

Click HERE or the image below to submit your entry to play the 9th Annual All Together Now Showcase



RSVP does not guarantee entry, so arrive early!


Welcome to the 9th annual All Together Now Showcase in Austin, TX from March 13-18, 2013. We'll be featuring 60+ bands over 5 days and have already started working on some amazing things for the event!

We at the ATN Showcase always feature an impacting and active charity in our events. We are in the process of researching and finding the absolute best fit for 2013. We are definitely open to any ideas or suggestions. If you would like to submit ideas, please send those to jennifer@atnmanagement.com.

For interview requests, press inquiries, etc. click here.

ATN Management is a hands-on, independent management firm producing charity-driven showcases for the past 7 years. Jennifer DaRe is ATN Management's principle, overseeing the coordination of the All Together Now Showcase.

Jennifer has collected 25 combined years of experience in the music industry and entertainment industry, and 8 years in talent management. Ms. DaRe has amassed a network of industry contacts with whom she has collaborated in developing and growing ATN Management and is well known for her well-rounded and proven managerial style unique in the industry.

Line-up coming soon....

HISTORY OF GNG 501(c)3
www.guitarsnotguns.org

“Guitars not Guns” (GnG) was founded by Ray and Louise Nelson. They became foster parents in 1992 and it was through this experience that Ray realized these youth needed more positive opportunities to help them grow into productive citizens. Ray was a life long musician; he knew the benefits of engaging in a music program and he saw few music opportunities for these youth.

He decided to start a music program for foster kids; any child that had the desire would be provided a guitar and free lessons. On July 24, 2000 Guitars not Guns was incorporated and became a federally exempt 501(c) (3) non-profit. Shortly thereafter they started their first guitar class with two volunteer teachers in San Jose, California. Over the next few years classes expanded to neighboring Counties in California and the program expanded to include any youth living in adverse circumstances who lacked the means to participate in a music program. In 2006 the program started spreading outside of California; today GnG’s Music Program is operating in several states and Canada.

Guitars not Guns Virginia was chartered as a GnG Affiliate in June 2006; Guitars not Guns Maryland and Guitars not Guns Washington D.C. were chartered as GnG Affiliates in April 2009. Virginia, Maryland and DC operate jointly asGnG NCA (Guitars Not Guns of the National Capital Area). Collectively we operate 32 teaching locations and serve over 300 youth annually. New locations are being opened as volunteers and funds are found to operate them.


More (delicious and sweet) details to follow soon.

Over the next few years classes expanded to neighboring Counties in California and the program expanded to include any youth living in adverse circumstances who lacked the means to participate in a music program. In 2006 the program started spreading outside of California; today GnG’s Music Program is operating in several states and Canada.

Guitars not Guns Virginia was chartered as a GnG Affiliate in June 2006; Guitars not Guns Maryland and Guitars not Guns Washington D.C. were chartered as GnG Affiliates in April 2009. Virginia, Maryland and DC operate jointly asGnG NCA (Guitars Not Guns of the National Capital Area). Collectively we operate 32 teaching locations and serve over 300 youth annually. New locations are being opened as volunteers and funds are found to operate them.

More (delicious and sweet) details to follow soon.

Bald Logo.com sells ad space on bald heads. This local start-up marketing company, that focuses on stunt media and online marketing, is throwing a party featuring FREE BEER and Bluegrass!


Join us at 707 W. 21st Street, Austin, TX, 78705 on MARCH 9TH from 4:00 p.m. to 2:00 a.m. where Bluegrass/Folk Bands will be playing non-stop from 4:00 to 11:00 p.m. The fun doesn't stop there- we've got a Moon Bounce, along with $1 tacos. FREE BEER provided during the main event occurring from 11:00 p.m. to 2:00 a.m.


We are pleased to announce our AMAZING headliners will be:

-Whiskey Shivers

Make sure to RSVP- See You There!

The Midwest Music Foundation is proud to present the fourth annual MidCoast Takeover, March 13th – 16th at Shangri-La in Austin, TX.


This event promises four days of music, mayhem, and general debauchery — the definitive Midwestern musical throw down. MidCoast Takeover will showcase bands from Kansas City, Lawrence, and the Midwest region on the national stage during South by Southwest.

Austin Angers Music Official Day Party

Thursday, March 14th /// 12PM to 5PM
Free Entry with RSVP on Do512!



Bungalow
92 Rainey Street

12pm Arno Gonzalez (electronic Angers-Fr) soundcloud.com/arnogonzalez
1pm The RocketBoys (rock Austin-Tx) www.therocketboys.com
2pm Titi Robin trio (world Angers-Fr) www.thierrytitirobin.com
3pm Erin Ivey (Singer-Songwriter Austin-Tx) www.erinivey.com
4pm Wild Child (folk Austin-Tx) www.wildchildsounds.com
5pm Not in the Face (rock Austin-Tx) www.notinthefacerocks.com

Also! Check out the lineup for Austin Angers Music’s Official Showcase & Austin Angers Psych Day

Austin Angers Music is a company from Angers, Loire Valley, France. They're committed to creating cultural and musical exchanges between Austin and it's "sister city" in France, Angers.

During SXSW, the organizers are hosting two day parties and an official showcase that will feature a blend of Angers and Austin musicians including local acts Wild Child, UME and Not In The Face. These events are an opportunity to network and develop relationships between the sister cities in the hopes of fostering cross-cultural experiences and artistic opportunities here in Austin and in Angers.

Welcome to the 9th annual All Together Now Showcase in Austin, TX from March 13-18, 2013. We'll be featuring 60+ bands over 5 days and have already started working on some amazing things for the event!

We at the ATN Showcase always feature an impacting and active charity in our events. We are in the process of researching and finding the absolute best fit for 2013. We are definitely open to any ideas or suggestions. If you would like to submit ideas, please send those to jennifer@atnmanagement.com.

Ms. DaRe has amassed a network of industry contacts with whom she has collaborated in developing and growing ATN Management and is well known for her well-rounded and proven managerial style unique in the industry.

Line-up coming soon....

Austin: We have a festival every other weekend. Everyone's got at least one tattoo. For a while we had our own town transvestite. "Keep Austin Weird"? It's Weird Enough! So come over and take your weird out at, March 12th! Pre-show at 8, Comedians at 9! We have a stellar list of local comics!

HOST: Luis Flandes

Rob Gagnon
Pat Sirois
Chance Royce
Michael Navarette
Lawson Bennett
Ben Cholok
Tyler Harris
Eric Nagurney
Jacob Collings
Chad Comstock
Michael Monsour

The best part is that it's totally FREE (but donations accepted and much appreciated) and BYOB, sponsored by EZ Irie One Love, merch available.

Do you have a weird talent skill? Would you like to perform that skill to during the Preshow if it will get you free beers for the night? If so, email me at Luisiflandes@gmail.com and we'll see if if I can get you on, I'll take the best 5.

column14:
Presents:
Epic Interactive
Fri. March 8, 7:30pm


Sponsored By:



Complimentary cocktails on the Do512 tab until it runs out!

21+ Only, no exceptions!
To RSVP, Click the RSVP Button at the top of this page. PLEASE NOTE: RSVP does NOT guarantee entry. This event will likely be at capacity and we recommend coming early.




  • 11:00 pm– Akron/Family
  • 10:00 pm - Air Review
  • 9:00 pm - Hello Wheels
  • 8pm - Seryn


For media and special requests: Rachel@Do512.com



About Deep Eddy Vodka:

Deep Eddy Straight Vodka & Deep Eddy Sweet Tea Vodka is handcrafted in Austin, Texas. We distill our vodka 10+ times in a state-of-the-art 20 foot column still, and source the ingredients and water from right here in Texas


About Get Smart Content
:
Get Smart Content is a dynamic targeting and testing platform that enables your company to provide content and messaging that is tailored to a user's interests and their position in the sales funnel. Brands that provide targeted content convert a higher percentage of visitors into leads and customers - increasing their ROI. Learn more at GetSmartContent.com About CrowdSYNC: CrowdSYNC merges fan and professional video footage shot at the same time and place. We sync the content, you call the shots.

About The Belmont:

The Belmont is Austin's premier intimate live music music venue. The Belmont boasts over 15,000 sq. ft of completely renovated indoor/outdoor space, 5 bars, a rooftop deck with Austin skyline views, a big new stage, and professional sound and lighting, all in an upscale setting in the heart of the Warehouse District.

THE LINEUP:


On April 30th, Akron/Family will release their fifth album, Sub Verses, on Dead Oceans Records. Influenced, in part, by monumental land art installations and harnessed by producer Randall Dunn (Sunn 0))), Earth, Black Mountain, Wolves In The Throne Room etc…). In a sense it sees the band returning to their roots, revisiting the heavy physical impact, emotional confrontation, intensity, and musicality of their collaborations w/ Michael Gira of Swans.



Seryn is a 6 piece band who calls Denton, Texas their home. When listening to the well layered textures of guitars, ukulele, accordion, bass, viola, banjo and various percussion, it’s hard to imagine This Is Where We Are is the band’s debut effort. The band’s strength resides in their vast musical talent and understanding of dynamics.




Hello Wheels is a four strong stomp-folk act from Austin, TX. Harmony rich and driving, their songs boast dynamic arrangements, thoughtfully woven into the stories they tell. The result has been called ‘a new sound with an old soul’. In their third year together, the group is hard at work on their first full-length release to follow their debut EP Baby John the Fox and split 7" with locals Whiskey Shivers Friends Do Things Together.





Air Review started writing songs in 2008 out of the converted garage of an unassuming suburban house outside of Dallas, Texas. Meeting once a week for nearly a year in a room without air conditioning or heating, the quintet carefully crafted a record that they later self-released in 2009. After a couple years of playing countless shows and receiving glowing reviews, the band still felt like something was missing. The group hibernated for another 12 months and re-invented themselves.

column6: 422 Congress Avenue, Suite D, Austin, TX, 78701

column13: Free Entry with RSVP on Do512!|On Friday, March 15 and Saturday, March 16, Austin’s Eye in the Sky Collective and Chicago app startup eevzdrop will take over Shiner’s Saloon in the heart of downtown Austin for the third annual Future of Music Showcase, an unofficial party happening during SXSW presented in partnership with T. Cannon Media, Ditto Music, ATX Music Mag, and Push Music. Food and drink will be provided. Featuring 25+ bands playing from noon-2am each day, this year’s lineup highlights rising Texas stars like Shakey Graves and The Tontons with a selectively curated mix of acts ranging from Chicago hip-hop to Danish psychedelic folk. It will also feature a special performance from the legendary BP Fallon and the Bandits (Third Man Records), featuring Rock and Roll Hall of Famers Scott Asheton (The Stooges), Clem Burke (Blondie), and Nigel Harrison (Blondie). More headliners will be announced in the coming weeks. See below for a list of confirmed acts so far. Curated by Eye in The Sky co-founder and “Vision Quest Executive” Anthony Erickson, The Future of Music Showcase has become a bellwether for predicting SXSW’s next breakout artists. Previous performers have since performed on Jimmy Kimmel Live and Anthony Bourdain’s “No Reservations,” been featured on MTV’s “Buzzworthy” and NPR Music and topped the popularity lists of Hype Machine and Reddit.|Saturday Schedule:| 12pm Tyagaraja|> 1pm The Tontons|> 2pm Emily Bell|> 3pm Leopold and His Fiction|> 4pm Equals|> 5pm SORNE|> 6pm Riders Against the Storm|> 7pm Retrospect|> 8pm Carlton Zeus|> 9pm Seveer Transmission|> 10pm Ditto Music contest winner|> 11pm Larry g(EE)|> 12am Featherface|> 1am Hard Proof Afrobeat| For a preview of 2013’s artists, stream The Future of Music artist sampler here: https://soundcloud.com/eyeintheskycollective/sets/future-of-music-showcase-2013/s-jX01K
column14:
Free Entry with RSVP on Do512!


On Friday, March 15 and Saturday, March 16, Austin’s Eye in the Sky Collective and Chicago app startup eevzdrop will take over Shiner’s Saloon in the heart of downtown Austin for the third annual Future of Music Showcase, an unofficial party happening during SXSW presented in partnership with T. Cannon Media, Ditto Music, ATX Music Mag, and Push Music. Food and drink will be provided.

Featuring 25+ bands playing from noon-2am each day, this year’s lineup highlights rising Texas stars like Shakey Graves and The Tontons with a selectively curated mix of acts ranging from Chicago hip-hop to Danish psychedelic folk. It will also feature a special performance from the legendary BP Fallon and the Bandits (Third Man Records), featuring Rock and Roll Hall of Famers Scott Asheton (The Stooges), Clem Burke (Blondie), and Nigel Harrison (Blondie). More headliners will be announced in the coming weeks. See below for a list of confirmed acts so far.

Curated by Eye in The Sky co-founder and “Vision Quest Executive” Anthony Erickson, The Future of Music Showcase has become a bellwether for predicting SXSW’s next breakout artists. Previous performers have since performed on Jimmy Kimmel Live and Anthony Bourdain’s “No Reservations,” been featured on MTV’s “Buzzworthy” and NPR Music and topped the popularity lists of Hype Machine and Reddit.

column13: THE OUTLAW ROADSHOW is produced by Ryan Spaulding (Creator of rslblog.com and Producer and Host of The Bubbler on myTV38 in New England) and Adam Duritz (of Counting Crows and Producer of the new comedy Freeloaders). The Outlaw returns to Austin, TX this March for 2 SHOWS... Sat, March 9th and Sat, March 16th in Downtown Austin at Rusty's - the best live music venue in the city.|THE OUTLAW ROADSHOW is a thrill ride for the music fan: 3 stages featuring bright emerging bands who deserve some time in your headphones in 2013.|SATURDAY MARCH 9 |8pm - Rusty's at 405 East 7th |Austin, TX| NO BADGES REQUIRED* FREE RSVP TO ATTEND!|17 LIVE BANDS|Both sessions of The Outlaw Roadshow 2013 are presented by ZAZOO. THE LINEUP:


The Polyphonic Spree - The Polyphonic Spree is a self-described choral symphonic rock group from the Dallas, Texas area. The band generally consists of a 10-person choir, a pair of keyboardists, as well as a percussionist, drummer, bassist, guitarist, flautist, trumpeter, trombonist, violinist/violist, harpist, French horn player, a pedal steel player, theremin player, and an electronic effects person. Individual members and the number of musicians, however, vary, because of the flexibility necessary in traveling with such a large band


Big Freedia - Big Freedia (pronounced “Free-da”) is the undisputed “Queen Diva” of Bounce Music, and performs six or more times a week in various venues throughout her home town of New Orleans. Bounce Music is an original urban music rising up from the intimate and fun-loving nature of the New Orleans housing projects which dominate the city’s street culture, and Freedia performs a derivative of Bounce reserved for self-proclaimed “Sissies” (a locally used name for biological men with varied and ambiguous sexual identities) that has risen to prominence in recent years and features explicitly gay and cross-dressing musicians and themes.

Girl in a Coma - Female rock trio Girl in a Coma formed in San Antonio, Texas in 2001. Their first show at Sin13 that same year left their audience in awe of the group’s extraordinary sound (courtesy of childhood friends Jenn Alva on bass and Phanie D. on drums) and Nina Diaz’s jaw-dropping vocals, which have been compared to those of Bjork and Patsy Cline. Girl in a Coma’s history began in 1993 when Phanie and Jenn found themselves seated next to each other in an art class at Longfellow Junior High School and decided to form their first band.



Junius - Boston has long been known as a breeding ground for renowned political dissidents as well as mind-expanding sonic adventurists. Carrying in that tradition is Junius–a rainy, Brit-inflected supernova of gigantic guitars, entrancing lights, and erudite lyrics, named after the pseudonym of an enigmatic late 18th century political critic. The New England coast was first illuminated by Junius’ sonic declarations in 2004


Brazos - As he likes to tell it, Martin McNulty Crane is the fifth in a long line of Martins in his family, all hailing from Texas. The first was an orphan who taught himself law, became the Attorney General of Texas and fought the KKK. The second was a lieutenant in World War I. The third was an airline pilot who raised his family in Iran. The fourth is a scientist.


Ultimate Fakebook- 3-piece power pop band from Manhattan KS who are ready to rock and it's not a question, baby.



DJ sets by Johhny Hottub (80's hair bands)

DJ SETS|Sponsored by Sweet Tea Pumpkin Pie (STPP)|www.sweetteapumpkinpie.com|www.stppfest.com|STPP is proud to partner with the following...|The Deli Magazine|www.thedelimagazine.com|HISTORY OF GNG 501(c)3|www.guitarsnotguns.org|“Guitars not Guns” (GnG) was founded by Ray and Louise Nelson. They became foster parents in 1992 and it was through this experience that Ray realized these youth needed more positive opportunities to help them grow into productive citizens. Ray was a life long musician; he knew the benefits of engaging in a music program and he saw few music opportunities for these youth.|He decided to start a music program for foster kids; any child that had the desire would be provided a guitar and free lessons. On July 24, 2000 Guitars not Guns was incorporated and became a federally exempt 501(c) (3) non-profit. Shortly thereafter they started their first guitar class with two volunteer teachers in San Jose, California. Over the next few years classes expanded to neighboring Counties in California and the program expanded to include any youth living in adverse circumstances who lacked the means to participate in a music program. In 2006 the program started spreading outside of California; today GnG’s Music Program is operating in several states and Canada.|Guitars not Guns Virginia was chartered as a GnG Affiliate in June 2006; Guitars not Guns Maryland and Guitars not Guns Washington D.C. were chartered as GnG Affiliates in April 2009. Virginia, Maryland and DC operate jointly asGnG NCA (Guitars Not Guns of the National Capital Area). Collectively we operate 32 teaching locations and serve over 300 youth annually. New locations are being opened as volunteers and funds are found to operate them.|More (delicious and sweet) details to follow soon.|+ in.sessions w/ in.gredients (@ store!)|http://www.in.gredients.com/|http://in.gredients.com/in-sessions/ |(the in.sessions are really special!!!)

HISTORY OF GNG 501(c)3
www.guitarsnotguns.org

“Guitars not Guns” (GnG) was founded by Ray and Louise Nelson. They became foster parents in 1992 and it was through this experience that Ray realized these youth needed more positive opportunities to help them grow into productive citizens. Ray was a life long musician; he knew the benefits of engaging in a music program and he saw few music opportunities for these youth.

He decided to start a music program for foster kids; any child that had the desire would be provided a guitar and free lessons. On July 24, 2000 Guitars not Guns was incorporated and became a federally exempt 501(c) (3) non-profit. Shortly thereafter they started their first guitar class with two volunteer teachers in San Jose, California. Over the next few years classes expanded to neighboring Counties in California and the program expanded to include any youth living in adverse circumstances who lacked the means to participate in a music program. In 2006 the program started spreading outside of California; today GnG’s Music Program is operating in several states and Canada.

Guitars not Guns Virginia was chartered as a GnG Affiliate in June 2006; Guitars not Guns Maryland and Guitars not Guns Washington D.C. were chartered as GnG Affiliates in April 2009. Virginia, Maryland and DC operate jointly asGnG NCA (Guitars Not Guns of the National Capital Area). Collectively we operate 32 teaching locations and serve over 300 youth annually. New locations are being opened as volunteers and funds are found to operate them.

More (delicious and sweet) details to follow soon.

About Band of the Day: Band of the Day unearths the best new music by delivering one new artist a day, every single day. Through expert curation, free music (commercial free and uninterupted), a stunning user interface, videos, photographs, biographies, and more - we help you discover your new favorite uninterrupted


About Applauze: makes the experience of discovering, planning, and securing tickets for free or paid events simpler and more beautiful than ever before.




Portugal. the Man - By now, the peripatetic trail etched out by Portugal. The Man is well documented. The band’s nomadic path snakes down the Cascades, starting first in Wasilla, Alaska (yes, the very same city whose identity has been hijacked by a certain celebrity politician, one who we shall not mention again here), and then eventually settling in amongst the puddles and monochromatic haze of Portland, Oregon. There were Iditarod-racing parents, wooden cabins tucked deep in the woods, and the sort of upbringing that skews the very notion of convention. But let us end that chapter of Portugal. The Man’s lore and move forward.

That is the Portugal. The Man of then, In The Mountain In The Cloud is the Portugal. The Man of now.




Bonaparte - the ridiculous endeavor of starting a circus was suggested to me by my therapist dr. minski wellington upon my release from the private siamese pseudo clinic for lobsterpossesiveobssesivecompulsive disorder in the mountains of southern france. after having to play the role of fake tigers, whips and rings of fire all at once, slowly the word started to spread amongst the unemployed superhero community and other long forgotten tradesmen. fluffy creatures hopped on the fire engine red steam train and joined in the fun, leaving their former lives of hardship behind without a single care in the world



Marmalakes - is a rock band from Austin, TX. Dynamic and lyrically-attentive, their songs carry folk-pop sensibilities. Since 2008, they've released 3 EPs and a 7-inch.

They have played with Shearwater, Sondre Lerche and Black Taxi and have sold out venues such as Rockwood Music Hall, The Parish and The Mohawk Austin.

column14:
RSVP for Free Entry on Do512!


The OUTlander 2013 Spring Music Festival is a multimedia festival that will be held in Austin, Texas from March 08-16, 2013, during the 2013 South By Southwest Festival. In addition to interactive and film components, OUTlander will be the largest gathering of lesbian, gay, bisexual, transgender, and queer (LGBTQ) and allied music artists in Texas performing over 5 days right in the heart of one of the iconic events of the music industry. The event will showcase several regional and national acts along with several well-known local acts.

The OUTlander Project Day 3 of music week is a showcase on Friday, March 15, 2013 at Oilcan Harry's at 211 W 4th Street in the heart of downtown Austin featuring more than a dozen LGBTQ and allied artists from around the country on one stage!

Confirmed performers include:

column14:
Spirithouse, IndyMusicSales.com, and The Collective Music Group Present...

The Northampton Comes To Austin Mobile Studio!!

Thursday March 14th- Friday March 15th

Tamale House East
1707 E 6th St.
2pm-10pm

The Northampton Comes To Austin Mobile Studio will take place in an RV set up at the Tamale House East during SXSW. Northampton based artists will host the best independent musicians from around the world to record and collaborate in this truly unique space. The live performances and collaborations on the RV will be recorded by Spirithouse Studios and videotaped for release on YouTube. Industry tastemaker 93.9 The River has also joined the project as a media partner and will broadcast “live” recordings from the RV throughout the festival to thousands of music fans around the world!


A stage will also be set up outside the RV and various acts will perform throughout the day/evening on both the 14th and 15th.


Come on by the Tamale House, grab some food, check out the studio, dance your ass off, and be a part of this killer live music experience!!

Sorted Noise & Friends Day Party
Friday, March 15th // 1:30pm - 7pm
Free Entry with RSVP on Do512

Come join Nashville based production & management team, Sorted Noise, and some of our closest friends for our big ass (unofficial) SXSW day party.
We'll have wall to wall music from buzzy "it" artists like SleeperStar, The CO, AutoVaughn, Andrew Ripp, and Shay Mooney, as well as from established headliners like Leigh Nash (of Sixpence None the Richer), Julie Roberts, and the iconic Ron Sexsmith. Some of the best food trucks in Austin will be on the scene, and we'll have free drinks as long as they last. We'll be setting up shop at a brand new venue called Easy Beat located on the corner of 3rd and Trinity, directly across from the convention center, from 1-7pm on Friday, March 15th. Basically, it's going to be awesome, and you need to be there.

And you do NOT need a SXSW badge to attend.

The OUTlander 2013 Spring Music Festival is a multimedia festival that will be held in Austin, Texas from March 08-16, 2013, during the 2013 South By Southwest Festival. In addition to interactive and film components, OUTlander will be the largest gathering of lesbian, gay, bisexual, transgender, and queer (LGBTQ) and allied music artists in Texas performing over 5 days right in the heart of one of the iconic events of the music industry. The event will showcase several regional and national acts along with several well-known local acts.

The OUTlander Project Day 4 of music week is a showcase on SATURDAY, March 16, 2013 at Oilcan Harry's at 211 W 4th Street in the heart of downtown Austin featuring more than a dozen LGBTQ and allied artists from around the country on one stage!

column14:
HEAR THERE. EVERYWHERE.
The 6th Annual Dart Music International House

Since 2008 DMI has helped Austin "Hear There. Everywhere." by presenting unprecedented international cultural events in Austin during the big festival week. Some of the highlights have included historic events like "Music From Space" (an exclusive video from the International Space Station), "6 Bands 6 Continents" (back-to-back performances by artists from every inhabited continent), and "Taquacore + i:Made in Israel + ATX Hip Hop" (Iranian, Israeli, and Austin artists performing together).


This year is going to add to that legacy in an informal, "happy hour" setting. From Tuesday, March 12 through Friday, March 15, in between the music panels / day parties and the nightly showcases, DMI will be producing the 6th Annual Dart Music International House event in downtown Austin. This is your opportunity of a lifetime to experience global culture in an informal setting. We hope to see you there!


WHEN: Tuesday, March 12 through Friday, March 15, 2013; 5-8PM Daily
WHERE: Mark McCrimmon Law Office, 704 West 9th Street (Map)
WHAT: Music & culture with Artists from Every Inhabited Continent
WHO: Complimentary food and drinks from The Peached Tortilla, Austin Beerworks, Tito's Handmade Vodka, and more.
ADMISSION: FREE, ALL AGES


This project is funded and supported in part by the City of Austin through the Economic Growth & Redevelopment Services Office / Cultural Arts Division believing an investment in the Arts is an investment in Austin's future. Visit Austin at NowPlayingAustin.com.

column14:
DJ Geno, Across the Board and Gowhere Hip Hop present "Coup de Grace" Unofficial SXSW Showcase. (Free Entry with RSVP on Do512)

"Coup De Grace" (pronounce: kuː də ˈɡrɑːs) an end all be all event that punctuates the SXSW 2013 culture. Coup de Grace will stay true to the SXSW culture by not sticking to a script. This event will cover a broad range of Music, with the focus from Hip Hop to Rock, Indie, and R&B. The Historic Victory Grill is the perfect venue to present this ground breaking event.

Independent Artists will be able to share the stage with mainstream Acts to create a surreal experience that will leave lasting impressions to those blessed to attend!

With event partners DJ Geno, Across the Board, LiveGrandeur and along with our media sponsors SongDish and GoWhereHipHop, together we deliver and showcase talents at SXSW that we believe to be the next "New Artist of the Year."

So join us whether on stage or in the building, Enjoy what SXSW was meant to be, and witness the future of Music.

Hosted By: Dj Geno & Tony Baines

column14:
Free Entry with RSVP on Do512!


March 8th - 14th
Emo’s East Plaza
2015 E Riverside
(Between Emo’s East and the Beauty Ballroom)

We're elated to present 100 films, including featured premieres, 18 films that have won Best Feature, Best Documentary or Best Short at Film ExChange Network Festivals in Victoria, TX; Brooklyn, NY; New Orleans, LA; Corpus Christi, TX; Hamburg, Germany; and Lahti, Finland.

Highlights & Special Events: 100 Films, Superior Cinephile Contest, Unlimited Libations, Celebrity Appearances, Late Late Thursday Night Social Ride After Party, Special Event Premiere of Danko Jones (Lemmy Kilmister, Elijah Wood, Selma Blair, & Mike Watt), and NO BADGES/WRISTBANDS REQUIRED.

One film from each category will travel to the Victoria, TX Independent Film Festival, held April 4-7 2013, to compete for cash prizes totaling $5,000. As always Rxsm is FREE!

Unlimited complimentary libations during the entire 7 days thanks to the support of our sponsors: Revel Stoke Whiskey, UV Vodka, Tecate, Treaty Oak Rum, Waterloo Gin, Zico Water, Montana Cans, Cervexa Indio,Slacker Magazine, and Red River Noise.

DON'T FORGET TO SIGN UP FOR THE CONTEST! Got what it takes to set a record? This year RxSM has announced the Superior Cinephile Contest where 5 film addicts will be selected to view 100 films, in 84 hours, over 7 days! Only one will be crowned as the "Superior Cinephile"! Prizes include VIP passes to upcoming film festivals, cash money prize of $100, a sweet customized trophy, and a gift basket assortment of goodies provided by our sponsors! If you are psycho about cinema and want to enter the contest please send an email about why you have what it takes to win the contest (info@rxsm.com) and we will select 5 film addicts to compete for the title.

This trip reciprocates last year’s visit by Austin’s Mayor Lee Leffingwell and his digital media trade mission, organised to foster exchange in the areas of high-tech and digital media, the creative industries, economic development, and sustainability. The Hackney team will be setting up as Hackney House Austin – an international travelling ‘capsule’ edition of 2012’s stunning and successful urban pop-up space, set up in Hackney's Shoreditch district during last year’s Olympic Games. Created by Hackney Council to act as a hub for new investment to Hackney, it succeeded in showcasing this cluster of culturally relevant creative businesses currently making their global mark. For four days only, Hackney House Austin will transform a 3,000+ sq ft space on 6th Street into the ultimate Hackney-inspired workshop space. Through a carefully curated programme of Art, Design, Music, Film, Product and Events, 25 local businesses will have the opportunity to spotlight their work, network with Austin friends, entertain and enlighten, all within an exceptional space. By day, Hackney House Austin will be a welcoming hangout, complete with free WIFI and coffee, meeting spaces, and power chargers. Come by between 10am – 2pm and the space will be filled with a curated programme of short films by Protein, onedotzero and ITV. The Sugru repair shop will be open for business, and you’ll be invited to drop by and pick up your pre-ordered business cards by Moo. The afternoons see us amp up the pace with panels and workshops byMakieLab and onedotzero, as well as a screening of Choose Your Own Documentary presented by ITV. This trip reciprocates last year’s visit by Austin’s Mayor Lee Leffingwell and his digital media trade mission, organised to foster exchange in the areas of high-tech and digital media, the creative industries, economic development, and sustainability.

The Hackney team will be setting up as Hackney House Austin – an international travelling ‘capsule’ edition of 2012’s stunning and successful urban pop-up space, set up in Hackney's Shoreditch district during last year’s Olympic Games. Created by Hackney Council to act as a hub for new investment to Hackney, it succeeded in showcasing this cluster of culturally relevant creative businesses currently making their global mark.

For four days only, Hackney House Austin will transform a 3,000+ sq ft space on 6th Street into the ultimate Hackney-inspired workshop space. Through a carefully curated programme of Art, Design, Music, Film, Product and Events, 25 local businesses will have the opportunity to spotlight their work, network with Austin friends, entertain and enlighten, all within an exceptional space.

By day, Hackney House Austin will be a welcoming hangout, complete with free WIFI and coffee, meeting spaces, and power chargers. Come by between 10am – 2pm and the space will be filled with a curated programme of short films by Protein, onedotzero and ITV. The Sugru repair shop will be open for business, and you’ll be invited to drop by and pick up your pre-ordered business cards by Moo.

The afternoons see us amp up the pace with panels and workshops byMakieLab and onedotzero, as well as a screening of Choose Your Own Documentary presented by ITV. Protein will (re)launch its premium video content platform Protein TV at the ‘Future of TV’ forum, featuring experts in the field of television and hosted by Protein’s Founder and CEO William Rowe.

The supporting, 4-day programme of events will confirm Hackney House Austin as the key destination for showcasing Hackney’s best new ideas and business networking. Styled with beautiful products straight out of Hackney including a 2m2 Plumen chandelier and the Goodnight Lamp, Hackney House Austin is an open opportunity for guests to meet Hackney’s top creative and digital companies, including: Bare Conductive, BERG, Choose Your Own Documentary, The Church of London, Dezeen, Digital Shoreditch, Goodnight Lamp, Hulger, iCITY, Kahoot! Makielab, Mixcloud, MOO, Mother, Not Tom, onedotzero, POKE, Protein,Sugru, Technology Will Save Us and Trampery.

Follow us on Twitter at @HackneyHouse13 #HackneyHouseAustin


“Our friendship with the City of Austin is leading us into exciting territory, the SXSW festival is the perfect destination for Hackney House bringing with it the best of Hackney’s creative, design and tech sectors to showcase their world leading ideas, develop new relationships and form new ventures” said Guy Nicholson, lead Cabinet Member for Economic Development and Regeneration at the London Borough of Hackney.”

column14:
Chicago, I Love You… BBQ @ SX2013
Presented by Tom Schraeder, Do312 & Friends

Saturday, March 16, 2013 // noon - midnight // 21+
Free Entry with RSVP on Do512!


Special Magic Barn Fantastic
2507 Willow Street

Tom Schraeder’s revolutionary music, arts, and culture festival Chicago, I Love You… will return for a second installment in October, 2013. In it’s inaugural outing last September, the free festival ran for thirty days and nights exclusively at one venue. “This fall however, will be something a bit different,” says Schraeder. “Instead of one month, it’s one week. Instead of one venue, it’s fifty!” With support from Do312, the Chicago, I Love You… Free Week Festival will be spread throughout the city as a celebration of all things Chicago- music, art, comedy, film, literature, restaurants, and theater.

As part of that celebration of the city and to give people a glimpse of what is in store for the next installment of the festival, Schraeder is throwing a party in Austin, Texas, called Chicago, I Love You… BBQ @ SX2013. On Saturday, March 16, over twenty artists will perform on two stages at "Special Magic Barn Fantastic" the converted barn/recording studio belonging to famed Austin singer-songwriter Danny Malone. The show begins at noon, and the complete lineup of artists and set times is below.
“Special Magic Barn Fantasitco is just walking distance from downtown Austin, and we’ll be only a few blocks away from the hipster hangout known as The Fader Fort,” Schraeder quipped. "This show should be looked at as a meeting ground for all our Chicago bands, booking agents, and fans. Even a few journalists will be allowed.”

For those who won’t be in Austin to see the show live, The Chicago, I Love You… BBQ @ SX2013 will be filmed and made available online. For more information, contact tomschraeder@gmail.com

Chicago, I Love You… BBQ @ SX2013 is sponsored in part by HIS EGO, Do312, Squirrel Trap Records, and SideCar Chicago.

1504 E 6th Street


It's not that we're saying we have the best party in Austin, but we kind of have the best party in Austin. On Friday March 15th, come to Altamont/ Blundertown and Cultist presents The Altamont Showcase at The Sailor Jerry House.

If you like awesome bands like Hanni El Khatib, King Tuff, Pangea, Nu Sensae, White Lung, Hunters, The Blind Shake, Meat Market, and Lovely Bad Things, good music by DJs Shannon Cornett and Yasi Cultist, warm happiness by Sailor Jerry, and you know, making memories that will last a lifetime (or about 12 minutes, depending on how much time you spend with Sailor Jerry).

For the more cavalier (or just-plain-nuts) Sailor Jerry has teamed up withDowntown Terry Brown to give free tattoos on a first-come-first-served basis. You’ll have your choice between classic Anchor, Cherry, Star, Swallow or Shark but here’s the rub: you’ll have to throw darts at a board to choose your image.

Cheap Drinks, must be 21+

column14:
INDIE GAME DEV HAPPY HOUR
Presented by Minicore Studios
Monday, March 11th // 4pm
Free Entry with RSVP on Do512

The Brixton
1412 E 6th St

Featuring special guest DJ, Jared Blondeau!

Minicore Studios is hosting a happy hour in honor of the Indie Game Dev Community. Whether you are involved locally, like us, or a game dev from out of town, we’d love to meet you and treat you to some free drinks and a little down time during SXSWi.

Join us at The Brixton on the East Side starting at 4:00pm. Drinks will last as long as they last (so arrive early!) but the conversation and good times will go until 8:00pm. RSVP for a guaranteed free drink and score a BONUS free drink if you show us that you’ve downloaded our latest mobile word puzzler, Tumblewords.

About Minicore Studios:

Minicore Studios is an Austin-based Indie Game Developer founded in 2011. Since then, we had developed two mobile games and are working on a downloadable PC/Console game. Our most recent release is Tumblewords, an original blend of traditional word games and strategic puzzle games with customizable art styles featuring some of our favorite artists. Tumblewords is perfect for strategic competitive play with friends or unwinding by yourself.

You can download and play Tumblewords from the App Store: https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/id548414808

We’re super excited about Austin’s Game Dev community and want to share our passion for artfully-crafted games with everyone in town for SXSW! Come by and celebrate this awesome community with us!


You can learn more about Minicore Studios here: http://minicorestudios.com/
And more about Tumblewords here: http://minicorestudios.com/games/tumblewords

La Patisserie
602 W. Annie St.


LINEUP

Western Youth (Austin, TX) @ 12:10 PM
http://www.western-youth.com/
"hailing from Austin, TX by way of Dallas, Detroit and Otago, New Zealand, Western Youth staggers between beer-drenched rock n' roll, folk and alt. country to create a sound that's all their own."

Drew Kennedy (New Braunfels, TX) @ 12:50 PM
http://www.drewkennedymusic.com/
"his knack for detail and a touch of wry wit allows him to hit up those old themes of heartache, travel, and regret for one more dance with his distinctive baritone drawl."

"an americana/alt-country/gang of picker-gypsies from Dallas, Texas."

Nicolette Good (San Antonio, TX) @ 2:10 PM
http://nicolettegood.com/
[Nicolette Good's] "voice is pure ear candy. It’s an ethereal thing, one part smoky youth, another part fluorescent wisdom, a dream you just woke up from and are dying to remember.”

Daniel Markham (Denton via Lubbock, TX) @ 3:00 PM
http://danielmarkham.bandcamp.com/
"dark but hopeful melodies that will get stuck in your head like a misguided dart. All hearts will be broken."

http://www.myspace.com/serynsound
"like listening to the soundtrack of a great love story, breathtaking drama, and a dark tragedy all rolled into one over-the-top, unparalleled performance"

https://www.facebook.com/longproblems
"low-fi, confessional rock with a teenager's capacity for heartbreak and a man's penchant for ruining things."

http://www.thekinfolk.com/
"the Kinfolk are us and you and everyone, too."

Telegraph Canyon (Ft Worth, TX) @ 6:15pm
http://www.telegraphcanyon.net/
"combines compelling songwriting with layers of driving, dynamic sounds only to, at times, strip it all away and expose a raw and gentle undercurrent"

http://lpaustin.com/

Thanks to the amazing ShowLush, our gracious hosts at La Patisserie, and our sponsors, there will be complimentary Zhi Tea, Lone Star & PBR Beer as well as Texas' favorite Vodka.*

You decide. |-----------------------------------------------------------------|The next chapter of the Business Friendship Agreement, established in 2012 between Austin, Texas and the London Borough of Hackney, will see a delegation of some of the most exciting and innovative companies travelling from London’s East End to showcase their wares in Austin this March 8-11, during the city’s SXSW Interactive 2013 festival. This trip reciprocates last year’s visit by Austin’s Mayor Lee Leffingwell and his digital media trade mission, organised to foster exchange in the areas of high-tech and digital media, the creative industries, economic development, and sustainability. The Hackney team will be setting up as Hackney House Austin – an international travelling ‘capsule’ edition of 2012’s stunning and successful urban pop-up space, set up in Hackney's Shoreditch district during last year’s Olympic Games. Created by Hackney Council to act as a hub for new investment to Hackney, it succeeded in showcasing this cluster of culturally relevant creative businesses currently making their global mark. For four days only, Hackney House Austin will transform a 3,000+ sq ft space on 6th Street into the ultimate Hackney-inspired workshop space. Through a carefully curated programme of Art, Design, Music, Film, Product and Events, 25 local businesses will have the opportunity to spotlight their work, network with Austin friends, entertain and enlighten, all within an exceptional space. By day, Hackney House Austin will be a welcoming hangout, complete with free WIFI and coffee, meeting spaces, and power chargers. Come by between 10am – 2pm and the space will be filled with a curated programme of short films by Protein, onedotzero and ITV. The Sugru repair shop will be open for business, and you’ll be invited to drop by and pick up your pre-ordered business cards by Moo. The afternoons see us amp up the pace with panels and workshops byMakieLab and onedotzero, as well as a screening of Choose Your Own Documentary presented by ITV. Protein will (re)launch its premium video content platform Protein TV at the ‘Future of TV’ forum, featuring experts in the field of television and hosted by Protein’s Founder and CEO William Rowe. The supporting, 4-day programme of events will confirm Hackney House Austin as the key destination for showcasing Hackney’s best new ideas and business networking. Styled with beautiful products straight out of Hackney including a 2m2 Plumen chandelier and the Goodnight Lamp, Hackney House Austin is an open opportunity for guests to meet Hackney’s top creative and digital companies, including: Bare Conductive, BERG, Choose Your Own Documentary, The Church of London, Dezeen, Digital Shoreditch, Goodnight Lamp, Hulger, iCITY, Kahoot! Makielab, Mixcloud, MOO, Mother, Not Tom, onedotzero, POKE, Protein,Sugru, Technology Will Save Us and Trampery. Follow us on Twitter at @HackneyHouse13 #HackneyHouseAustin |“Our friendship with the City of Austin is leading us into exciting territory, the SXSW festival is the perfect destination for Hackney House bringing with it the best of Hackney’s creative, design and tech sectors to showcase their world leading ideas, develop new relationships and form new ventures” said Guy Nicholson, lead Cabinet Member for Economic Development and Regeneration at the London Borough of Hackney.”|Please note that registering for an event does not guarantee admission. Admission is granted on a first come, first served basis to those who have booked through Eventbrite. Schedule subject to change. |Hackney House Austin|119 W 6th StAustin, TX 78701|For details see our upcoming events see here|And don't forget…|Keep up to date with the news and events through our Facebook page and Twitter feeds.| http://www.facebook.com/pages/Hackney-House/217051391742967?ref=ts&fref=ts https://twitter.com/HackneyHouse13
column14:
Free Entry with RSVP on Do512!

HACKNEY HOUSE Austin March 8th-11th, 2013


March 9th Events:


Minibar Meetup x Mother - 5pm to 9pm


The legendary meetup that is Minibar comes to Austin Texas for the very first time.


MiniBar is a social evening that has been running for the last seven years in Shoreditch, which offers people a chance to snaffle some free beer while discussing mobile web, web applications, start ups, social networking, investment and general Web 2.0 mayhem & fandango.


It is held every month at Mother London in Shoreditch's iconic Tea Building.

There is usually a brilliant mix of around 250 web entrepreneurs, developers, tech investors and other geeks plus a few 5 min presentations on what's hot right now.


elevenfiftyfive x Little White Lies Cinema Forum - 5pm to 6pm


Join elevenfiftyfive and Little White Lies for an exciting double-bill exploring cinema and its evolving connection with audiences.


Film Production and Distribution via Brand Support: elevenfiftyfive


Since 2008 elevenfiftyfive have been working with brands to connect with audiences through film whilst supporting the film industry. Understanding that shared objectives, reward and utility are key to success, elevenfiftyfive will talk through emerging areas of film open to brand partnerships.


Film Journalism Uncut: Little White Lies


The film landscape is changing rapidly but one thing remains the same: the power of cinema to connect with audiences. One of the sector’s most innovative players will explore how audiences are (and will be) engaging with conversations around film both online and off.


Protein Forum: The Future of TV - 4pm to 5pm


One part TED-style talks, one part discussion, and one part social club, Protein Forums are events designed to inspire and provoke, covering the most relevant issues and topics that are changing consumer behaviour. Protein brings their renowned Forum series to Austin for the first time on Saturday 9th March with "The Future of TV", a forum featuring experts in the field of television including Blake Whitman (Vimeo), Costas Syrmos (Nokia) and Fernando Gutierrez De Jesus (ITV NEW), and hosted by Protein’s Founder and CEO William Rowe.

The forum will mark the re-release of the original Protein TV platform first launched in February 1999. Hailed as "Europe's first online TV channel", its aim was to deliver 60 mins of exclusive, diverse, entertaining and engaging selection of cultural programming (known as "pods") every month. In March 2013, Protein TV is reincarnated as an online platform curating the world's best video content from our global media network including Dezeen, Resident Advisor, and many more.

Join us at "The Future of TV" forum and please drop by our Protein TV stand located in the space 8-11 March, where you can watch Protein TV throughout the day.


Choose Your Own Documentary - 2pm to 4pm


Pages from a forgotten diary fall from a book you buy on eBay, what do you do?...YOU decide


Inspired by the ‘Choose Your Own Adventure’ phenomenon of the 1980s - Nathan Penlington’s Choose Your Own Documentary tells the true story of the discovery of a long-forgotten diary and his attempts to unravel its many mysteries. Part stand-up, part film documentary and part spoken word, it’s a unique and compelling interactive experience in which the audience play the most important role.


With over 1500 possible versions, and multiple endings, every performance is different. At each twist and turn it’s the audience who dictate which paths the documentary takes - whether Nathan meets with success, failure, or the unexpected, depends on the choices audience members make via remote control. Where will the story lead? How will the story end? You decide.



-----------------------------------------------------------------



The next chapter of the Business Friendship Agreement, established in 2012 between Austin, Texas and the London Borough of Hackney, will see a delegation of some of the most exciting and innovative companies travelling from London’s East End to showcase their wares in Austin this March 8-11, during the city’s SXSW Interactive 2013 festival.

This trip reciprocates last year’s visit by Austin’s Mayor Lee Leffingwell and his digital media trade mission, organised to foster exchange in the areas of high-tech and digital media, the creative industries, economic development, and sustainability.

The Hackney team will be setting up as Hackney House Austin – an international travelling ‘capsule’ edition of 2012’s stunning and successful urban pop-up space, set up in Hackney's Shoreditch district during last year’s Olympic Games. Created by Hackney Council to act as a hub for new investment to Hackney, it succeeded in showcasing this cluster of culturally relevant creative businesses currently making their global mark.

For four days only, Hackney House Austin will transform a 3,000+ sq ft space on 6th Street into the ultimate Hackney-inspired workshop space. Through a carefully curated programme of Art, Design, Music, Film, Product and Events, 25 local businesses will have the opportunity to spotlight their work, network with Austin friends, entertain and enlighten, all within an exceptional space.

By day, Hackney House Austin will be a welcoming hangout, complete with free WIFI and coffee, meeting spaces, and power chargers. Come by between 10am – 2pm and the space will be filled with a curated programme of short films by Protein, onedotzero and ITV. The Sugru repair shop will be open for business, and you’ll be invited to drop by and pick up your pre-ordered business cards by Moo.

The afternoons see us amp up the pace with panels and workshops byMakieLab and onedotzero, as well as a screening of Choose Your Own Documentary presented by ITV. Protein will (re)launch its premium video content platform Protein TV at the ‘Future of TV’ forum, featuring experts in the field of television and hosted by Protein’s Founder and CEO William Rowe.

The supporting, 4-day programme of events will confirm Hackney House Austin as the key destination for showcasing Hackney’s best new ideas and business networking. Styled with beautiful products straight out of Hackney including a 2m2 Plumen chandelier and the Goodnight Lamp, Hackney House Austin is an open opportunity for guests to meet Hackney’s top creative and digital companies, including: Bare Conductive, BERG, Choose Your Own Documentary, The Church of London, Dezeen, Digital Shoreditch, Goodnight Lamp, Hulger, iCITY, Kahoot! Makielab, Mixcloud, MOO, Mother, Not Tom, onedotzero, POKE, Protein,Sugru, Technology Will Save Us and Trampery.

Follow us on Twitter at @HackneyHouse13 #HackneyHouseAustin


“Our friendship with the City of Austin is leading us into exciting territory, the SXSW festival is the perfect destination for Hackney House bringing with it the best of Hackney’s creative, design and tech sectors to showcase their world leading ideas, develop new relationships and form new ventures” said Guy Nicholson, lead Cabinet Member for Economic Development and Regeneration at the London Borough of Hackney.”

Social bike ride details:
The Skellies are very honored to be supporting this amazing Sound Barrier Kick Off Party showcasing tons of musical talent. We ride bikes, we have fun and we're nice to people. Ride bikes? Join us on a little cruise to the party! The Skellies are hosting a very leisurely and social bike ride, where we'll have some fun on two-wheels rolling around these fine Austin streets going straight to the event.

Everyone is invited! On the day of the Sound Barrier Kick Off Party, Tuesday March 12th, bring your bikes and your butts. We'll meet up at The Grackle (1700 E 6th) at 7pm, and roll out shortly after. column14:
Free Entry with RSVP on Do512!

HACKNEY HOUSE Austin March 8th-11th, 2013


March 11th Events:


Digital Shoreditch 2013 Preview - 4pm to 5pm


Digital Shoreditch is the festival celebrating the outstanding creative, technical and entrepreneurial talent of London's Tech City and beyond. The festival runs from May 20th to 31st 2013, includes talks, showcases, competitions, workshops, open studios, exhibitions and parties that will engage, inspire and celebrate the cream of the digital crop.


Over the two weeks the festival brings together outstanding local and international talent. With themes for each day covering a range of topics from what’s next in digital, interactivity and play to funding, capital and brands to innovation, design and new ideas.


Experience the buzz of Hackney's biggest digital festival as the main man, Kam Star, gives you a whirlwind tour of all things to come at Digital Shoreditch 2013.


www.digitalshoreditch.com


Digital Enlightenment and Innovation - 2pm to 4pm


What can 6 youths with nothing but passion and creativity accomplish in a weekend? We took a group of talented, yet computer science illiterate young adults, gave them a crash course in coding and innovation, and came up with something that would amaze even the most demanding of admen.

Smile Machine's Account Director Eric Brotto will explain, step by step, how the weekend was structured, what code was written and how the ideas came into being. Decoded's Business Director Anika Saigal will also be on hand to discuss Decoded's involvement in the project and how, even if you don't need to be a coder, you need to understand the power of code and how it can be used.

*The weekend workshop was created in conjunction with four agencies: Livity, Urgent Genius, Decoded and Smile Machine.


-----------------------------------------------------------


The next chapter of the Business Friendship Agreement, established in 2012 between Austin, Texas and the London Borough of Hackney, will see a delegation of some of the most exciting and innovative companies travelling from London’s East End to showcase their wares in Austin this March 8-11, during the city’s SXSW Interactive 2013 festival.

This trip reciprocates last year’s visit by Austin’s Mayor Lee Leffingwell and his digital media trade mission, organised to foster exchange in the areas of high-tech and digital media, the creative industries, economic development, and sustainability.

The Hackney team will be setting up as Hackney House Austin – an international travelling ‘capsule’ edition of 2012’s stunning and successful urban pop-up space, set up in Hackney's Shoreditch district during last year’s Olympic Games. Created by Hackney Council to act as a hub for new investment to Hackney, it succeeded in showcasing this cluster of culturally relevant creative businesses currently making their global mark.

For four days only, Hackney House Austin will transform a 3,000+ sq ft space on 6th Street into the ultimate Hackney-inspired workshop space. Through a carefully curated programme of Art, Design, Music, Film, Product and Events, 25 local businesses will have the opportunity to spotlight their work, network with Austin friends, entertain and enlighten, all within an exceptional space.

By day, Hackney House Austin will be a welcoming hangout, complete with free WIFI and coffee, meeting spaces, and power chargers. Come by between 10am – 2pm and the space will be filled with a curated programme of short films by Protein, onedotzero and ITV. The Sugru repair shop will be open for business, and you’ll be invited to drop by and pick up your pre-ordered business cards by Moo.

The afternoons see us amp up the pace with panels and workshops byMakieLab and onedotzero, as well as a screening of Choose Your Own Documentary presented by ITV. Protein will (re)launch its premium video content platform Protein TV at the ‘Future of TV’ forum, featuring experts in the field of television and hosted by Protein’s Founder and CEO William Rowe.

The supporting, 4-day programme of events will confirm Hackney House Austin as the key destination for showcasing Hackney’s best new ideas and business networking. Styled with beautiful products straight out of Hackney including a 2m2 Plumen chandelier and the Goodnight Lamp, Hackney House Austin is an open opportunity for guests to meet Hackney’s top creative and digital companies, including: Bare Conductive, BERG, Choose Your Own Documentary, The Church of London, Dezeen, Digital Shoreditch, Goodnight Lamp, Hulger, iCITY, Kahoot! Makielab, Mixcloud, MOO, Mother, Not Tom, onedotzero, POKE, Protein,Sugru, Technology Will Save Us and Trampery.

Follow us on Twitter at @HackneyHouse13 #HackneyHouseAustin


“Our friendship with the City of Austin is leading us into exciting territory, the SXSW festival is the perfect destination for Hackney House bringing with it the best of Hackney’s creative, design and tech sectors to showcase their world leading ideas, develop new relationships and form new ventures” said Guy Nicholson, lead Cabinet Member for Economic Development and Regeneration at the London Borough of Hackney.”

column14:
Free Entry with RSVP on Do512!

HACKNEY HOUSE Austin March 8th-11th, 2013


March 10th Events:


Hackney x Austin Mixer - 6pm to 8pm


The spirit of Hackney storms into Austin bringing an evening of celebration and exclusive entertainment.


This is your opportunity to meet with the movers and shakers of the heart of London which also stands out as the Digital capital of Europe. As the friendship agreement between Austin and Hackney is strengthened through this unique partnership, take the opportunity to make contact with anyone who's anyone from Austin and Hackney.


Hackney House - Managing the monster: How to operate a Corporate Startup - 5pm to 6pm

Albion: Design Director Jonty Sharples and Technical Director Andy Beaumont


A new methodology is taking hold - a kind of Franken-start-up. Allowing for swift product conception, delivery, and iteration by small, highly skilled teams the model is increasingly being adopted by multi-national corporations who see the business benefits of behaving like entrepreneurial teams.

The session will examine this new way of working, how best to implement it, the pitfalls to watch out for, and how to make projects a success using it - from both an agency and client perspective.


onedotzero: "Technology + Making" with Technology Will Save Us - 4pm to 5pm


onedotzero presents

'Technology + Making'

with Technology Will Save Us


Makielab: Story of the First CE-certified 3D Printed Toy - 3pm to 4pm


MakieLab is a London-based company making internet-connected customisable playthings. Formed in 2011, MakieLab has created technology to create physical toys from digital game objects, starting with avatars. Its first product, Makies™, is a world-first: a customisable 3D-printed action figure, CE-marked and EU-certified safe for kids aged 3+.


Come and listen to our story and see how we develop Makies, the world's first CE-certified 3D printed toy. :)

Bare Conductive Workshop - 2pm to 4pm


Do you like painting? Are you interested in electronics? Imagine being able to create circuits just by drawing them directly on paper! Bare Conductive’s Electrically Conductive Paint lets you do just that. Swing by and find out more about the future of paper electronics, or if you're in a making mood, join in our workshop and make your own blinking LED badge with Bare Paint!


Bare Conductive is revolutionizing the way people think about electronics through it's unique range of products. From DIY electronic greeting cards, to 3D paper crafts and non-toxic electrically conductive paint, Bare Conductive is lowering the barrier to scientific learning and making electronics fun for everyone!


This pratical workshop allows you to experience this innovative technology and get involved making something extraordinary....



-----------------------------------------------------------


The next chapter of the Business Friendship Agreement, established in 2012 between Austin, Texas and the London Borough of Hackney, will see a delegation of some of the most exciting and innovative companies travelling from London’s East End to showcase their wares in Austin this March 8-11, during the city’s SXSW Interactive 2013 festival.

This trip reciprocates last year’s visit by Austin’s Mayor Lee Leffingwell and his digital media trade mission, organised to foster exchange in the areas of high-tech and digital media, the creative industries, economic development, and sustainability.

The Hackney team will be setting up as Hackney House Austin – an international travelling ‘capsule’ edition of 2012’s stunning and successful urban pop-up space, set up in Hackney's Shoreditch district during last year’s Olympic Games. Created by Hackney Council to act as a hub for new investment to Hackney, it succeeded in showcasing this cluster of culturally relevant creative businesses currently making their global mark.

For four days only, Hackney House Austin will transform a 3,000+ sq ft space on 6th Street into the ultimate Hackney-inspired workshop space. Through a carefully curated programme of Art, Design, Music, Film, Product and Events, 25 local businesses will have the opportunity to spotlight their work, network with Austin friends, entertain and enlighten, all within an exceptional space.

By day, Hackney House Austin will be a welcoming hangout, complete with free WIFI and coffee, meeting spaces, and power chargers. Come by between 10am – 2pm and the space will be filled with a curated programme of short films by Protein, onedotzero and ITV. The Sugru repair shop will be open for business, and you’ll be invited to drop by and pick up your pre-ordered business cards by Moo.

The afternoons see us amp up the pace with panels and workshops byMakieLab and onedotzero, as well as a screening of Choose Your Own Documentary presented by ITV. Protein will (re)launch its premium video content platform Protein TV at the ‘Future of TV’ forum, featuring experts in the field of television and hosted by Protein’s Founder and CEO William Rowe.

The supporting, 4-day programme of events will confirm Hackney House Austin as the key destination for showcasing Hackney’s best new ideas and business networking. Styled with beautiful products straight out of Hackney including a 2m2 Plumen chandelier and the Goodnight Lamp, Hackney House Austin is an open opportunity for guests to meet Hackney’s top creative and digital companies, including: Bare Conductive, BERG, Choose Your Own Documentary, The Church of London, Dezeen, Digital Shoreditch, Goodnight Lamp, Hulger, iCITY, Kahoot! Makielab, Mixcloud, MOO, Mother, Not Tom, onedotzero, POKE, Protein,Sugru, Technology Will Save Us and Trampery.

Follow us on Twitter at @HackneyHouse13 #HackneyHouseAustin


“Our friendship with the City of Austin is leading us into exciting territory, the SXSW festival is the perfect destination for Hackney House bringing with it the best of Hackney’s creative, design and tech sectors to showcase their world leading ideas, develop new relationships and form new ventures” said Guy Nicholson, lead Cabinet Member for Economic Development and Regeneration at the London Borough of Hackney.”


Please note that registering for an event does not guarantee admission. Admission is granted on a first come, first served basis to those who have booked through Eventbrite. Schedule subject to change.


Hackney House Austin


119 W 6th St

Austin, TX 78701


For details see our upcoming events see here


And don't forget…

Keep up to date with the news and events through our Facebook page and Twitter feeds.


http://www.facebook.com/pages/Hackney-House/217051391742967?ref=ts&fref=ts

https://twitter.com/HackneyHouse13

column14:
Spirithouse, IndyMusicSales.com, and The Collective Music Group Present...

The Northampton Comes To Austin Mobile Studio!!

Thursday March 14th- Friday March 15th

Tamale House East
1707 E 6th St.
2pm-10pm

The Northampton Comes To Austin Mobile Studio will take place in an RV set up at the Tamale House East during SXSW. Northampton based artists will host the best independent musicians from around the world to record and collaborate in this truly unique space. The live performances and collaborations on the RV will be recorded by Spirithouse Studios and videotaped for release on YouTube. Industry tastemaker 93.9 The River has also joined the project as a media partner and will broadcast “live” recordings from the RV throughout the festival to thousands of music fans around the world!


A stage will also be set up outside the RV and various acts will perform throughout the day/evening on both the 14th and 15th.


Come on by the Tamale House, grab some food, check out the studio, dance your ass off, and be a part of this killer live music experience!!

Free Entry with RSVP on Do512!

FEATURED VERY SPECIAL GUESTS!

The AfterDark x V Productions Closing Party!!!!

-----
When the beat drops at a Nadastrom show, you better have your hands up. Dave Nada is known to stage dive while his DJ partner Matt Nordstrom squeezes the duo’s most riotous beats through the speakers. It’s a reminder Nadastrom aren’t just pushing 21st century dance music toward the edge – they’re jumping off it.
The D.C.-born, L.A.-based duo of DJ-producers come from different
backgrounds, but share a ravenous appetite for extremes. As the prime architects of Moombahton – a sound Nada invented on the fly at a basement party by slowing Dutch house music down to the tempo of reggaeton – the duo have been praised in the pages of Spin and Rolling Stone, pumped on the airwaves of BBC Radio 1 and NPR, and revered at nightclubs and festivals across the planet.


more info to come...

@ The W Hotel

column2: Our Heart Aches For Syria: Red Cross Benefit Concert (No Badges Req)
column5: Long Center for the Performing Arts
column12: The Young,The Orwells,White Lung,Deer Tick,Omar Souleyman,Black Lips
column13: "SXSW is proud to announce an interview with Syrian artist and cult international legend Omar Souleyman on March 15th from 5-6pm in ACC room 16AB. Omar will speak with Daily Dot Editor Austin Powell about the issues surrounding the devastating conflict in his home country, the evolution of the Syrian music landscape, and what the future may hold for himself and artists like him."|"Later that evening Omar will be joined by the amazing Black Lips, Deer Tick and more in a special performance at a Red Cross benefit aptly named Our Heart Aches For Syria. The show takes place at Long Center For The Performing Arts beginning at 9pm on Friday 3/15 after the Flaming Lips Auditorium Shores show. Donations are $10 with all money going to the International Red Cross's Syrian Arab Red Crescent. Please join us for a spectacular evening for a great cause. THIS SHOW IS OPEN TO THE GENERAL PUBLIC"|Our Heart Aches For Syria|Friday March 15, doors at 8PM|Long Center For The Performing Arts|9:00-9:25 - The Young|9:40-10:05 - Orwells|10:20-10:45 - White Lung|11:00-11:40 - Deer Tick|12:00-12:40 - Omar Souleyman|1:00-1:40 - Black Lips|via SXSW
column14:
"SXSW is proud to announce an interview with Syrian artist and cult international legend Omar Souleyman on March 15th from 5-6pm in ACC room 16AB. Omar will speak with Daily Dot Editor Austin Powell about the issues surrounding the devastating conflict in his home country, the evolution of the Syrian music landscape, and what the future may hold for himself and artists like him."


"Later that evening Omar will be joined by the amazing Black Lips, Deer Tick and more in a special performance at a Red Cross benefit aptly named Our Heart Aches For Syria. The show takes place at Long Center For The Performing Arts beginning at 9pm on Friday 3/15 after the Flaming Lips Auditorium Shores show. Donations are $10 with all money going to the International Red Cross's Syrian Arab Red Crescent. Please join us for a spectacular evening for a great cause. THIS SHOW IS OPEN TO THE GENERAL PUBLIC"


Our Heart Aches For Syria
Friday March 15, doors at 8PM


Long Center For The Performing Arts

9:40-10:05 - Orwells

@ The W Hotel

It's time for the big lineup reveal! We're very excited to be welcoming the following artists. Last year’s line-up included Grammy performers fun., The Lumineers, and Ed Sheeran. 9:30am | Bob Schneider w/ The Tosca String Quartet

There are several paid parking options, including valet at the hotel, the City Hall garage at 2nd and Caesar Chavez, and the Amli located across the street from The W Austin Hotel. Entry is not guaranteed so make sure to arrive early.

Passion Pit and Wildcat! Wildcat!

When: Monday, March 11th 8pm CST
Where: Hype Hotel, 301 Brazos Street Austin, TX
Why: Because we’re not making an experimental fan-made Rockumentary. You are.

Help shoot and direct an experimental, fan-made Rockumentary starring Passion Pit and Wildcat! Wildcat! Shot live from the Hype Hotel at SXSW on Monday, March 11th.

Premiered on Twitter. Co-Directed by thousands of fans.

Want in? All you have to do is go to www.feedthebeat.com and get your assignments from an acclaimed director. Then, submit your piece of the film by Tweeting with #FeedTheBeat

Anything you capture, tweet, and share to #FeedTheBeat could be used in the Rockumentary.

By RSVPing to this event you consent to any likeness and/or footage being used in the music documentary mentioned above.

*Please arrive early; entrance is subject to venue capacity. Must be at least 21 years old to enter.

The Austin Music Awards are presented by The Austin Chronicle and SXSW and co-sponsored by KUTX, Planet K, Discount Electronics, Ticketbud and is a benefit for the SIMS Foundation. This year, the Music Awards show will air live on America’s longest, continually running community television station, channelAustin (Channel 10).

column14:
SPIN's 2013 Party at Stubb's:

SPIN has already announced that the man behind one of our favorite albums of last year,Kendrick Lamar, will be headlining our annual Austin throwdown on March 15 — now we're pleased to reveal the rest of the bill for our bash at Stubb's BBQ (and more!).


The Stubb's lineup buzzes with a diverse array of today's most original young artists, led by provocative R&B innovator Solange, who released one of 2012 finest singles, "Losing You," and will unleash one of the the year's most-anticipated full-lengths in 2013. Other SPIN faves who will taking the Stubb's stage: heavenly Scottish synth-pop romantics CHVRCHES, intoxicatingly melancholy psych-soul trio Unknown Mortal Orchestra, and New York indie upstarts Parquet Courts, who come on like Pavement with Wire's rhythm section, yet also very stoned. Plus, as a token of our appreciation, SPIN has arranged for a special appearance by the rap game's own King of Mollywood, Trinidad James, of "All Gold Everything" fame. In addition, head-spinning DJs Jackmaster, Oneman, and Machinedrum will hit the decks between acts.


It all goes down from noon until 6 p.m. with the generous assistance of our sponsors Crispin Cider, Embassy Suites, esurance, SESAC, and Smirnoff Master of the Mix. And guess what: Some of you can win the chance to attend this historic throwdown! Follow @SPINsxsw for details, we'll have an announcement coming soon!

Kendrick Lamar
Solange
CHVRCHES
Unknown Mortal Orchestra
Parquet Courts

Oneman
