This year’s Paste party at SXSW will be bigger than ever. Four days. Forty-four bands.


HGTV has teamed up with Paste for our ninth annual party in Austin, Texas, at SXSW, March 13-16. With 11 bands per day, the lineup includes both some of the festival’s most exciting veteran performers including Billy Bragg, Buddy Miller & Jim Lauderdale, Josh Ritter and The Zombies, as well as newcomers like Foxygen, The Lone Bellow and GUARDS.


Last year, HGTV and Paste paired together to find The New Sound of HGTV. Grand prize winner CR Smith, whose music has been regularly featured on the channel, will be playing the Austin event, as well.


The SXSW Official four-day party will be held at one of 6th Street’s biggest music venues, The Stage on Sixth (508 E.6th Street), from noon to 6pm.

column12: Jim James,Michael Kiwanuka,Shovels and Rope,Phosphorescent,Diamond Rugs,Elle King,The Treasures,Houndmouth,The Happenins,Will Johnson,Valerie June,Shakey Graves,Spirit Family Reunion,Samantha Crain,Jonny Burke,The Mastersons,The Lonesome Heroes
column13: Electric Lady Studios and Robot Fondue, in association with John Varvatos, will present Heartbreaker Banquet, an unparalleled concert experience, atWillie Nelson’s “Luck, Texas” western town in Austin. Heartbreaker Banquetis an exclusive event for media, tastemakers, and special guests featuring live musical performances, unique pop-up shops, and special attractions. The event will be held on Thursday, March 14 from Noon until 11PM. Heartbreaker Banquet provides guests a one-of-a-kind music experience completely removed from the SXSW festival hoards. Electric Lady Studios andRobot Fondue have curated a full day of music, food, fashion, and featured attractions held at Nelson’s “Luck, Texas”, a longtime creative hub for some of the world’s most heralded musicians. The concert will showcase artists on two main stages: an outdoor “Medicine Show” stage for featured performances; and an acoustic stage in the town’s intimate 50-seat chapel, where guests have the opportunity to sit within arm’s length of their favorite artists. “Medicine Show” Stage:Jim James, Michael Kiwanuka, Phosphorescent, Shovels & Rope, Diamond Rugs,Elle King, Houndmouth, and The Treasures Acoustic Chapel Stage:Will Johnson, Hurray For The Riff Raff, Valerie June, Shakey Graves, Spirit Family Reunion, Samantha Crain, The Tumbleweeds, Lonesome Heroes, Jonny Burke,The Mastersons, and The Happen-Ins The event will feature live musical performances, food trucks curated by Immaculate Infatuation, a tattoo parlor, and event lighting and design from Austin's Gypsy Sun Vintage. Jack White’s own Third Man Records “Rolling Record Store” will serve Heartbreaker’s official record pop-up shop. Ticketholders will have the option of taking private buses from a select number of hotspots in Austin directly to the venue. Guest parking will also be available, and a shuttle service will be running the short distance between the parking lot and the venue throughout the night. Heartbreaker Banquet 2013 is benefiting the SIMS Foundation, providing mental health services to Austin Musicians. On behalf of SIMS, we encourage patrons to make a tax-deductible donation hereFor more information on the event, please visit http://www.heartbreakerbanquet.com/ or http://www.facebook.com/heartbreakerbanquet. |Follow on Twitter at @HBbanquet.

column2: HEAR THERE. EVERYWHERE. The 6th Annual Dart Music International House - Day One
column12: Gina Chavez,Galaxy Express,Ane Trolle,The Mornings
column13: HEAR THERE. EVERYWHERE.|The 6th Annual Dart Music International HouseSince 2008 DMI has helped Austin "Hear There. Everywhere." by presenting unprecedented international cultural events in Austin during the big festival week. Some of the highlights have included historic events like "Music From Space" (an exclusive video from the International Space Station), "6 Bands 6 Continents" (back-to-back performances by artists from every inhabited continent), and "Taquacore + i:Made in Israel + ATX Hip Hop" (Iranian, Israeli, and Austin artists performing together). |This year is going to add to that legacy in an informal, "happy hour" setting. From Tuesday, March 12 through Friday, March 15, in between the music panels / day parties and the nightly showcases, DMI will be producing the 6th Annual Dart Music International House event in downtown Austin. column14:
HEAR THERE. EVERYWHERE.
The 6th Annual Dart Music International House

Since 2008 DMI has helped Austin "Hear There. Everywhere." by presenting unprecedented international cultural events in Austin during the big festival week. Some of the highlights have included historic events like "Music From Space" (an exclusive video from the International Space Station), "6 Bands 6 Continents" (back-to-back performances by artists from every inhabited continent), and "Taquacore + i:Made in Israel + ATX Hip Hop" (Iranian, Israeli, and Austin artists performing together).


This year is going to add to that legacy in an informal, "happy hour" setting. From Tuesday, March 12 through Friday, March 15, in between the music panels / day parties and the nightly showcases, DMI will be producing the 6th Annual Dart Music International House event in downtown Austin. This is your opportunity of a lifetime to experience global culture in an informal setting. We hope to see you there!


WHEN: Tuesday, March 12 through Friday, March 15, 2013; 5-8PM Daily
WHERE: Mark McCrimmon Law Office, 704 West 9th Street (Map)
WHAT: Music & culture with Artists from Every Inhabited Continent
WHO: Complimentary food and drinks from The Peached Tortilla, Austin Beerworks, Tito's Handmade Vodka, and more.
ADMISSION: FREE, ALL AGES


This project is funded and supported in part by the City of Austin through the Economic Growth & Redevelopment Services Office / Cultural Arts Division believing an investment in the Arts is an investment in Austin's future. Visit Austin at NowPlayingAustin.com.

column14:
We had this as a rumor - now we know JT will be here! Will update with details as we get 'em.



Via Justin Timberlake's Open Letter

This year is an exciting one for me. As you probably have heard through the "grapevine," I'm gearing up for a big 2013.


Back in June of last year, I quietly started working on what is now, my next journey with that thing I love called MUSIC.


The inspiration for this really came out of the blue and to be honest, I didn't expect anything out of it. I just went into the studio and started playing around with some sounds and songs. It was probably the best time I've had in my career... Just creating with no rules and/or end goal in mind and really enjoying the process.


What I came up with is something I couldn't be more excited about! It is full of inspiration that I grew up listening to and some newfound muses that I've discovered along the way.

I'm calling it "The 20/20 Experience," and it's coming out this year.


I hope you enjoy listening to it as much as I enjoyed making it.


That's all I'm giving you for now... I know, I know! Again, with the teasing!!!

Get ready. This is going to be fun (well, at least it is for me).

Highlights & Special Events: 100 Films, Superior Cinephile Contest, Unlimited Libations, Celebrity Appearances, Late Late Thursday Night Social Ride After Party, Special Event Premiere of Danko Jones (Lemmy Kilmister, Elijah Wood, Selma Blair, & Mike Watt), and NO BADGES/WRISTBANDS REQUIRED.

One film from each category will travel to the Victoria, TX Independent Film Festival, held April 4-7 2013, to compete for cash prizes totaling $5,000. As always Rxsm is FREE!

This year’s Paste party at SXSW will be bigger than ever. Four days. Forty-four bands.


HGTV has teamed up with Paste for our ninth annual party in Austin, Texas, at SXSW, March 13-16. With 11 bands per day, the lineup includes both some of the festival’s most exciting veteran performers including Billy Bragg, Buddy Miller & Jim Lauderdale, Josh Ritter and The Zombies, as well as newcomers like Foxygen, The Lone Bellow and GUARDS.


Last year, HGTV and Paste paired together to find The New Sound of HGTV. Grand prize winner CR Smith, whose music has been regularly featured on the channel, will be playing the Austin event, as well.


The SXSW Official four-day party will be held at one of 6th Street’s biggest music venues, The Stage on Sixth (508 E.6th Street), from noon to 6pm.

column13: Tickets on sale November 30th @ 10:00AM |Rock ‘n’ roll legend Eric Clapton will headline a concert at the Frank Erwin Center Sunday, March 17 with special guest The Wallflowers. The stop in Austin will be Clapton’s only appearance in the area.Clapton is the only three-time inductee into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame, has won 17 Grammy awards and placed second on Rolling Stone’s list of the “100 Greatest Guitarists of All Time” last year. This will be Clapton’s third concert at the Frank Erwin Center and the first in almost 18 years.Clapton has assembled an impressive band for the U.S. dates, which will consist of long-time touring partners Doyle Bramhall II (guitar), Steve Jordan (drums), Chris Stainton (piano and keyboards) and Willie Weeks (bass), along with newcomers Paul Carrack (organ and keyboards) and Greg Leisz (pedal steel guitar). Michelle John and Sharon White will join the touring band again as backing vocalists.
column14:
Tickets on sale November 30th @ 10:00AM


Rock ‘n’ roll legend Eric Clapton will headline a concert at the Frank Erwin Center Sunday, March 17 with special guest The Wallflowers. The stop in Austin will be Clapton’s only appearance in the area.

Clapton is the only three-time inductee into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame, has won 17 Grammy awards and placed second on Rolling Stone’s list of the “100 Greatest Guitarists of All Time” last year. This will be Clapton’s third concert at the Frank Erwin Center and the first in almost 18 years.

Clapton has assembled an impressive band for the U.S. dates, which will consist of long-time touring partners Doyle Bramhall II (guitar), Steve Jordan (drums), Chris Stainton (piano and keyboards) and Willie Weeks (bass), along with newcomers Paul Carrack (organ and keyboards) and Greg Leisz (pedal steel guitar). Michelle John and Sharon White will join the touring band again as backing vocalists.

This year’s Paste party at SXSW will be bigger than ever. Four days. Forty-four bands.


HGTV has teamed up with Paste for our ninth annual party in Austin, Texas, at SXSW, March 13-16. With 11 bands per day, the lineup includes both some of the festival’s most exciting veteran performers including Billy Bragg, Buddy Miller & Jim Lauderdale, Josh Ritter and The Zombies, as well as newcomers like Foxygen, The Lone Bellow and GUARDS.


Last year, HGTV and Paste paired together to find The New Sound of HGTV. Grand prize winner CR Smith, whose music has been regularly featured on the channel, will be playing the Austin event, as well.


The SXSW Official four-day party will be held at one of 6th Street’s biggest music venues, The Stage on Sixth (508 E.6th Street), from noon to 6pm.

This year’s Paste party at SXSW will be bigger than ever. Four days. Forty-four bands.


HGTV has teamed up with Paste for our ninth annual party in Austin, Texas, at SXSW, March 13-16. With 11 bands per day, the lineup includes both some of the festival’s most exciting veteran performers including Billy Bragg, Buddy Miller & Jim Lauderdale, Josh Ritter and The Zombies, as well as newcomers like Foxygen, The Lone Bellow and GUARDS.


Last year, HGTV and Paste paired together to find The New Sound of HGTV. Grand prize winner CR Smith, whose music has been regularly featured on the channel, will be playing the Austin event, as well.


The SXSW Official four-day party will be held at one of 6th Street’s biggest music venues, The Stage on Sixth (508 E.6th Street), from noon to 6pm.

column2: MTV & mtvU present mtvU Woodies Festival - FREE
column12: Haim,TRAVI$ SCOTT,Trinidad Jame$,Jake Bugg,alt-j,Timeflies,Pusha T,Atlas Genius,Joey Bada$$
column13: HAIM and Timeflies are the latest performers added to the “2013 mtvU Woodie Awards Festival.” Previously announced Festival performers include Alt-J, Jake Bugg, and MTV Jams Stage artists includingTrinidad Jame$, Joey Bada$$, and Travi$ Scott. HAIM is from the San Fernando Valley and consists of three sisters (Este, Danielle, and Alana) who grew up playing classic rock songs with their parents in a family band, called Rockinhaim. Over the past few years, the band has toured with Florence and the Machine, Mumford and Sons Ke$ha, Julian Casablancas and Edward Sharpe and the Magnetic Zeros among many others. Last summer, HAIM released a three song EP titled “Forever,” which is also the title track on the record. HAIM’s debut album is set for release in summer of 2013. Timeflies duo Rob “Rez” Resnick and Cal Shapiro started the band in 2010 and in September 2011 they released their first debut album, “The Scotch Tape.” They’re known for their remixes, performing live covers, freestyling and original beats. Their second album will be released in Spring/Summer 2013.

Pitchfork is heading to Austin for SX. We'll host four events at spaces around town on Tuesday, March 12, Wednesday, March 13, and Thursday, March 14. The shows will feature artists such as Toro Y Moi, Rhye, Rustie, Disclosure, Youth Lagoon, Andy Stott, Mac DeMarco, Autre Ne Veut, Savages, Merchandise, Waxahatchee, Parquet Courts, Unknown Mortal Orchestra, Hundred Waters, Icona Pop, Foxygen, FIDLAR, California X, Ryan Hemsworth, Sky Ferreira, Pissed Jeans, Doldrums, Cloud Nothings, Marnie Stern, and more.


Pitchfork will present an official showcase at Mohawk during SX Interactive on Tuesday night, an unofficial day party at 1100 Warehouse on Thursday, and an official showcase at 1100 Warehouse on Thursday night. All shows are all ages.


All of this is in addition to the Show No Mercy party at House of Vans on Wednesday, featuring Skeletonwitch, Pallbearer, Trash Talk, and more.


via pitchfork

FRIDAY NIGHT at Stubb's Amphitheater, Time Out NY returns to SXSW with another stellar lineup. Iconic ska revival/punk band The Specialswill without a doubt bring the party atmosphere, teaming up with American indie rock heavy hitters The Cold War Kids to anchor the night.


A huge highlight of the evening will be folk rocking powerhouse Lissie, who blew audiences away with her version of Kid Cudi's Pursuit of Happinessduring her performances at SXSW 2012. She comes this year to support the release of her highly anticipated, second full-length album, dropping this summer. As always, come early and check out sets from amazing up-and-comers like Southern California's The Mowgli's and YouTube sensationsWalk Off the Earth.


Stay tuned to the schedule for more information and set times, still to come.


via SXSW Music

This year, we at Beautiful Buzzz are teaming up with Beagle Freedom Project to present our 3rd SXSW unofficial showcase, FREE NOW! FREE NOW! will take place March 13 -16, four days and nights during the SXSW Music Conference, from 12pm to 2am at The Brew Exchange in downtown Austin, Texas. Over 100 bands will be selected to present and create awareness for the Beagle Freedom Project. This gives attendees, performers and sponsors the opportunity to give back to the global community.









BEAUTIFUL BUZZZ (WWW.BEAUTIFULBUZZZ.COM)
Beautiful Buzzz is a new music blog based out of San Francisco, CA. Our goal is to expose up-and-coming artists who we believe are on the cutting edge of indie rock, electronic and dance music. We believe the world needs to know about the little guys – and we love to support independent musicians from around the globe!
The name comes from a Rolling Stones song called “Loving Cup” which happens to be Editor/Founder Erin Maher’s favorite song from the British rockers. It’s not a reference to anything else but that – but we like to think we have our finger on the pulse of what is buzzing within the indie music scene. The site caters to those interested in music news and goings on within the Los Angeles, San Francisco, United Kingdom, and Australian music scene, although does not exclude any other regions.
The site includes: a new music section, gig guide, record and show reviews, links to videos and other interesting music related items around the web, and a mix tape section complied monthly and showcasing some of the best music available at the time of its creation.

column14:
SX2013 details to come...

Running March 13 - 17, 2013, FILTER will be taking over Rainey Street with a four-day “block party” taking over some of the best venues in town including Lustre Pearl, Bar 96, Clive Bar and special pop-up locations including Container Bar! There will be bands that you don't want to miss (and shindigs that you won't be able to stop bragging to your friends about), so start booking your planes, trains and automobiles for Texas because next month is going to be nuts!

This year FILTER on Rainey will be powered by Tumblr, so expect an abnormal (but not unwelcomed) surge in cat gifs and and awesome photo sets!

Stay tuned to FILTERMagazine.com and our Tumblr for more info about Rainey Street, Cedar Street + more!

Ultra Music is not only a Grammy award-winning company, but has also won Best American Dance Label from 2005 through 2011. Since opening their door in 1996, Ultra Music has continued to share their passion for electronic music throughout the world. Their YouTube channel is the #1 electronic music channel, proving they are leading the pack of independent dance labels. Tiësto, Armin van Buuren, David Guetta, Above & Beyond, Paul Oakenfold, and Benny Benassi are just a few of the legendary greats who call Ultra home.

Disco Donnie presents is glad to lend a hand to the Ultra Records Official Showcase, going down at Republic Live on Thursday, March 14th. Like with all SXSW official showcases, those with badges and wristbands will have priority entry.


via disco donnie

column14:
COME ONE, COME ALL!!! It's that time of year again for everyone's favorite hangover day; the 4th annual UNCLE DOUG'S CHILI DOG FEST!!!

4 STAGES: The Side Bar, Empire Automotive, Lipstick 24 & Club 606

As always, there's NO COVER for this event. And this year we've BEEFED it up and made it a dang ol' BLOCK PARTY with 40+ BANDS on 4 STAGES, FREE CHILI and VEGGIE DOGS (come early, cuz they go quick!), CARNIVAL MIDWAY GAMES (1-6pm), and our 1st ever SILENT AUCTION!!!

The Silent Auction will be open from 1-6pm and will have plenty of bitchin' swag, tickets, goods, and services from local and national vendors donated for your bidding pleasure. All proceeds go to benefit ANIMAL TRUSTEES OF AUSTIN, HEALTH ALLIANCE for AUSTIN MUSICIANS, GIRLS ROCK CAMP, SIMS FOUNDATION, SCHOOL OF ROCK and AUSTIN PETS ALIVE! Check in here for updates on our growing list of donors and please contact Danielle Norris via Facebook if you'd like to donate!

Some of our amazing prizes include:

Tickets Tickets TICKETS from TRANSMISSION ENTERTAINMENT
A HEARTLESS BASTARDS merch package
A RUBBERNECK photoshoot
Cut 'n' style from MOXIE SALON LOUNGE
Art from BILL JEFFRIES
A singing telegram from WES COLEMAN
A tune-up lesson and t-shirt from WINDMILL BICYCLES

Vintage fashions from ELEPHAS MAXIMUS VINTAGE and SLINKY WHISTLE BAIT

And gift certificates to:

UCHI
END OF AN EAR
LIBERTY
YELLOW JACKET SOCIAL CLUB
I ♥ VIDEO
The GRACKLE

WAIT! There's music, right? Pfft, DUH! Helping you to cut the mustard and not the cheese are:



You say a Silent Auction or Carny Games ain't your bag but you still wanna give support? NO SWEAT! We'll be accepting cash AND credit/debit card donations throughout the evening. And as a convenience to you, we'll have a Square reader on hand cuz "cash only" just won't cut it anymore and the greatest nation is DONATION!

So come and share a great day of rad music, "tubed" "meats", cold beer, and great causes. It's gonna be a BALL, Y'ALL and that's the DILL, Pickle.

It isn’t yet known if the reunion will result in new music, but Give Upremains Sub Pop’s second-highest selling album, behind only Nirvana’s Bleach. column2: Guitartown/Conqueroo in conjunction with M Music and Musicians and AllMusic Present Kickoff 2013
column12: Billy Joe Shaver,Chuck Mead & His Grassy Knoll Boys,Jon Dee Graham,American Aquarium,The Waterboys,Howlin' Brothers,James McMurtry,SHURMAN,Chelle Rose,Dustin Welch,Tim Easton,Anne McCue,Henry Wagons,White Buffalo,Steve Poltz,Tom Freund,Willie Nile,Chris Stamey,Shoes,The Trishas,Nakia,Dash Rip Rock,Michael Des Barres,The Silos,Taylor Greenwood,Charlie Terrell & the Murdered Johns
column13: The 13th annual Guitartown/Conqueroo Kickoff event in conjunction with M Music & Musicians Magazine and AllMusic expands the scope from one venue to two adjacent West 6th Street venues — the Dogwood and Molotov. The expansion brings three stages and a record 29 artists on the bill. Guitartown/Conqueroo happens Wed., March 13, 11 a.m. - 9 p.m. And while the show has always showcased an eclectic mix of high-profile and emerging artists, we may have outdone ourselves this year: Mike Scott and Steve Wickham of the Waterboys open their US. tour here. Legendary Zion, Ill. powerpop band Shoes makes their first foray out of the Midwest in 18 years. Chris Stamey of The dB’s gives a glimpse of his new Yep Roc CD. Billy Joe Shaver performs classics and new songs from his fall 2013 studio album. And that’s just the start: Chuck Mead, Henry Wagons, Chelle Rose, Willie Nile, Nakia, James McMurtry, Michael Des Barres, The Trishas, Dustin Welch, Howlin’ Brothers, Dash Riprock, Steve Poltz, Shurman, the Silos, Tom Freund. Best of all, the event is free and open to the public — no badges. Three full bars to satisfy your thirst and a food menu. Tastemakers, journalists, a&r reps, managers, agents and just plain fans have come to make this they obligatory Wednesday stop during SXSW week. Many come for a particular artist and end up staying well into the night. We hope we’ll see you. Watch for updates at http://on.fb.me/11lDsw5>.

Legendary Zion, Ill. powerpop band Shoes makes their first foray out of the Midwest in 18 years. Chris Stamey of The dB’s gives a glimpse of his new Yep Roc CD. Billy Joe Shaver performs classics and new songs from his fall 2013 studio album. And that’s just the start: Chuck Mead, Henry Wagons, Chelle Rose, Willie Nile, Nakia, James McMurtry, Michael Des Barres, The Trishas, Dustin Welch, Howlin’ Brothers, Dash Riprock, Steve Poltz, Shurman, the Silos, Tom Freund. Best of all, the event is free and open to the public — no badges. Three full bars to satisfy your thirst and a food menu. Tastemakers, journalists, a&r reps, managers, agents and just plain fans have come to make this they obligatory Wednesday stop during SXSW week. Many come for a particular artist and end up staying well into the night. We hope we’ll see you. Watch for updates at <http://on.fb.me/11lDsw5>.

column14:
We are excited to announce that local food maven, Paul Qui is partnering with SXSW to curate a selection of gourmet food trucks for SXSW attendees this year. Paul is the executive Chef at Qui, opening in Spring 2013, the owner of Austin’s renowned East Side King trailers, winner of Top Chef Season 9, and is the recipient of the James Beard Award for Best Chef: Southwest 2012.


SouthBites is operating for all nine days of SXSW (March 8-16), open to the public and located right across the road from the Austin Convention Center. It will be an essential destination for thousands of hungry Music, Film and Interactive fans and industry players.


With Qui’s involvement, SXSW aims to provide a unique, high caliber selection of eateries– bringing together Austin’s well-known food truck culture and diverse range of cuisines.

This year, we at Beautiful Buzzz are teaming up with Beagle Freedom Project to present our 3rd SXSW unofficial showcase, FREE NOW! FREE NOW! will take place March 13 -16, four days and nights during the SXSW Music Conference, from 12pm to 2am at The Brew Exchange in downtown Austin, Texas. Over 100 bands will be selected to present and create awareness for the Beagle Freedom Project. This gives attendees, performers and sponsors the opportunity to give back to the global community.



BEAUTIFUL BUZZZ (WWW.BEAUTIFULBUZZZ.COM)

Beautiful Buzzz is a new music blog based out of San Francisco, CA. Our goal is to expose up-and-coming artists who we believe are on the cutting edge of indie rock, electronic and dance music. We believe the world needs to know about the little guys – and we love to support independent musicians from around the globe!

The name comes from a Rolling Stones song called “Loving Cup” which happens to be Editor/Founder Erin Maher’s favorite song from the British rockers. It’s not a reference to anything else but that – but we like to think we have our finger on the pulse of what is buzzing within the indie music scene. The site caters to those interested in music news and goings on within the Los Angeles, San Francisco, United Kingdom, and Australian music scene, although does not exclude any other regions.

The site includes: a new music section, gig guide, record and show reviews, links to videos and other interesting music related items around the web, and a mix tape section complied monthly and showcasing some of the best music available at the time of its creation.

column14:
RSVP
Come Make Your Mark and party with Los Lonely Boys, Camper Van Beethoven, and the Copyright Alliance—a Washington, D.C.-based non-profit that connects creators and protects creative work. Enjoy complimentary drinks and food from El Sol y La Luna, films by young filmmakers, and a set by Austin-area musician and CEO of Patronism, John Pointer who has launched a tool to allow fans to invest in musicians’ careers.

This inaugural SXSW Creative Upstarts event will connect fans with musicians, filmmakers, photographers, designers, and other creatives, as well as creatives with resources to support their work.

The event will also launch a collaboration between the Copyright Alliance and NewFilmmakers, (a group which was begun in 1998 by NYU Film Students www.newfilmmakers.com). The TBA project will be dedicated to discovering, supporting, and showcasing the next generation of great filmmakers.

PERFORMANCE TIMES: John Pointer (5:30), Los Lonely Boys (6:00), Camper Van Beethoven (7:00)

COME MAKE YOUR MARK!
Partners: A2IM, Adastra Creative, NewFilmmakers, Patronism, Professional

The Purple One is getting a specially remodeled stage at La Zona Rosa in downtown Austin, a source confirmed to HitFix. |The festival this year is already boasting music's biggest names like Yeah Yeah Yeahs, the Flaming Lips and Dave Grohl's Sound City Players, but Prince's concert will be bursting from its own seams with a 22-piece band. Prince hits the stage late Saturday night.|Furthermore, fest-goers should keep their eyes peeled for a certain awards show held during music festivities in Austin this week: His Royal Badness is slated as a "special guest" at the podium. |No word yet on how badge -holders or fans get access to the concert, stay tuned.|Read more at http://www.hitfix.com/immaculate-noise/exclusive-prince-will-perform-at-sxsw#eDQvpshZEslccwv0.99
column14:
Via HITFIX

The Rumors are true: Prince is set to take the stage at the South By Southwest music conference for the first time. The Purple One is getting a specially remodeled stage at La Zona Rosa in downtown Austin, a source confirmed to HitFix.

The festival this year is already boasting music's biggest names like Yeah Yeah Yeahs, the Flaming Lips and Dave Grohl's Sound City Players, but Prince's concert will be bursting from its own seams with a 22-piece band. Prince hits the stage late Saturday night.

Furthermore, fest-goers should keep their eyes peeled for a certain awards show held during music festivities in Austin this week: His Royal Badness is slated as a "special guest" at the podium.

No word yet on how badge -holders or fans get access to the concert, stay tuned.
Read more at http://www.hitfix.com/immaculate-noise/exclusive-prince-will-perform-at-sxsw#eDQvpshZEslccwv0.99

column14:
Join us for the Twangfest and KDHX SX Day Parties at the Broken Spoke in Austin. Dates are Thursday, March 14 and Saturday, March 16, noon-5 p.m. each day.

Now in their 14th year, the Twangfest day parties are among the most anticipated afternoon events during the week-long South By Southwest gathering. These parties are open to the public, with RSVP required.

The lineup for the 2013 parties features 18 national artists from a wide-range of twangy genres.


Confirmed schedule for the Twangfest Day Parties at SXSW 2013


Thursday, March 14 – Main Stage


Noon – Chuck Mead & His Grassy Knoll Boys
1 p.m. – The Lone Bellow
2 p.m. – Kelly Hogan
3 p.m. – Bruce Robison and Kelly Willis
4 p.m. – Dale Watson


Thursday, March 14 – Lobby Stage


12:30 p.m. – Pretty Little Empire
1:30 p.m. – The Carper Family
2:30 p.m. – Whitehorse
3:30 p.m. – Ron Sexsmith


Saturday, March 16 – Main Stage


Noon – Deano and the Purvs

RSVP on the Facebook Event page. You may also RSVP by email: sxsw at twangfest dot com. Each RSVP may bring up to three guests.

See you in Austin!

Mass Appeal is proud to announce that we've joined forces with Pharrell's Ice Cream to present an official SXSW showcase like no other.

On Friday, March 15th we'll be at the Austin Music Hall with performers Kendrick Lamar, Bun B, Pusha T, Danny Brown, Alexander Spit, A$AP Ferg, Joey Bada$$, Roc Marciano, Harry Fraud, Emilio Rojas, BIA, Nylo, and other surprise guests.

The cherry on top of this Ice Cream sundae is that we'll also be celebrating Mass Appeal magazine's return to print as a quarterly publication with issue 52. Check back with us as we will be announcing more surprises and the new print issue in the coming days. Trust us, our SXSW event is going to be #MASSIVE.

Mass Appeal would like to thank our event sponsors: Ice Cream, Decon Records, Flat Fitty, Monster Energy and Trojan.

21+

column2: SHB, Slumerican and Monster present Slum by Slumwest: Trunk Muzik Returns Release Party ft. Yelawolf
column12: YelaWolf
column13: YELAWOLF: TRUNK MUZIK RETURNS RELEASE PARTY @ CLUB DE VILLE|Envision a humid world of slow-rolling Monte Carlos and slaughter houses; meth labs and rusting Mossberg’s, inked up arms and haircuts that look like they’ve been chopped by hatchets. Trunk Muzik. Southern Pine trees, smoking pine, and pine boxes. Call him Catfish Billy or Yelawolf, just don’t go make him go pop the trunk on you.|Enter Yelawolf’s Alabama—a backwoods badlands of sinners and salvation. He claims Gadsden, but he’s from everywhere. Born Michael Wayne Atha to an absentee father and a bartender mother, he attended over 15 schools while soaking up slang and spiritualism in Baton Rouge, Antioch, Tennessee, and Atlanta. While trying to stay afloat in a turbulent home life addled by drug and alcohol abuse, he discovered rap music in Tennessee and it soon became an obsession, along with the classic rock (Lynard Skynard, Pink Floyd, The Allman Brothers) that he was raised on. |via Monster Bands
column14:
YELAWOLF: TRUNK MUZIK RETURNS RELEASE PARTY @ CLUB DE VILLE

Envision a humid world of slow-rolling Monte Carlos and slaughter houses; meth labs and rusting Mossberg’s, inked up arms and haircuts that look like they’ve been chopped by hatchets. Trunk Muzik. Southern Pine trees, smoking pine, and pine boxes. Call him Catfish Billy or Yelawolf, just don’t go make him go pop the trunk on you.

Enter Yelawolf’s Alabama—a backwoods badlands of sinners and salvation. He claims Gadsden, but he’s from everywhere. Born Michael Wayne Atha to an absentee father and a bartender mother, he attended over 15 schools while soaking up slang and spiritualism in Baton Rouge, Antioch, Tennessee, and Atlanta. While trying to stay afloat in a turbulent home life addled by drug and alcohol abuse, he discovered rap music in Tennessee and it soon became an obsession, along with the classic rock (Lynard Skynard, Pink Floyd, The Allman Brothers) that he was raised on.

via Monster Bands

Their music is an ongoing experiment in sound and arrangement, and their palette wide. Drawing from just about every musical movement and style of the last 200 years, the Projectors have created an eclectic sound unlike any other, mostly under the direction of frontman David Longstreth. Today they hit the decks for Beats & Bytes, powered by Windows 8 and General Assembly.- Dennis Lynch, Flavorpill
column14:

Today they hit the decks for Beats & Bytes, powered by Windows 8 and General Assembly.

- Dennis Lynch, Flavorpill

The Firehouse Lounge features classically prepared cocktails, delectable accompaniments, an inviting atmosphere, and a variety of live music. Elevate your experience at Downtown's NEWEST venue.

The giftbags will be given out at the VIP Dinner Party and the Main Event. Mini Moo Business Cards will contain download codes for guests to return home and enter for more goodies!

column14:
Pop Montreal Official Showcase

The Swan Dive, 615 Red River @ 7 PM

The evening will kick off with Montreal's BRAIDS' long-awaited return to the stage! Following up on the international success of their 2010 debut, the band has now reinvented themselves and will give lucky audience members a sneak peak at their sophomore album, due out this summer. NME's 2011 Best New Artist Suuns will close the official showcase with songs from their eagerly awaited upcoming album, Images Du Futur, out March 5th. Lending a hand at filling the evening with music will be none other than Ottawa's electric pow wow kings, A Tribe Called Red, as well as some of Montreal's most talked about artists: Karneef + The Life, Each Other, AroarA and Solar Year...
via Pop Montreal

column12: Macklemore & Ryan Lewis,Twenty One Pilots,Zedd
column13: The 2013 mtvU Woodie Awards will take-over the Festival beginning just past 7:00 p.m. Music fans without SXSW badges will need a “Woodies” ticket for entry. |Tickets are free and available in the Austin Convention Center on Wednesday, March 13 from 12:00 p.m. to 5:00 p.m. at the top of the Rotunda stairs. |One of MTV’s 2013 Artists to Watch, twenty one pilots will join previously announced performers Macklemore & Ryan Lewis on the “2013 mtvU Woodie Awards” line-up. Members Tyler Joseph and Josh Dun have earned widespread acclaim for their energetic live sets and distinctive fusion of piano-driven schizoid pop and lyrical uplift. twenty one pilots built a fervent national following through their electrifying live performances at headline shows and tours. The band made its Fueled By Ramen debut with their highly anticipated full-length album titled “Vessel” available now.
column14:
The 2013 mtvU Woodie Awards will take-over the Festival beginning just past 7:00 p.m. Music fans without SXSW badges will need a “Woodies” ticket for entry.

Tickets are free and available in the Austin Convention Center on Wednesday, March 13 from 12:00 p.m. to 5:00 p.m. at the top of the Rotunda stairs.

One of MTV’s 2013 Artists to Watch, twenty one pilots will join previously announced performers Macklemore & Ryan Lewis on the “2013 mtvU Woodie Awards” line-up. Members Tyler Joseph and Josh Dun have earned widespread acclaim for their energetic live sets and distinctive fusion of piano-driven schizoid pop and lyrical uplift. twenty one pilots built a fervent national following through their electrifying live performances at headline shows and tours. The band made its Fueled By Ramen debut with their highly anticipated full-length album titled “Vessel” available now.

column14:
Join us for the Twangfest and KDHX SX Day Parties at the Broken Spoke in Austin. Dates are Thursday, March 14 and Saturday, March 16, noon-5 p.m. each day.

Now in their 14th year, the Twangfest day parties are among the most anticipated afternoon events during the week-long South By Southwest gathering. These parties are open to the public, with RSVP required.

The lineup for the 2013 parties features 18 national artists from a wide-range of twangy genres.


Confirmed schedule for the Twangfest Day Parties at SXSW 2013


Thursday, March 14 – Main Stage


Noon – Chuck Mead & His Grassy Knoll Boys
1 p.m. – The Lone Bellow
2 p.m. – Kelly Hogan
3 p.m. – Bruce Robison and Kelly Willis
4 p.m. – Dale Watson


Thursday, March 14 – Lobby Stage


12:30 p.m. – Pretty Little Empire
1:30 p.m. – The Carper Family
2:30 p.m. – Whitehorse
3:30 p.m. – Ron Sexsmith


Saturday, March 16 – Main Stage


Noon – Deano and the Purvs
1 p.m. – Waco Brothers
2 p.m. – JC Brooks & The Uptown Sound
3 p.m. – Laura Cantrell
4 p.m. – Pokey LaFarge


Saturday, March 16 – Lobby Stage


12:30 p.m. – David Wax Museum
1:30 p.m. – Mount Moriah
2:30 p.m. – Murder By Death (acoustic)
3:30 p.m. – Caitlin Rose
4:30 p.m. – Cree Rider Family Band


RSVP on the Facebook Event page. You may also RSVP by email: sxsw at twangfest dot com. Each RSVP may bring up to three guests.

See you in Austin!

column14:
RSVP

As a part of our mission to help local businesses connect and compete, we’re inviting a handful of Austin merchants to join us at our launch event. Using our mobile app, you’ll be able to buy merchandise from local shops in Austin right on site!

We’re hosting the event at The 512 Bar on 6th with several live bands and a DJ and plenty of free drinks! The guest list will be packed with movers and shakers from all over the technology and retail world and we’re hoping you can help us show them how important our technology is to local businesses.


Space is limited so please RSVP ASAP. Tickets are for SXSW pass holders only.

UPDATE: Here's the LINE-UP of local bands at the party!

8: Hello Wheels
9: The Preservation
10: HEADLINE ACT What Made Milwaukee Famous
11:00: DJ Mel



Who we are
Photiq is a new mobile app for the iPhone that creates an instant e-commerce site for your store. You can now compete with online retailers with no expertise needed!
Your customers can share their favorites from your store on their social networks like Facebook, Twitter and Pinterest, buy through Photiq on their iPhone and pick up their purchase instantly at the store. Visit us at www.photiqapp.com and sign up for our Beta!

column2: Comedy Stage at the IFC Crossroads House
column13: Long time SXSW Super Sponsor IFC is back and they are bringing their "Always On - Slightly Off" sense of humor with them as presenters of the newest official Comedy Stage of SXSW 2013. The network that has brought you countless side-splitting shows like Portlandia, The Whitest Kids U'Know and Comedy Bang! Bang! will be delivering four days of comedy from the IFC Crossroads House, located at Vice bar on 6th Street.|Last year some of the biggest names in comedy made their way through the Crossroads House including Reggie Watts, Jay Chandrasekhar, Mike Birbiglia and many more. It's a safe bet that IFC will have equally impressive talent on stage this year doing what they do best. It looks like the future of the Trapped in the Closet series might not be the number one thing you're looking forward to this year from our friends over at IFC anymore.|Keep an eye on ifc.com/sxsw for announcements on what you can expect March 9 through March 12 at the IFC Crossroads House. |Comedy lineups coming soon!
column14:
Long time SXSW Super Sponsor IFC is back and they are bringing their "Always On - Slightly Off" sense of humor with them as presenters of the newest official Comedy Stage of SXSW 2013. The network that has brought you countless side-splitting shows like Portlandia, The Whitest Kids U'Know and Comedy Bang! Bang! will be delivering four days of comedy from the IFC Crossroads House, located at Vice bar on 6th Street.


Last year some of the biggest names in comedy made their way through the Crossroads House including Reggie Watts, Jay Chandrasekhar, Mike Birbiglia and many more. It's a safe bet that IFC will have equally impressive talent on stage this year doing what they do best. It looks like the future of the Trapped in the Closet series might not be the number one thing you're looking forward to this year from our friends over at IFC anymore.


Keep an eye on ifc.com/sxsw for announcements on what you can expect March 9 through March 12 at the IFC Crossroads House.


Comedy lineups coming soon!

column14:
Do512 is giving away an amazing new Bohemian Guitar!

These awesome sounding, Boho Series electric oil can guitars produce a clean bluesy twang. These axes feature top quality maple necks with rosewood fingerboards, a noise-less single coil pickup, and volume and control knobs. Your Bohemian Guitar will make you the focus of your next jam session. Just plug the ax into any amp and get to shreddin'.

Specs:

  • Works with any amp
  • Maplewood neck with a rosewood fingerboard
  • Strap buttons
  • 24 frets
  • Single coil pickup
  • Volume & tone control
  • Chrome tuning machines
  • Adjustable truss rod
  • Adjustable bridge
  • Choose from 3 BOHO styles: Honey, Motor Oil, or Moonshine

About Bohemian Guitars:

Funded on Kickstarter, their guitars only available for pre-order but the winner will get one when the early bird Kickstarter backers receive theirs in May.
*A portion of every guitar we sell goes to purchasing instruments for youth organizations and schools.

Make sure you stop by their booth at the SXSW Trade Show and try one out for yourself!

Bohemian Guitars.... "Real. Far. Out."

column2: Soul Temple Showcase ft. Ghostface Killah (Badges / Wristbands)
column12: Ghostface Killah,RZA
column13: As the Wu Tang Clan celebrates the 20th anniversary of their debut album Welcome To The 36 Chambers this year, the crew from Staten Island shows us that they are still going strong with RZA's Soul Temple label showcase on Thursday, March 14 at Scoot Inn.|The show will feature new projects by Ghostface Killah (backed by Adrienne Younge's band), performing 12 Reasons to Die, U-God performing new tracks from Keynote Speaker and RZA dropping gems from his compilation of classics called Shaolin Soul. |The word on the street is that there's a new Wu Tang album due out later this year and the crew has already begun recording the first single, set to be released in the not too distant future...you best protect your neck SXSW fans!|via SX Music
column14:
As the Wu Tang Clan celebrates the 20th anniversary of their debut album Welcome To The 36 Chambers this year, the crew from Staten Island shows us that they are still going strong with RZA's Soul Temple label showcase on Thursday, March 14 at Scoot Inn.

The show will feature new projects by Ghostface Killah (backed by Adrienne Younge's band), performing 12 Reasons to Die, U-God performing new tracks from Keynote Speaker and RZA dropping gems from his compilation of classics called Shaolin Soul.

The word on the street is that there's a new Wu Tang album due out later this year and the crew has already begun recording the first single, set to be released in the not too distant future...you best protect your neck SXSW fans!

via SX Music

column2: Berklee College of Music
column12: Rebecca Loebe,Chloë Sunshine,MELISSA FERRICK,Air Traffic Controller,The Lights Out,THE FIELD EFFECT
column13: Berklee College of Music, the only college to host an official party at the SXSW Music and Media Conference—one of the music industry’s biggest events—presents its annual SXSW Party on Friday, March 15, from 12:00 p.m. to 6:00 p.m. at Brush Square Park (East Tent), located at 409 East 5th St. (Neches and 5th), Austin, Texas. Berklee’s eighth SXSW party is the college’s first at an outdoor all-ages venue. Also for the first time, the lineup is curated by the Red Room at Cafe 939, Berklee’s all-ages nightclub that hosts national and local acts year-round.|The party features up-and-coming Berklee, Berkleemusic.com, and Heavy Rotation Records (HRR) alumni and students performing rock, pop, electronic, Americana, and folk, including acclaimed singer-songwriter Melissa Ferrick, David Stewart Jr., Air Traffic Controller, Chloë Sunshine, Red Oblivion (HRR), Bear Language(HRR), Rebecca Loebe, the Lights Out, Holiday Mountain, and the Field Effect. In addition to performing with her band, Ferrick is co-hosting the event with alumna Sarah Sharp.|Check out Berklee’s SXSW Party Sampler with streaming and free downloads at BerkleeCollegeofMusic.bandcamp.com.|Berklee's SXSW Day Party is all-ages and open to SXSW badge holders. The public can email sxswrsvp@berklee.edu to attend free of charge. Free copies of student-run HRR's Dorm Sessions 8, featuring Red Oblivion and Bear Language, will be given away. Listen at HeavyRotationRecords.bandcamp.com. Free oyster bar provided by Island Creek Oysters.|Artists, in order of appearance:|Melissa Ferrick’s 11th original album, the truth is (MPress Records, out May 7), is by far the most revealing, beautiful, and complete of her 16 albums. She signed to Atlantic in 1992 after opening for Morrissey, and launched Right On Records in 2000. Ferrick, a classically trained violinist and trumpeter, attended Berklee and is an assistant professor of songwriting at the college. Regarded as one of the most prolific, hardworking, honest writers and performers in the singer-songwriter world, she has toured with artists including Paul Westerberg, Dwight Yoakam, John Haitt, Weezer, Tegan and Sara, Ani DiFranco, and k.d. lang. Ferrick has won numerous awards and was recently named one of the most influential queer artists/activists byOUT magazine.|Guitarist David Stewart Jr. came to the U.S. from Lima, Peru and was raised in Pompano Beach, Florida. By 18, Stewart had already written over 80 original compositions in genres spanning rock, pop, jazz, R&B, soul, funk, reggae, and instrumental film scores. He recently released Red Lipstick, a self-produced EP on which he played all of the instruments. Stewart is the first recipient of the Berklee Lollapalooza Endowed Scholarship—a full-tuition award. He plans to major in performance and contemporary writing and production.|Air Traffic Controller was formed after singer-songwriter and guitarist Dave Munro served in the U.S. Navy as an air traffic controller. With a refreshing sound resembling the Decemberists, ATC infuses its compositions with pop sensibilities and well-crafted storytelling in the vein of Petty, McCartney, and Springsteen. The band also features multi-instrumentalist Steve Scott; drummer Richie Munro; and Berklee student Casey Sullivan on bass, banjo, and vocals. ATC’s second album, Nordo, has received acclaim from American Songwriter, Under the Radar, and The Boston Globe.|New York band Chloë Sunshine is the brainchild of Berklee alumna Kendall Chloë Eagan. After college, Eagan relocated to New York and joined forces with Jessica Louise Dye (of D.C.’s Lightfoot) and alumna guitarist Natasha Chitayat. Their debut,Indian Summer, was released in 2011 and gained attention with comparisons to Cults, Tegan and Sara, Dum Dum Girls, and Tennis, (danceyrselfclean.com). Themes of heartbreak and love lost are clothed in happy melodies and mixed with pop sensibilities to unite classic surf rock aesthetics with summer fun.|Red Oblivion (HRR) is comprised of Sarah Chaffee (cello) and Berklee alumni Emma Torres (guitar), Zach Adams (lead vocals/bass), and Carson Groenewold (drums). The Boston-based band made a splash at Lollapalooza Chicago in 2012, and will perform at Lollapalooza Chile in April. With backgrounds in classical, metal, pop, electronic, and world music, it blends a rock band lineup with amplified cello. Red Oblivion recorded with producer Paul Kolderie (Radiohead, Portugal. The Man, Pixies) for HRR’s Dorm Sessions 8 CD. |Bear Language—guitarist/vocalist Luca Buccellati, bassist Archi Denis, and drummer Ian Barnett—combine Beatles-influenced rock like the Strokes and Tame Impala with the funky grooves of Two Door Cinema Club. The new single “Mary Go Round” is a preview to its upcoming debut album, mastered by Joe Lambert (Animal Collective, Dirty Projectors). The band continues to charm with energetic live performances, and was named in the Deli Magazine's Top 10 New England Artists of 2012. Bear Language also appears on HRR’s Dorm Sessions 8 CD. |Award winning singer-songwriter Rebecca Loebe is both candid and self-deprecating, attributes that shine through in her songwriting and laugh-out-loud storytelling. In 2011, Loebe took a break from her 200-show-per-year schedule to appear on Season 1 of NBC’s The Voice. Her performance of Nirvana’s “Come As You Are” inspired Christina Aguilera and Adam Levine to offer her mentorship and charted on iTunes worldwide. Loebe, a Berklee alumna from Atlanta who now lives in Austin, is touring nationally in support of her third album, Circus Heart.|The future looks bright for Boston rock quartet The Lights Out—composed of Berklee grad Rishava Green, Matt King, Jesse James, and Adam Ritchie. Since 2005, the band has showcased at music conferences from CMJ Music Marathon to MidPoint, released three albums and three EPs, placed songs on MTV, appeared inBillboard and sweated out enough High Life to fill the Carrier Dome. “It’s astounding haven’t been signed yet,” said Music Connection. “Their technical prowess coupled with memorable lyrics…makes them ideal Spin cover boys.” |Boston-based electro-dub-pop dance workout Holiday Mountain released its debut, Become Who You Are, in 2012. Songwriter Laura Patiño formed the group with drummer Zander Kagle and alumnus bassist/synth player Bradley Will while attending Berklee. The band is named for Billie Holiday and the Rocky Mountains where Patiño grew up. Holiday Mountain shines in performance, creating an atmosphere for freakiness, an experience they dubbed “anti-shame.” Sweat, glitter, grooves, and color are a part of every show. They are in the process of moving to Austin, Texas.|The Field Effect packs a collective punch, spiked with introspective lyrics, infectious melodies, and ferocious rhythms. An antidote to aloof, lo-fi indie music, the Field Effect reclaims the genre with its passion, musical ability, and aims to make music for “the many” and not just “the few.” The Field Effect has received rave reviews for its energetic live show and debut release. “They’re young, they’re exciting, they’re incredibly talented…they’ve got the potential to lead a new wave of Boston rock,” said Richard Bouchard in The Boston Phoenix.|Heavy Rotation Records (HRR) gives music business/management majors at Berklee hands-on experience running a record company. The students oversee all label functions, including A&R, marketing, sales, touring, web development, media, and accounting. HRR's releases since 1995 include Shekinah: 13 Artists, distributed by Epic; Apollo Sunshine's second album, coreleased with spinART; Dorm Sessions 1–8; and Under the Influence. Many up-and-coming artists have appeared on HRR compilations, including Annie Clark (St. Vincent); members of Passion Pit (as the Peasantry); Christopher Barnes (Gem Club); Madi Diaz; Elizabeth and the Catapult; and Big D and the Kids Table. The label also serves as a springboard for careers in the industry. Alumni have gone on to work at Interscope, Capitol, DreamWorks, BMG, Universal, Live Nation, AEG Live, and RightsFlow, among other companies.|Berkleemusic.com is the continuing education division of Berklee College of Music, delivering online access to Berklee's acclaimed curriculum from anywhere in the world. Berkleemusic's award-winning online courses and certificate programs are accredited and taught by the college's world-renowned faculty, providing lifelong learning opportunities to people interested in music and working in the music industry. As the business of music continues to move online, Berkleemusic is taking a leadership role in educating the next generation of producers, performers, and entrepreneurs on this evolving industry landscape. Berkleemusic's students come from over 130 countries around the world, and include Grammy Award–winners, managers, artists, publishers, music business entrepreneurs, and major international touring acts.|http://berklee.edu/news/berklee-sxsw-party-march-15-austin
column14:
Berklee College of Music, the only college to host an official party at the SXSW Music and Media Conference—one of the music industry’s biggest events—presents its annual SXSW Party on Friday, March 15, from 12:00 p.m. to 6:00 p.m. at Brush Square Park (East Tent), located at 409 East 5th St. (Neches and 5th), Austin, Texas. Berklee’s eighth SXSW party is the college’s first at an outdoor all-ages venue. Also for the first time, the lineup is curated by the Red Room at Cafe 939, Berklee’s all-ages nightclub that hosts national and local acts year-round.


The party features up-and-coming Berklee, Berkleemusic.com, and Heavy Rotation Records (HRR) alumni and students performing rock, pop, electronic, Americana, and folk, including acclaimed singer-songwriter Melissa Ferrick, David Stewart Jr., Air Traffic Controller, Chloë Sunshine, Red Oblivion (HRR), Bear Language(HRR), Rebecca Loebe, the Lights Out, Holiday Mountain, and the Field Effect. In addition to performing with her band, Ferrick is co-hosting the event with alumna Sarah Sharp.


Check out Berklee’s SXSW Party Sampler with streaming and free downloads at BerkleeCollegeofMusic.bandcamp.com.


Berklee's SXSW Day Party is all-ages and open to SXSW badge holders. The public can email sxswrsvp@berklee.edu to attend free of charge. Free copies of student-run HRR's Dorm Sessions 8, featuring Red Oblivion and Bear Language, will be given away. Listen at HeavyRotationRecords.bandcamp.com. Free oyster bar provided by Island Creek Oysters.


Artists, in order of appearance:


Melissa Ferrick’s 11th original album, the truth is (MPress Records, out May 7), is by far the most revealing, beautiful, and complete of her 16 albums. She signed to Atlantic in 1992 after opening for Morrissey, and launched Right On Records in 2000. Ferrick, a classically trained violinist and trumpeter, attended Berklee and is an assistant professor of songwriting at the college. Regarded as one of the most prolific, hardworking, honest writers and performers in the singer-songwriter world, she has toured with artists including Paul Westerberg, Dwight Yoakam, John Haitt, Weezer, Tegan and Sara, Ani DiFranco, and k.d. lang. Ferrick has won numerous awards and was recently named one of the most influential queer artists/activists byOUT magazine.


Guitarist David Stewart Jr. came to the U.S. from Lima, Peru and was raised in Pompano Beach, Florida. By 18, Stewart had already written over 80 original compositions in genres spanning rock, pop, jazz, R&B, soul, funk, reggae, and instrumental film scores. He recently released Red Lipstick, a self-produced EP on which he played all of the instruments. Stewart is the first recipient of the Berklee Lollapalooza Endowed Scholarship—a full-tuition award. He plans to major in performance and contemporary writing and production.


Air Traffic Controller was formed after singer-songwriter and guitarist Dave Munro served in the U.S. Navy as an air traffic controller. With a refreshing sound resembling the Decemberists, ATC infuses its compositions with pop sensibilities and well-crafted storytelling in the vein of Petty, McCartney, and Springsteen. The band also features multi-instrumentalist Steve Scott; drummer Richie Munro; and Berklee student Casey Sullivan on bass, banjo, and vocals. ATC’s second album, Nordo, has received acclaim from American Songwriter, Under the Radar, and The Boston Globe.


New York band Chloë Sunshine is the brainchild of Berklee alumna Kendall Chloë Eagan. After college, Eagan relocated to New York and joined forces with Jessica Louise Dye (of D.C.’s Lightfoot) and alumna guitarist Natasha Chitayat. Their debut,Indian Summer, was released in 2011 and gained attention with comparisons to Cults, Tegan and Sara, Dum Dum Girls, and Tennis, (danceyrselfclean.com). Themes of heartbreak and love lost are clothed in happy melodies and mixed with pop sensibilities to unite classic surf rock aesthetics with summer fun.


Red Oblivion (HRR) is comprised of Sarah Chaffee (cello) and Berklee alumni Emma Torres (guitar), Zach Adams (lead vocals/bass), and Carson Groenewold (drums). The Boston-based band made a splash at Lollapalooza Chicago in 2012, and will perform at Lollapalooza Chile in April. With backgrounds in classical, metal, pop, electronic, and world music, it blends a rock band lineup with amplified cello. Red Oblivion recorded with producer Paul Kolderie (Radiohead, Portugal. The Man, Pixies) for HRR’s Dorm Sessions 8 CD.


Bear Language—guitarist/vocalist Luca Buccellati, bassist Archi Denis, and drummer Ian Barnett—combine Beatles-influenced rock like the Strokes and Tame Impala with the funky grooves of Two Door Cinema Club. The new single “Mary Go Round” is a preview to its upcoming debut album, mastered by Joe Lambert (Animal Collective, Dirty Projectors). The band continues to charm with energetic live performances, and was named in the Deli Magazine's Top 10 New England Artists of 2012. Bear Language also appears on HRR’s Dorm Sessions 8 CD.


Award winning singer-songwriter Rebecca Loebe is both candid and self-deprecating, attributes that shine through in her songwriting and laugh-out-loud storytelling. In 2011, Loebe took a break from her 200-show-per-year schedule to appear on Season 1 of NBC’s The Voice. Her performance of Nirvana’s “Come As You Are” inspired Christina Aguilera and Adam Levine to offer her mentorship and charted on iTunes worldwide. Loebe, a Berklee alumna from Atlanta who now lives in Austin, is touring nationally in support of her third album, Circus Heart.


The future looks bright for Boston rock quartet The Lights Out—composed of Berklee grad Rishava Green, Matt King, Jesse James, and Adam Ritchie. Since 2005, the band has showcased at music conferences from CMJ Music Marathon to MidPoint, released three albums and three EPs, placed songs on MTV, appeared inBillboard and sweated out enough High Life to fill the Carrier Dome. “It’s astounding haven’t been signed yet,” said Music Connection. “Their technical prowess coupled with memorable lyrics…makes them ideal Spin cover boys.”


Boston-based electro-dub-pop dance workout Holiday Mountain released its debut, Become Who You Are, in 2012. Songwriter Laura Patiño formed the group with drummer Zander Kagle and alumnus bassist/synth player Bradley Will while attending Berklee. The band is named for Billie Holiday and the Rocky Mountains where Patiño grew up. Holiday Mountain shines in performance, creating an atmosphere for freakiness, an experience they dubbed “anti-shame.” Sweat, glitter, grooves, and color are a part of every show. They are in the process of moving to Austin, Texas.


The Field Effect packs a collective punch, spiked with introspective lyrics, infectious melodies, and ferocious rhythms. An antidote to aloof, lo-fi indie music, the Field Effect reclaims the genre with its passion, musical ability, and aims to make music for “the many” and not just “the few.” The Field Effect has received rave reviews for its energetic live show and debut release. “They’re young, they’re exciting, they’re incredibly talented…they’ve got the potential to lead a new wave of Boston rock,” said Richard Bouchard in The Boston Phoenix.


Heavy Rotation Records (HRR) gives music business/management majors at Berklee hands-on experience running a record company. The students oversee all label functions, including A&R, marketing, sales, touring, web development, media, and accounting. HRR's releases since 1995 include Shekinah: 13 Artists, distributed by Epic; Apollo Sunshine's second album, coreleased with spinART; Dorm Sessions 1–8; and Under the Influence. Many up-and-coming artists have appeared on HRR compilations, including Annie Clark (St. Vincent); members of Passion Pit (as the Peasantry); Christopher Barnes (Gem Club); Madi Diaz; Elizabeth and the Catapult; and Big D and the Kids Table. The label also serves as a springboard for careers in the industry. Alumni have gone on to work at Interscope, Capitol, DreamWorks, BMG, Universal, Live Nation, AEG Live, and RightsFlow, among other companies.

Berkleemusic.com is the continuing education division of Berklee College of Music, delivering online access to Berklee's acclaimed curriculum from anywhere in the world. Berkleemusic's award-winning online courses and certificate programs are accredited and taught by the college's world-renowned faculty, providing lifelong learning opportunities to people interested in music and working in the music industry. As the business of music continues to move online, Berkleemusic is taking a leadership role in educating the next generation of producers, performers, and entrepreneurs on this evolving industry landscape. Berkleemusic's students come from over 130 countries around the world, and include Grammy Award–winners, managers, artists, publishers, music business entrepreneurs, and major international touring acts.

All Things Go and Indie Shuffle are teaming up for a mega-blog SX showcase of epic proportions. Join us on Saturday, March 16th at Club de Ville in Austin, TX for an eight-band line-up stacked with artists we love from start to finish, including The Neighbourhood, Youngblood Hawke, MØ, Ghost Beach, Darwin Deez, The 1975,HAERTS, and Trails and Ways.


Doors are at 11AM and music kicks off at 11:30AM. Make sure you get there early, though, because we're going to be giving out free sandwiches, chips and cookies from Schlotzsky's. There'll also be awesome beer courtesy of Lone Star. Free food. Rad beer. Incredible music. Get on this people.

column14:
A Mid West Festival + Unofficial Showcase Event during SX in Austin, TX March 12th - 17th, 2013.

This is an Unofficial SXSW Event and brought to you by BSHR Entertainment and Sponsored by Music Saves Lives


THE VENUE

The Firehouse Lounge features classically prepared cocktails, delectable accompaniments, an inviting atmosphere, and a variety of live music. Elevate your experience at Downtown's NEWEST venue.


FEATURING. . .

The giftbags will be given out at the VIP Dinner Party and the Main Event. Mini Moo Business Cards will contain download codes for guests to return home and enter for more goodies!


Plus play the Indie Band Drinking Game + Sky Scavenger Hunt all week to win Sponsored Prize Packages!

THE [SOS] SCHEDULE of SHOWS

Tuesday 3/12 Welcome to Austin: A Singer/Songwriter Party + Evening Events


Wednesday 3/13 Rockin’ Zombie Luau Day Party + Evening Events


Thursday 3/14 The Calm Before the Storm Day Party and the VIP Dinner + Cocktail Party+ evening events.

Mini spa treatments, an art gala with VIP Dinner + Cocktail party.

Friday 3/15 Blue Sky on Broadway + The Indie Dance Party: Bring on the Weekend

The start of the Vinyl Record Club in Partnership with Broadway Recording Company.


Saturday 3/16 BSHR’s “Giant” Launch Party

The main event complete with miniature EVERYTHING. Guests receive The “Grow it @ Home” Giftbag. Raffles of various prizes and giveaways.


Sunday 3/17 The Green Giant Party + Closing events

column14:
► 21+ from 2PM-2AM

► Ins & outs -- feel free to come and go
► FREE wristband for SXSW badge holders until 10PM!

LINE-UP:


Headlining: Kill Paris from Los Angeles, CA

  • NEXUS from Orlando, FL
  • ### (PoundPoundPound) from West Lafayette, IN
  • Team Bayside High from Chicago, IL
  • Valentino Khan from Los Angeles, CA
  • Sound Remedy from Los Angeles, CA
  • Worthy from Los Angeles, CA
  • Amine Edge & DANCE from Marseille,France
  • Knight Riderz from Edmonton, Canada
  • ill-esha from Denver, CO
  • LeDoom from San Antonio, TX
  • Joe Mousepad from San Francisco, CA
  • Sazon Booya from New York City, NY
  • gLAdiator from Los Angeles, CA

VIP entry begins at 1 P.M. with: SPECIAL GUEST: NEXUS

FOR OUR FULL LIST OF SPONSORS PLEASE VISIT MUSICYOUNEED.NET/BASSICKELEMENTS

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

NEXUS

Connect with Nexus
Facebook | SoundCloud

Pound Pound Pound(###)

This up and coming producer/dj duo, hailing from west Lafayette Indiana, are taking over the Midwest. In their first year of storming the EDM scene ### (pronounced Pound Pound Pound) has opened for Vibesquad, Krewella, Midnight Conspiracy, Cenob1te, Ghost House, and other awesome acts. ### has been spinning for a couple years but in 2012 they started focusing on original production. You can expect multiple individual releases and at least two e.p.'s this year. Not only are these guys putting out crazy originals and remixes like the one they did of Clique with FootwoRk, but their live show is one full of energy and bass all the way through. These guys are doing some big things this year so keep them on your radar! Are you down to pound?

Connect with ###
Facebook | Twitter | SoundCloud

Team Bayside High

Team Bayside High are a duo from hailing from Chicago currently putting out freaky bass music on Teenage Riot Records. Their combination of heavy sub bass, complex rhythms and melodies have been taking over dance floors by storm leaving audiences scrambling for more. Rising from a metal background, these multi-instrumentalists are bringing a fresh perspective to the world of dance music breaking tempo and genre barriers, fusing together an all encompassing audio assault. Team Bayside High is rapidly on the rise after completing several national tours, and standout festival appearances such as Lollapalooza and North Coast Music Festival. With multiple tracks breaching the top 5 in Hypem charts and receiving tons of support from some of the bigger artists in the bass game, stay tuned for Team Bayside Highs newest record being in Spring 2013.

Connect with Team Bayside High
Facebook | Twitter | SoundCloud

FEATURING (4 p.m. - 2 a.m.):

Kill Paris

Corey Baker aka Kill Paris has been scorching the internet blogesphere this summer. Receiving support from A-Trak, Dillon Francis, Flux Pavilion, and Skrillex. Kill Paris’s focus has been on giving his music away for free and make it easier for people to share with others. He just had his own “name your own price” album release on killparis.bandcamp.comcall “The Beginning (2012)” His also soundcloud features 23 songs that anyone can download for free. Being an Ableton Certified Trainer, his software of choice is Ableton Live. Live shows consist of 90 percent originals and remixes. Corey is currently sharing the stage all over the US with the likes of Pretty Lights, Zion I, Mimosa, AraabMuzik, Whiskey Pete, Figure, Mac Miller, Infected Mushroom, & Nicky Romero to name a few.

Connect with Kill Paris
Official Website | Facebook | Twitter | Soundcloud

Dov

Dov is the person behind Muti Music, a selector at heart, compulsively picking tunes for record labels and for your dancing / listening pleasure. He produces various bassline centric music, downtempo, midtempo and uptempo Dubstep, Drumstep, Glitch Hop, Breaks and whatever catches his fancy in the future, also receiving accolades for collaborations with ill.Gates, An-ten-nae and Funk Monsta. His sound when performing represents that of a whole movement of young producers coming out on his Muti Music imprint and adds directions that you know are going to emerge more in the future. Known for his energetic sets that delve as hard into a tranquil interlude as they do into bassline drops and glitched out frenzies. The sounds to be expected from Dov are always elevated and emotional, whether downtempo or peak time uptempo in super-clubs, his diversity and experience have prepared him for the job.

Connect with Dov
Official Website | Facebook | Twitter | Soundcloud

Sound Remedy

Sound Remedy is an American electronic music producer based out of Los Angeles, California. Hailing from Chicago, SR has been crafting his sound since the young age of 16, but only started to produce music fulltime 2 years ago. Despite obtaining a degree in finance from one of the nation’s elite business schools, SR opted to take a risk and pursue his true passion; music. Being that both of his parents are graduates of Juilliard School of Music and full time Chicago Symphony Orchestra players, this decision may have been in the cards all along.

Connect with Sound Remedy
Official Website | Facebook | Twitter | SoundCloud

Worthy

When it comes down to all the press and hype, his name says it all. He is Worthy. With an in-depth knowledge of production, mixing, and performance, Worthy has the insight to play for his audience, cultivating intense positive energy on the dance floor that can only be portrayed as superhuman. His sound can be described as organic breakbeats with a mix of future house, 80s, booty bass, and techno. As Carl Cox said, "The Worthy sound has always been powerful, rocking, funky, bass-driven music at its best, and for me this is the new wave in house music." Worthy has received the recognition of major producers who have played his tracks including Sven Vath, Diplo, and Richie Hawtin, among many.

Connect with Worthy
Official Website | Facebook | Twitter | SoundCloud

Amine Edge & DANCE

Born in 1983 in South of France, Amine Edge was House, DANCE was Hip Hop. Together they mash their experience, mood and style to create their own style “G-House”, Amine Edge & DANCE are knows in France as one of the symbolic figures of the brand new "G House" movement. Basically called "Gangsta House", the name of this movement comes from the special atmosphere this music just kicks away: here comes another vision of the House music, a stunning combination between Funk’s deep basses and inspired by the latest 80s Hip House movement. So far, 2012 was a great year. Released on Exploited, Noir, Rekids, Nurvous, FFRR (Pete Tong) or 2diy4 thanks to the legendary Going To Heaven With The Goodie-Goodies. Amine Edge & DANCE are one of major artists in deep-house industry. Recently, Mark Knight himself invited Amine Edge & DANCE as Guest on his radioshow. At work for his own imprint « CUFF » or in homestudio for the fourthcoming album released on Get Physical and releases stuff in OFF Recordings & Hot Creation. 2013 will be very busy for the Bad Boys of Marseille.

Connect with Amine Edge & Dance
Official Website | Facebook | Twitter | SoundCloud

Knight Riderz

Canadian-based producer Nick Samalack, performing as Knight Riderz which was originally formed as a duo, hails from Edmonton, AB but spends most of his time traveling the United States, rocking crowds. Once a mainstay as a Drum n’ Bass MC in the early 2000s, Samalack continued to expand his interest in bass music and found Knight Riderz. Strongly influenced by jungle and hip-hop, Samalack dove head first into the art of product ion wit h no limit at ion on genre or style....and Knight Riderz was born.With the musical creation of Knight Riderz, Samalack, began pushing boundaries with techniques, which is what distinguishes this project and his unique live performances from others. As Knight Riderz, Samalack delivers high energy sets composed of entirely original compositions that are accompanied by cutting edge dance rhythms and dance floor-targeted bass lines.

Connect with Knight Riderz
Facebook | Twitter | SoundCloud

LeDoom

Doombahton -- In a matter of one short year, Texas producer LeDoom has managed to push the boundaries of dance music with his signature approach to producing tracks in the moombahton genre. This versatile and prolific young artist has already gained support from the likes of DJs and producers such as Knife Party,Dillon Francis, DJ Craze, Tittsworth, Nadastrom and Munchi, Kissy Sell Out, Bro Safari to name a few, all proponents of their own unique bass-driven styles. Their stamps of approval reveal LeDoom's power as a genre-bending tastemaker. With his first EP "Doombah", released on the El Cuco Recordings imprint, LeDoom managed to chart at #5 on the Beatport Indie Dance charts and earn the respect of gigging DJs, fellow producers and the electronic music community at large. Fast forward a few short months and LeDoom has consistently released quality new music with Mad Decent, T & A Records, Party Like Us and Play Me Records, Slow Roast Records, continually charting in the Beatport Top 100 across various genres. A distinct production talent in the studio and a crowd favorite in his live sets, LeDoom's sound and selection have organically established him as a defining artist of the moombahton family, from behind the decks of DJs to the party on the dancefloor.

Connect with LeDoom
Official Website | Facebook | Twitter | SoundCloud

ill-esha

For over a decade, ill-esha has been an integral part of the North American electronic scene. Beginning as a vocalist, she soon added MCing and DJing to her repertoire, creating a dynamic and unique live show which has headlined alongside artists such as Andy C, Klute, Dieselboy, Vibesquad, LTJ Bukem, Tipper, T- Power & De La Soul. She has performed across North America, Europe and Asia; in clubs, at festivals, and even on TV shows on MTV Canada and the CBC. In 2001 her first 12” single was released on New York label Breakbeat Science; since then ill-esha has worked steadily as a producer and vocalist on labels like Dub Police, Haunted Audio, Simplify & Muti Music; hitting #1 singles download on Juno and commanding six spots of the top ten in the inaugural Beatport Glitch Hop charts. One of the founding members of the premier online community GlitchHopForum.com, her remixes are hugely popular, popping up in DJ sets across the globe. Her show is a fiery combination of original beats, glitch edits and live vocals, not to be missed!

Connect with ill-esha
Official Website | Facebook | Twitter | SoundCloud

Sazon Booya

Moombaton production & DJ two-piece Sazon Booya (click here) made up of NYC natives Mr.Vega & DJ SAV, have been making substantial waves across the blogosphere with their original moombahton productions since the beginning of 2011, and they’ve received countless nods of respect from top tier tastemakers from around the globe ever since.Sazon Booya debuted their first track “IIuvia” via moombahton creator Dave Nada’s soundcloud and website, to much success; instantly gaining play support from Munchi, Heartbreak, DJ Sabo, Obeyah, Skrillex, Boyfriend, Fellow and of course Dave Nada himself.

Connect with Sazon Booya
Official Website | Facebook | Twitter | SoundCloud

gLAdiator
gLAdiator is a DJ/Production duo from Los Angeles comprised of Danl Goodman and Ian Johnson. The two have established themselves as heavy hitters in the Trap/Bass-music game and show no signs of slowing down. They show their flex and diverse backgrounds by melding their collected musical taste and experience into a sound unique to gLAdiator. Their love of the Lakers and all things Mila Kunis fuels their productive fire with the aim of making a name for themselves in the wonderful melting pot they call home, Los Angeles.

Connect with gLAdiator
Facebook | Twitter | SoundCloud

column14:
Los Angeles public radio station KCRW will be broadcasting Morning Becomes Eclectic live from theSonos Studio @ SXSW from March 11 to 15 from 11am to 2pm (Austin time) during the SXSW Music Conference.


KCRW was one of the first radio stations to ever broadcast remotely from SXSW and is thrilled to have a new home that is open to the public.

“Sonos is committed to quality audio, innovation and music discovery, so this partnership is a natural fit, said Music Director and Morning Becomes Eclectic host Jason Bentley. “It also allows us to plant our flag in the middle of all the action at SXSW. People are welcome to stop by and pay us a visit.”


Like the Sonos Studio in Los Angeles, the Sonos Studio @ SXSW will feature a video installation, WiFi, film screenings, workshops and live bands. Band performances start Wednesday, March 13 from 3 to 8pm, and they will include; Poolside, Robert Delong, Sir Sly, Thomas Dybdahl, Chali 2Na, Kitten, and Robert Glasper.


SXSW badgeholders get priority access to the Sonos Studio, located directly behind the Convention Center at 608 Third Street, and it is open to the public during the day until it reaches capacity.

If you listen to KCRW on a Sonos speaker system, it is brought to you by TuneIn, who will be the supporting sponsor for KCRW’s on air broadcasts. In a continuing effort to make our content as accessible as possible,KCRW has found an ally in TuneIn, a service that offers access to thousands of streaming internet radio stations and millions of on-demand programs. KCRW continues to redefine what radio means in a world of evolving technology.

KCRW is hosting two official showcases open to anyone with a festival badge or wristband (no RSVP needed) on Wednesday, March 13, at the Radio Day Stage from 3pm to 6pm (Jake Bugg, Devendra Banhart, Boy) and at Haven from 8pm to 2am (Toro y Moi, Ra Ra Riot, Atlas Genius, Flight Facilities, Tom Odell, Wild Belle)

KCRW is also sponsoring Filter Magazine’s Showdown at Cedar Street showcases, which are open to the public. RSVP here and make sure to arrive early.


March 11th – March 15th, 11am-2am, 608 3rd St, Austin, TX

Schedule TBA

Lineup:

Robert Delong
Sir Sly
Thomas Dybdahl
Chali 2Na
Kitten
Robert Glasper

column14:
KUTX 98.9, The Austin Music Experience, and Four Seasons Hotel Austin
invite music fans to “KUTX Live at the Four Seasons,” which connects
music fans to some of the SXSW Music Festival’s most anticipated
artists. Produced by KUTX 98.9, each early-morning concert will
feature four artists playing 25-minute sets. The performances will be
broadcast live on KUTX 98.9. The event is open to the public on a
first-come, first served basis; no SXSW badges or wristbands are
required. Admission is $10 per day, which includes a breakfast taco,
granola bar and unlimited coffee. All proceeds benefit the Seton
Shivers Cancer Center.

DAY FOUR LINE-UP:

8 a.m. Kelly Hogan
9 a.m. My Jerusalem
10 a.m. Lianne La Havas
11 a.m. True Believers

column14:
For the 4th consecutive year, we'll be kicking off the gdgt live Tour down in Austin and we'd love to have you there.



Come out, have a drink and check out some of today's hottest new gear and services. We'll have the list of sponsors posted on the gdgt live site very soon.



As always, gdgt live is FREE to attend and SXSW badges are not required.


We'll have free gdgt t-shirts for the first several hundred attendees so be sure to get there early if you want one.

Everyone who shows up will have plenty of chances to win some awesome stuff from our great sponsors.

Unfortunately, due to circumstances beyond our control, this event is 21+ only. We're not happy about it, but all our other 2013 gdgt live events will open to everyone...



gdgt live is the only tech event series specifically designed to give actual consumers a chance to connect face-to-face with todays top tech companies and hottest startups.


Make sure to tell your friends and share info on the event on your social networks. The official Twitter hashtag is @gdgtaustin.


Look forward to seeing you there!


- via Eventbrite
