column14:
MashBash at SXSWi 2013 Details
Date: Sunday, March 10, 2013
Time: 9 p.m. to 2 a.m.
Location: Speakeasy, 412 Congress Ave, Austin, Texas

RSVP Policy
Open to all 21+ SXSWi badge holders. Please RSVP on Eventbrite.

We're happy to announce the return of MashBash at SXSWi 2013! Amid the plethora of panels, presentations and parties, Mashable will be hosting one of the biggest and most memorable events in Austin.


Join Mashable and the SXSWi community on Sunday, March 10 from 9 p.m. to 2 a.m. for an evening of music, dancing and digital inspiration, along with an open bar. And as always, there will be a few surprises along the way.


Joining us as the talent behind the turntables will be DJ Mick Boogie, whose arsenal of tunes range from 80s, rock and soul, to disco, house and electro. Make sure to come with your dancing shoes on.


Our MashBash sponsors Yappem and 3M will make the evening truly unique with their special digital activations, which will be revealed at the party.

In addition to the MashBash on Sunday night, we have some exciting plans that we'll be announcing soon, so stay tuned!


Socialize
Follow #MashSXSW on Twitter, Facebook, Google+, Foursquare, and Instagram.



via Mashable.com

column14:
HEAR THERE. EVERYWHERE.
The 6th Annual Dart Music International House

Since 2008 DMI has helped Austin "Hear There. Everywhere." by presenting unprecedented international cultural events in Austin during the big festival week. Some of the highlights have included historic events like "Music From Space" (an exclusive video from the International Space Station), "6 Bands 6 Continents" (back-to-back performances by artists from every inhabited continent), and "Taquacore + i:Made in Israel + ATX Hip Hop" (Iranian, Israeli, and Austin artists performing together).


This year is going to add to that legacy in an informal, "happy hour" setting. From Tuesday, March 12 through Friday, March 15, in between the music panels / day parties and the nightly showcases, DMI will be producing the 6th Annual Dart Music International House event in downtown Austin. This is your opportunity of a lifetime to experience global culture in an informal setting. We hope to see you there!


WHEN: Tuesday, March 12 through Friday, March 15, 2013; 5-8PM Daily
WHERE: Mark McCrimmon Law Office, 704 West 9th Street (Map)
WHAT: Music & culture with Artists from Every Inhabited Continent
WHO: Complimentary food and drinks from The Peached Tortilla, Austin Beerworks, Tito's Handmade Vodka, and more.
ADMISSION: FREE, ALL AGES


This project is funded and supported in part by the City of Austin through the Economic Growth & Redevelopment Services Office / Cultural Arts Division believing an investment in the Arts is an investment in Austin's future. Visit Austin at NowPlayingAustin.com.

column14:
JACK BLACK and KYLE GASS of TENACIOUS D will be to promote the web comedy series Ghost Girls out via Yahoo! Screen. The two of them will be performing at a screening party presented by Yahoo! in the company's venue. ...The event will not be open to the public and only be open to SXSW attendees, as well as the press.

“There is no better to unleash the beast that is Ghost Ghirls on an unsuspecting audience,” said Black, in a statement. “Austin knows how to rock, and how how to party, and how to marvel at the supernatural forces that inhabit our world. I’m so proud of this show, and I will be there with bells on, to bask in the glory.” (via popwatch)

Ghost Ghirls is a new, 12-episode web series about two hilariously inept female ghost hunters, played by Amanda Lund and Maria Blasucci, attempting to solve mysteries behind paranormal procedural, while attempting to prove their legitimacy to their clients, other visitors and themselves.The show was created by Jeremy Konner (of Comedy Central’s Drunk History) is also directing the series.

column14:
Carson Daly's "Last Call" show will hold its annual showcase at SXSW, this year emphasizing rock bands that have not made their television debuts.

Angel Haze, Big Black Delta, Glossary, Grape St., Maximum Hedrum and The Coup will perform March 13 at Cedar Street Courtyard in Austin. A week-long spotlight on SXSW will begin March 19 on "Last Call with Carson Daly," which airs on NBC 1:35 a.m.-2:05 a.m. Jake Bugg, Joey Bada$$, Angel Haze and Chloe Chaidez from the band Kitten will be among the guests.

"The object is to put together the most eclectic lineup possible," Daly told Billboard. "Having national television debuts is important, whether it's a band that's been around for a minute or brand new like Angel Haze. They can say 'I've been on NBC' and use it as a calling card. New music and storytelling -- that's what we work on and something (music booker) Davis Powers and I speak about: Who are the people with a good story?"

Ford Fiesta is sponsoring the showcase. "Last Call" will also feature Ford Fiesta's social media program, "Fiesta Movement: A Social Remix," where a handpicked group of insiders will be introducing the 2014 Ford Fiesta through their photos and videos.
Daly says they continue to book acts for the interview segments, noting the JoeyBada$$ booking was the most recent one added. "Were not a traditional late night show," Daly notes, saying they move quickly when the buzz around an act starts growing. "But it is nimble and modular. We're like kids in a candy store at SXSW, but we have to be economical with our time and money."

via Billboard

column2: Boot Campaign's "Friends With Benefits" Party During SXSW
column12: Cody Canada,Sunny Sweeney,Aaron Watson,Sons of Fathers,Six Market Blvd,Midnight River Choir,The Rankin Twins
column13: Boot Campaign to Throw “Friends With Benefits” Party During SXSW 2013| Performances by Cody Canada, Sunny Sweeney, Aaron Watson, Sons of Fathers, Six Market Boulevard, Midnight River Choir, The Rankin Twins and surprise guests! Looking for a truly unique experience during SXSW? KOKE FM and Wild Turkey present the Boot Campaign’s “Friends With Benefits” party during SXSW. “Friends With Benefits” features performances by Cody Canada, Sunny Sweeney, Aaron Watson, Sons of Fathers, Six Market Blvd, Midnight River Choir, The Rankin Twins and other surprise guests! The Boot Campaign’s “Friends With Benefits” party during SXSW is March 12, 2013 at Peckerheads on Austin’s famed 6th Street. “Friends With Benefits” will directly benefit the Boot Campaign’s programs that are caring for military personnel, past and present, healing from a variety of physical and emotional combat wounds. Doors open at 7:00pm with your “Friends With Benefits” hosts Rita Ballou of Rawhide and Velvet, and KOKE FM’s Eric Raines and Drew Bennett. The party will feature live music on two stages, raffle, and more! Wild Turkey and Shiner Beers will be the featured beverages of the night, with a portion of your drink purchases being donated back to the Boot Campaign. “Friends With Benefits” is an intimate concert experience. Tickets are extremely limited, so purchase yours today on http://bit.ly/FWBSXSW For those who cannot attend, the Boot Campaign is partnering with KOKE-FM and Stage It to offer a live radio broadcast and online video stream of the concert. Details on how to watch and listen will be posted on www.KOKEFM.com and www.BootCampaign.com The “Friends with Benefits” party wouldn’t be possible with out these supporters: KOKE-FM, Wild Turkey, Peckerheads, Rawhide and Velvet, Shiner Beers, and Stage It. About The Boot Campaign The Boot Campaign is a national 501c3 patriotic movement that is dedicated to showing tangible appreciation of our active military, raising awareness of the challenges they face upon return and supporting their transition home. Through the sale of its signature military combat boots, general public donations, and corporate sponsorship, the Boot Campaign operates five distinct programs -- Jobs, Housing, Family Support, Urgent Assistance and Wellness-- that are caring for military personnel, past and present, healing from a variety of physical and emotional combat wounds, embodying the campaign motto that, “When They Come Back, We Give Back”. www.BootCampaign.com * Media Contact: Meghan McDermott Meghan@BootCampaign.com * Join the line up: Larry Murray Booking@BootCampaign.com

column14:
Silent Frisco Austin Session5 - Night One
Presented by Silent Frisco
Thursday, March 14th - 10pm to 6am

For 2013 we are moving downtown to the sublime WANDERLUST LIVE space on 4th St. We are thrilled to be welcomed into this unique and sacred artspace. Silent Frisco and SunsetSF have worked to assemble yet another 'once in a lifetime' 3-night musical lineup, and will be unveiling quite a few visual thrills as well.

Running from 10pm till sunrise on Thursday-Saturday, March 14-16, these events aim to provide the Austin arts community with a pure-music, after-hours event. Unlike much of SX, these are non-sponsored and unofficial events that are focused solely on the arts, the music and the communal experience. They will leverage the unparalleled sound, comfort and range of Silent Frisco’s unique “yellowjacket” twin-channel headphones, of which no more than THREE HUNDRED will be available.

Featuring the sounds of...

::ROB GARZA (thievery corporation | esl-dc)
::KENTARO (ninja tune | japan)
::SHORTKUT (beat junkies | sfo)
::RHETTMATIC (beat junkies | l.a.)
::FORT KNOX 5, (fort knox recordings | dc)
::THUNDERBALL (esl records - dc)
::SABO(sol selectas | nyc)
::CHICO MANN (antibalas - nyc)
::SMALLTOWN DJs (calgary)
::KNIGHT RIDERZ (canada)
::QUICKIE MART(new orleans)
::DJ MANNY (austin)
::MOTION POTION (silent frisco | sfo)
::TUNAFIST (sex party | new orleans)
::LAFA TAYLOR (portland)
::MAX ULIS (canada)
::WAX ROMEO (canada)
::MAMA MICHE (canada)
::DEEJAY THEORY (sfo)
::NICO LUMINOUS (los angeles)
::MANCUB (space cowboys | oakland)
::EXPO (rootdown | la)
::PLATURN (oakland faders)
::BIGFACE (austin)
::JESSE BREDE (austin)
::CONGO SANCHEZ (see-i/thievery corp | dc)
::S.P.E.C.T.R.E. (colorado)
::ULTRAVIOLET (trap city | sfo)
::$MALL $HANGE (nyc)
::KUNG FU CHRIS (new orleans)

To see who is playing on individual nights, check that show page (www.silentfrisco.com)

TICKETS: http://www.silentfrisco.com/
As always, Silent Frisco Austin Session5 remains a no "sponsor", no “branding”, no “industry” event and is not a “rave”. There IS a cover charge to cover our costs and this WILL SELL OUT so please PURCHASE ADVANCE at www.silentfrisco.com. We will also have a limited # of 3-night discount passes.

FOOD & BEVERAGE: Wanderlust Live will be serving café-fare and non-alcoholic beverages throughout the run.


WE ARE 21+ THIS YEAR | We regret to inform that due to the smaller capacity and its proximity to the downtown scrutiny, Silent Frisco Austin Session5 will be a 21+ w/ID event. As always, Silent Frisco did its best to attempt to make this an all-ages event but we were not successful in this case. Our apologies to our under/21 fans.

Manitoba will host a stellar showcase featuring four SXSW favorites: noise pop act Boats, fresh from the release of its Kill Rock Stars full-length debut, A Fairway Full of Miners; the charming and powerful soul/pop songstresses of Chic Gamine, one of NPR’s top four SXSW picks last year; inventive indie outfit Royal Canoe, which wowed the crowds and critics at CMJ in October; and Paste Magazine fave, explosive indie soul popsters Imaginary Cities, a band that wears Manitoba on its sleeve (tattooed to guitarist/songwriter Rusty Matyas’ right arm, actually), but is loved around the globe.

column14:
RSVP

*FREE*

THE LINE-UP (not in order of appearance):

Andrew Duncan Brown and The Dirty Rascals:
Andrew’s moody singing is entrancing, rooted in folk and delta-blues coupled with rock music elements. Simple, yet full of emotion; there is something deeper that lies at the heart of every song. The melody intoxicates the listeners by allowing them to form their own relationship and attachment with the songs.
http://www.andrewduncanbrown.com/

Avery:
Avery formed in March of 2011 by Allison Galbreath and Mariah DeRaet. After playing together for a couple months Brad Mitchell joined the mix and changed the game by further producing their simplistic stylings with slide guitars and ambient lead parts. In July of 2012 some heavier percussion was needed and Eric Estrada was happy to oblige.
www.reverbnation.com/averyaz

Bad Lucy:
The trio of J. Miller, Alex Kyhn and Alex Lee are an amalgamation of differing influences that meld into their unique style known for its nuance, use of space and surprising harmonies. J. Miller pulls heavily from his folk sensibilities when writing and performing, while bassist Alex Kyhn brings to the fold a mix of jazz and soul. Drummer Alex Lee’s marching and rock roots add the final layer.

Officially formed in March 2011, the band showcased their sounds on a self-titled release in May 2012. The debut, which was recorded live to tape, came on the heels of a year of highs for the band including the broadcast of their single “Forward” on the Macy’s Thanksgiving Day Parade. The song was also a “homegrown hit” on the local, Phoenix airwaves.

Known for “sounding just like the recording” during their live performances, the band often silences a room within minutes. A reviewer/blogger, that was first introduced to the band via a live stream, sums it up best: "The band is called Bad Lucy, and their gorgeous, melodic songs and energetic live show blasted right through the off-kilter webcam and livestream hiccups—and into my heart. Shut up, I’m serious."
www.badlucyband.com

Captain Squeegee:
"The Gods of Music are not dead! They are coming out of retirement for this young group brimming with talent, enthusiasm, and freshness" (French-Webzine "Progressia"). In a world strangled by mediocrity and distraction, Captain Squeegee leads a legacy to push the boundaries of music and bend the rules of the industry itself. Since their mysterious formation in 2003, they have allowed fate to arrange their current line-up (no original members), which has since performed hundreds of shows and festivals, released two albums, and manifested multiple music videos. Even before birthing their internationally acclaimed full length, Nothing vs Everything (2008), the band has made numerous journeys across the southwest with an intent to infect the people with their unique sound and offer something seriously different to the artistic community. Their progressive blend of multi-instrumentation and conceptualized orchestrations have been described as "Fantasia music, with lead singer Danny Torgersen making like Mickey in a swirling maelstrom of flying horns, dancing guitars, broken melodies, and mad-prophet vocalizing" (Phoenix New Times), and was even awarded "Best album of 2008" and "Best hope of 2009" by French Webzine-"Progressia". Recently, they have paired up with the "Lucidity Web-Saga" as actors and musicians, even writing it's theme song, "Your Own Invention", which they recorded in a pyramid. Forever in stark contrast to the robotic, zombie infested waters of the mass media and mainstream, Squeegee will continue to offer a new age perspective, driving their fans and future fans to open the mind's eye (and ear)... and "See More Clearly".
www.captainsqueegee.com

Danger Paul:
Danger Paul consists of Paul Balazs (guitar/vocals), Calin Gross (guitar/lap steel slide), Keith Fama (bass), and Ari Leopold (drums). With a wide variety of influence the only simple working description is JAZZ GRUNGE.
http://dangerpaul.bandcamp.com/

Japhy’s Descent:
Japhy's Descent is about planting seeds to watch our community grow. Music has brought us & those around us so much joy, that we wish to share that love with the world around us. Brian, Martin, James & Travis wish to invite you to take the plunge into the wonderful world around you. Listen to music, laugh, play, love, share, & experience the awe around you by simply being apart of it. Remember... "You can't fall off a mountain".
www.reverbnation.com/japhysdescent

Field Tripp:
Field Tripp is an American alternative rock band based in Phoenix, AZ. The band was formed in 2007 as a three-piece by songwriters Dan Allmond, Jonathon Smith, and Matthew Newcomb. The trio released one self-titled 5 song EP in late 2007. Field Tripp's roster has changed frequently, with only singer/guitarist Dan Allmond remaining from the original lineup. Since mid 2011 the other members include multi-instrumentalists Eliz Christy and Brian Mabry with Amir Azzabi on drums. The band has developed a reputation for their raw yet poppy sound, use of unconventional instruments, and strong songwriting. Field Tripp released their first full length album entitled Super-Ego Friendly in 2011 and is currently recording their second album due for release in Summer 2013.
www.reverbnation.com/fieldtripp

Frequent Kings:
Frequent Kings originally started with Glenn Nishida and WuT then migrated to WuT and Kamakane who Met in Hawaii through a musical mutual friend. “ Now...... Frequent Kings Consist of Band that is sticking like Hot glue melted. WuT (Tim), Guitarist ,Vocalist, and occasional harmonica player... the Pocket playing Drummer Josh, and The laid Back Bassist and Keyboardist Ryan. Occcasionally Kamakane lead Guitarist comes in from Hawaii to grace us with his Masterful skills. This combination of players has evolved in a next generation Dirty Blues, new to old school Low Flow, Vibed Out organically based Fresh Band! Currently were Playing steady Gigs, mixed with originals and Covers.
COME ON IN!
www.frequentkings.com

Sundressed:
Sundressed is a 4-piece indie rock band from Tempe Arizona comprised of songwriter Trevor Hedges, GUitarist Tyler Kees, Bassist Evan Kees and Garrett Tretta. Their sound is a mix of a variety of influences from bright eyes to the Doors. They formed in November of 2011. Since then they have released a very promising ep and are currently wrapping up their first full length record. Sundressed has been described as taking a Neil young song and playing it with the punk rock fury of the pixies. Be sure to check out their showcase at sxsw!
http://sundressed.bandcamp.com

The Hourglass Cats:
Forming together in the dusty southwest, The Hourglass Cats are a high energy five piece outfit with members from NY, Germany, CA, and AZ. THC brings a wide range of influences to the table to create a truly unique genre-defying soundscape. Their music has heavy roots in Latin Reggae/Ska, RockNRoll, Funk, and Hip hop.
www.iheartthc.com

column14:
Join Tech Cocktail as we celebrate some of the world's hottest startups on the grand stage at SXSW.


We're finalizing the details for SXSW 2013, but you can rest assured it's going to be an action packed day, concluding with a massive Tech Cocktail Mixer (which is code for party).


This marks Tech Cocktail's fourth annual SXSW bash. Chances are, if you've been to SXSW in years' past, you're familiar with how we roll. In case you missed the previous festivities, check these links from SXSW 2012, SXSW 2011 and SXSW 2010.

Showcasing Startups
Past showcased startups at our events have gotten great feedback, been funded on the spot, met new employees, investors, and some have even be acquired. Some of our SXSW showcased startup alumni include FitOrbit, Foodspotting, Khush, Mobile Roadie, Personal, Storify, Udemy, Tango, SaneBox, Sawbuck, Sifteo, Sonar, Sphero, Stitch Labs, Votizen, and many more.


Showcase Your Startup
Want to showcase your startup in front of hundreds of fellow technology enthusiasts, investors, and high profile media? You can - simply fill out the application here.


Interested in Sponsoring?
Sponsorship opportunities are available for all the various activities. If you are interested contact us here and we’ll circle back with the SXSW information.

Event details:

When: Saturday, March 9th, 2011 at 6:00 p.m. till the cows come home

Where: The Stage on Sixth, 508 East 6th Street, Austin, TX

What: A cocktail of tech and startup enthusiasts

Price: Free with a SXSW badge (must be 21+ years old to enter)

***RSVP does not guarantee entrance. First come first serve.

THANK YOU TO OUR SPONSOR!!!

Gold Sponsor, CO


Tech Cocktail (http://tech.co) is a media company that covers the latest tech innovations across the globe. Tech Cocktail has been hosting mixer events and writing about technology start-ups and entrepreneurs across the country with the focus of helping to amplify the local technology signal since 2006. We have hosted large events in Chicago, D.C., NY, San Francisco, Boston, Boulder, San Diego, Detroit, Boise, Austin, Barcelona and more. Read more about Tech Cocktail.

column14:
Silent Frisco Austin Session5 - Night Two
Presented by Silent Frisco
Friday, March 15th - 10pm to 6am

For 2013 we are moving downtown to the sublime WANDERLUST LIVE space on 4th St. We are thrilled to be welcomed into this unique and sacred artspace. Silent Frisco and SunsetSF have worked to assemble yet another 'once in a lifetime' 3-night musical lineup, and will be unveiling quite a few visual thrills as well.

Running from 10pm till sunrise on Thursday-Saturday, March 14-16, these events aim to provide the Austin arts community with a pure-music, after-hours event. Unlike much of SX, these are non-sponsored and unofficial events that are focused solely on the arts, the music and the communal experience. They will leverage the unparalleled sound, comfort and range of Silent Frisco’s unique “yellowjacket” twin-channel headphones, of which no more than THREE HUNDRED will be available.

Featuring the sounds of...

::ROB GARZA (thievery corporation | esl-dc)
::KENTARO (ninja tune | japan)
::SHORTKUT (beat junkies | sfo)
::RHETTMATIC (beat junkies | l.a.)
::FORT KNOX 5, (fort knox recordings | dc)
::THUNDERBALL (esl records - dc)
::SABO(sol selectas | nyc)

::SMALLTOWN DJs (calgary)
::KNIGHT RIDERZ (canada)
::QUICKIE MART(new orleans)
::DJ MANNY (austin)
::MOTION POTION (silent frisco | sfo)
::TUNAFIST (sex party | new orleans)
::LAFA TAYLOR (portland)
::MAX ULIS (canada)
::WAX ROMEO (canada)
::MAMA MICHE (canada)

::NICO LUMINOUS (los angeles)
::MANCUB (space cowboys | oakland)
::EXPO (rootdown | la)
::PLATURN (oakland faders)
::BIGFACE (austin)

::CONGO SANCHEZ (see-i/thievery corp | dc)
::S.P.E.C.T.R.E. (colorado)
::ULTRAVIOLET (trap city | sfo)
::$MALL $HANGE (nyc)
::KUNG FU CHRIS (new orleans)

To see who is playing on individual nights, check that show page (www.silentfrisco.com)

TICKETS: http://www.silentfrisco.com/
As always, Silent Frisco Austin Session5 remains a no "sponsor", no “branding”, no “industry” event and is not a “rave”. There IS a cover charge to cover our costs and this WILL SELL OUT so please PURCHASE ADVANCE at www.silentfrisco.com. We will also have a limited # of 3-night discount passes.

FOOD & BEVERAGE: Wanderlust Live will be serving café-fare and non-alcoholic beverages throughout the run.


WE ARE 21+ THIS YEAR | We regret to inform that due to the smaller capacity and its proximity to the downtown scrutiny, Silent Frisco Austin Session5 will be a 21+ w/ID event. As always, Silent Frisco did its best to attempt to make this an all-ages event but we were not successful in this case. Our apologies to our under/21 fans.

column14:
HEAR THERE. EVERYWHERE.
The 6th Annual Dart Music International House

Since 2008 DMI has helped Austin "Hear There. Everywhere." by presenting unprecedented international cultural events in Austin during the big festival week. Some of the highlights have included historic events like "Music From Space" (an exclusive video from the International Space Station), "6 Bands 6 Continents" (back-to-back performances by artists from every inhabited continent), and "Taquacore + i:Made in Israel + ATX Hip Hop" (Iranian, Israeli, and Austin artists performing together).


This year is going to add to that legacy in an informal, "happy hour" setting. From Tuesday, March 12 through Friday, March 15, in between the music panels / day parties and the nightly showcases, DMI will be producing the 6th Annual Dart Music International House event in downtown Austin. This is your opportunity of a lifetime to experience global culture in an informal setting. We hope to see you there!


WHEN: Tuesday, March 12 through Friday, March 15, 2013; 5-8PM Daily
WHERE: Mark McCrimmon Law Office, 704 West 9th Street (Map)
WHAT: Music & culture with Artists from Every Inhabited Continent
WHO: Complimentary food and drinks from The Peached Tortilla, Austin Beerworks, Tito's Handmade Vodka, and more.
ADMISSION: FREE, ALL AGES


This project is funded and supported in part by the City of Austin through the Economic Growth & Redevelopment Services Office / Cultural Arts Division believing an investment in the Arts is an investment in Austin's future. Visit Austin at NowPlayingAustin.com.

column14:
The “Kingdom Experience” will take place on Saturday, March 16 from 10am – 4pm at the Carver Cultural Center (as it has been since 2009) and will be comprised of concerts and panel discussions about music ministry.


It is an official SXSW event and, as in the past, it will be FREE and open to the public. Attendees will NOT need a SXSW badge or wristband to get in.


A separate showcase by Reach Records (including Lecrae, Andy Mineo, and others) will also be held earlier in the week.


The first round of artists lined up for this event include:

  • Jin
  • Da’ T.R.U.T.H.
  • The Digital Age (aka the Dave Crowder Band minus Dave Crowder)
  • Sho Baraka
  • V Rose
  • FLAME
  • Eshon Burgundy
  • DJ DMD
  • Johnathan McReynolds
  • The W.A.R.R.I.O.R.S. ATX
  • Willie Moore, Jr.
  • Propaganda


Stay tuned for more details.

column14:
DJ Geno, Across the Board and Gowhere Hip Hop present "Coup de Grace" Unofficial SXSW Showcase. (Free Entry with RSVP on Do512)

"Coup De Grace" (pronounce: kuː də ˈɡrɑːs) an end all be all event that punctuates the SXSW 2013 culture. Coup de Grace will stay true to the SXSW culture by not sticking to a script. This event will cover a broad range of Music, with the focus from Hip Hop to Rock, Indie, and R&B. The Historic Victory Grill is the perfect venue to present this ground breaking event.

Independent Artists will be able to share the stage with mainstream Acts to create a surreal experience that will leave lasting impressions to those blessed to attend!

With event partners DJ Geno, Across the Board, LiveGrandeur and along with our media sponsors SongDish and GoWhereHipHop, together we deliver and showcase talents at SXSW that we believe to be the next "New Artist of the Year."

So join us whether on stage or in the building, Enjoy what SX was meant to be, and witness the future of Music.

Hosted By: Dj Geno & Tony Baines

column14:
REDEFINE magazine, Pour Le Corps, Clumsy N Shy & Holocene present…

FEEL YOU: a house party at the intersection of psych and dance

Saturday, March 16th, 2013

@ House Of Commons
2610 Rio Grande St., Austin, TX
3:00pm – Late


ALWAYS FREE, ALL-AGES, DIY
& 100% UNAFFILIATED W/ SXSW
AND OH YEAH +++ FREE BEER +++


RSVP ON FACEBOOK


Good things come in threes.


Three months after the world hasn’t ended, the all-female booking trifecta of Marjorie Owens (label owner of Pour Le Corps and influential blog Clumsy N Shy), Gina Altamura (talent buyer at innovative Portland nightclub Holocene), and Vivian Hua (Editor-in-Chief of REDEFINE magazine) return to SXSW for the third year in a row. We call upon this heap of holy trinities to inspire ferocious whimsy at yet another free, all-ages, and unofficial house party for all who are weak and worn from the usual festival circuit.


An oasis for mythic musics at SXSW 2013, FEEL YOU is all about creating clarity, harmony and POSI VIBES in an oft-overwhelming week of chaos. Our focus is on music that muddles introspective psychedelia with exuberant dance, so expect revelry and epiphanies.


FEEL YOU blesses showgoers throughout its duration first and foremost with a GOOD ZONE — while also boasting an excellent lineup, attention to audiovisual delights, a profusion of girl power, and – uh – plenty of FREE BEER. Join us in the spirit of liveliness (or even just post-non-apocalyptic aliveness) in the year 2013!


TRANSCENDING SOCIAL CONSTRUCTS ++ REVELING IN SHARED PARADIGMS


DOWNLOAD HOUSE PARTY MIXTAPE ON REDEFINE

M.I.A. CREW:

★•´´¯`• DANNY THE WILD CHILD
(compression san francisco / sound solution digital / rockers 175 / m.i.a. dnb chicago)

Danny the Wildchild aka Daniel Garcia was born on the South side of Chicago in 1977. The brother of a once aspiring DJ, he keenly watched and quickly learned the tricks of the trade. Danny began djing at age nine soon surpassing his brother’s abilities and eventually inherited his equipment and records. At twelve, Danny entered a Chicago area contest for young DJ’s and won. He took home that fifty-dollar prize and was called “The Wildchild” from that day forward.......
https://www.facebook.com/pages/Danny-The-Wildchild/115971325117979
http://soundcloud.com/danny-the-wildchild

★•´´¯`•ALFONZ "DELAMOTA"
(combat records / high $ociety / m.i.a. dnb chicago)

His name is synonymous with Chicago drum n bass and for being one of the founders and president of one of Americas largest drum n bass music groups, the M.I.A. (murda In america). DELAMOTA got his start djing the after-hours and small underground parties in Chicago during the early 90's rave scene as a dj, in 1998 he decided to start a production company called Sky High and put on several shows with attendance as high as 8500 people in a three room venue. With his dedication to the dnb sound he managed to travel all over the United States, Alfonz has played well over 25 cities in over 20 states both headlining and djing along side some of the worlds top electronic music producers and djs.
https://www.facebook.com/pages/Alfonz-DeLaMota/235722766465723
http://www.soundcloud.com/alfonzdelamota

★•´´¯`•RAGGA SCUM
(congo natty / cymbalism recordings / m.i.a. dnb kansas city)

Ragga Scum is widely known for his inhuman technical style of mixing on the decks. Getting his start in 1999 this artist is no rookie behind the turntables with his wide range of styles from tare-out/mash-up to melodic dubwise mixing. In 2006 he made his debut with his collaboration hit 'Another Champion' with long time producing partner Direct Feed on the label Hum Fi Drum.....
http://www.raggascum.com/
https://www.facebook.com/officialraggascum?fref=ts

★•´´¯`•AUDIO-ONE
(m.i.a. dnb norcal)

One of San Francisco's most musically diverse DJ’s making himself a staple in the notorious club and rave scenes for over a decade. DJ Audio1 digs deep with an eclectic mix of classics, new music, remixes and exclusive edits while showcasing his stellar programming, fast paced mixing and turntable skills. While his roots are in Hip-Hop, DJ Audio1 is better known as one of the top Drum&Bass/Dubstep DJs on the West Coast, affiliated to the MURDA IN AMERICA crew.
https://soundcloud.com/#audio1
https://www.facebook.com/thedjaudio1

★•´´¯`•SUBREAPER
(m.i.a. dnb boston)

Jeff 'Subreaper' has been defining his mix style since the turn of the millennium. With a solid dedication to the art form, Jeff secured slots performing at various venues along the east coast under, Marc Pastor, a name built from fragments of his name and interests.
Jeff devoted himself to growing as an artist through various means and methods. Taking on production in 2002, an alliance was formed with fellow Drum & Bass performer, Andromeda. The project resulted in 9 rough tracks that would cement a strong basis for future productions.
https://soundcloud.com/#subreaper
http://miadnb.com/profile.php?id=32

★•´´¯`•KRSP
(m.i.a. dnb kansas, Galactic Soul Tribe)
It started in the late 90's. I heard some Drum'n'Bass at some show I don't remember the name of. I didn't know it was drum'n'bass at the time, I just knew I had to get more of this NOW!!! It was that very next day I started in my search. I started coming up with some planet of the drum stuff. Then after that i moved right through the sub genres until I found Techstep. JeeYA!!!!
I started playing records about a decade ago. Really just got into it for me, I just wanted to hear what I could mix together in my room for me. My goal was never to be a superstar dj. Eventually after getting to the point of wanting to now share my music with people, I was ready.
https://www.facebook.com/pages/KRSP/138379402869280?ref=stream
https://soundcloud.com/#krsp

column13: Silent Frisco Austin Session5 - Night ThreePresented by Silent Frisco|Saturday, March 16th - 10pm to 6am|For 2013 we are moving downtown to the sublime WANDERLUST LIVE space on 4th St. We are thrilled to be welcomed into this unique and sacred artspace. Silent Frisco and SunsetSF have worked to assemble yet another 'once in a lifetime' 3-night musical lineup, and will be unveiling quite a few visual thrills as well.|Running from 10pm till sunrise on Thursday-Saturday, March 14-16, these events aim to provide the Austin arts community with a pure-music, after-hours event. Unlike much of SX, these are non-sponsored and unofficial events that are focused solely on the arts, the music and the communal experience. They will leverage the unparalleled sound, comfort and range of Silent Frisco’s unique “yellowjacket” twin-channel headphones, of which no more than THREE HUNDRED will be available.|Featuring the sounds of...|::ROB GARZA (thievery corporation | esl-dc)|::KENTARO (ninja tune | japan)|::SHORTKUT (beat junkies | sfo)|::RHETTMATIC (beat junkies | l.a.)|::FORT KNOX 5, (fort knox recordings | dc)|::THUNDERBALL (esl records - dc)|::SABO(sol selectas | nyc)|::CHICO MANN (antibalas - nyc)|::SMALLTOWN DJs (calgary)|::KNIGHT RIDERZ (canada)|::QUICKIE MART(new orleans)|::DJ MANNY (austin)|::MOTION POTION (silent frisco | sfo)|::TUNAFIST (sex party | new orleans)|::LAFA TAYLOR (portland)|::MAX ULIS (canada)|::WAX ROMEO (canada)|::MAMA MICHE (canada)|::DEEJAY THEORY (sfo)|::NICO LUMINOUS (los angeles)|::MANCUB (space cowboys | oakland)|::EXPO (rootdown | la)|::PLATURN (oakland faders)|::BIGFACE (austin)|::JESSE BREDE (austin)|::CONGO SANCHEZ (see-i/thievery corp | dc)|::S.P.E.C.T.R.E. (colorado)|::ULTRAVIOLET (trap city | sfo)|::$MALL $HANGE (nyc)|::KUNG FU CHRIS (new orleans)|To see who is playing on individual nights, check that show page (www.silentfrisco.com)|TICKETS: http://www.silentfrisco.com/|As always, Silent Frisco Austin Session5 remains a no "sponsor", no “branding”, no “industry” event and is not a “rave”. There IS a cover charge to cover our costs and this WILL SELL OUT so please PURCHASE ADVANCE at www.silentfrisco.com. We will also have a limited # of 3-night discount passes.|FOOD & BEVERAGE: Wanderlust Live will be serving café-fare and non-alcoholic beverages throughout the run. |WE ARE 21+ THIS YEAR | We regret to inform that due to the smaller capacity and its proximity to the downtown scrutiny, Silent Frisco Austin Session5 will be a 21+ w/ID event. As always, Silent Frisco did its best to attempt to make this an all-ages event but we were not successful in this case. Our apologies to our under/21 fans.
column14:
Silent Frisco Austin Session5 - Night Three
Presented by Silent Frisco
Saturday, March 16th - 10pm to 6am

For 2013 we are moving downtown to the sublime WANDERLUST LIVE space on 4th St. We are thrilled to be welcomed into this unique and sacred artspace. Silent Frisco and SunsetSF have worked to assemble yet another 'once in a lifetime' 3-night musical lineup, and will be unveiling quite a few visual thrills as well.

Running from 10pm till sunrise on Thursday-Saturday, March 14-16, these events aim to provide the Austin arts community with a pure-music, after-hours event. Unlike much of SX, these are non-sponsored and unofficial events that are focused solely on the arts, the music and the communal experience. They will leverage the unparalleled sound, comfort and range of Silent Frisco’s unique “yellowjacket” twin-channel headphones, of which no more than THREE HUNDRED will be available.

Featuring the sounds of...

::ROB GARZA (thievery corporation | esl-dc)
::KENTARO (ninja tune | japan)

To see who is playing on individual nights, check that show page (www.silentfrisco.com)

TICKETS: http://www.silentfrisco.com/
As always, Silent Frisco Austin Session5 remains a no "sponsor", no “branding”, no “industry” event and is not a “rave”. There IS a cover charge to cover our costs and this WILL SELL OUT so please PURCHASE ADVANCE at www.silentfrisco.com. We will also have a limited # of 3-night discount passes.

FOOD & BEVERAGE: Wanderlust Live will be serving café-fare and non-alcoholic beverages throughout the run.


WE ARE 21+ THIS YEAR | We regret to inform that due to the smaller capacity and its proximity to the downtown scrutiny, Silent Frisco Austin Session5 will be a 21+ w/ID event. As always, Silent Frisco did its best to attempt to make this an all-ages event but we were not successful in this case. Our apologies to our under/21 fans.

column14:
Artist rumored to be at SX2013. We think Operation Every Band might just be onto something here...


On March 12, "We are a Sad Band" is playing at The Main according to the official SX schedule BUT no band with that name seems to exist. Here's Operation Every Band's reasoning that it's ACTUALLY Thom Yorke:

Every year, there seems to be something that doesn’t quite look right on the SXSW roster. Many times, this ends up being a surprise show of some sort, an event many know takes place all over Austin. After looking through Spotify, I’ll normally hit Google to begin my research. We Are a Sad Band, who are apparently a funk band from “Sadville” , Texas (their website is listed as http://sxsw.com), came up with zero online references and currently sits alone on the schedule for Tuesday night at The Main...

Nate Headden, OEB writer and resident sleuth, put together a solid case that We Are A Sad Band is none other than Thom Yoke’s Atoms for Peace. Again, this is purely a rumor at this point, but some interesting notes:
- If this is a secret show, then the artist would have to be a pretty big name to necessitate a non-listed showcase, especially off the official SXSW roster.
- We Are A Sad Band has a tongue-in-cheek tone to it. Who would be a band that may be hastily called a “sad band” by press? Radiohead ended up being the first name we called out.
- A secret SXSW showcase would normally coincide with a major release. Radiohead hasn’t been in the studio, but Yorke’s Atoms For Peace is releasing AMOK next week.
- Yorke and Nigel Godrich recently inferred there will be some tour dates coming soon in a Reddit “Ask Me Anything” session this week.
- And our smoking gun. While AMOK is being released next week, a 12” is set to follow in the UK on March 11, which would mean a US release should coincide with March 12, the day of the showcase. Not only that, the 12” will also contain a non-album B-side. The name of the B-side: SAD.



Do512 will keep you up to date! Follow "Thom Yorke and Atoms for Peace" on Do512...

column2: VH1 Presents: VH1 2nd Annual Music + Pop Culture SXSW Event (Invite Only)
column12: Youngblood Hawke,St. Lucia,Mia Moretti
column13: VH1 ANNOUNCES 2nd ANNUAL MUSIC + POP CULTURE EVENT DURING SXSW FEATURING PERFORMANCES BY YOUNGBLOOD HAWKE,ST. LUCIA AND DJ MIA MORETTI OF THE DOLLS Exclusive Event To Be Held At The W Austin’sGrand Ballroom and Balcony, March 13, 2013|VH1 is excited to announce the details for its 2nd annual music + pop culture event during SXSW, set to take place at the W Austin on Wednesday, March 13 at 9pm CT. The grand ballroom and balcony will host live sets by Youngblood Hawke and St. Lucia, along with DJ Mia Moretti of The Dolls. This event will be by invite only.|VH1 is showcasing an exciting lineup of artists, all with strong ties to the channel. LA-based indie pop outfit Youngblood Hawke, VH1’s March You Oughta Know artist, will headline the event. Launched in 2004, VH1’s You Oughta Know franchise introduces promising new artists on the rise to VH1’s base of music lovers. Youngblood Hawke is set to follow in the footsteps of You Oughta Know artists such as Adele, The Civil Wars, Mumford & Sons, The Lumineers, Gotye, Ed Sheeran, and many, many more. Sheeran, who performed at last year’s event at The W Austin, went on to be nominated for a GRAMMY® award this year.|The event kicks off with a performance by St. Lucia, whose music has been recently integrated in several VH1 programs. St. Lucia is the electro-dance-pop brainchild of Jean-Philip Grobler, a singer, musician and producer hailing from South Africa. St. Lucia has recently toured with Ellie Goulding in the US and will follow up their debut EP with a full-length album later this year. |After wrapping up a tour of high-profile Fashion Week events around the world, DJ Mia Moretti of The Dolls, one of the judges on the brand new season of VH1 and SMIRNOFF’s Master of the Mix, will spin and perform with electric violinist Caitlin Moe. As one of NYC's most sought-after DJs, Mia has been profiled in the New York Times ("The New Club Kids," Sunday Style Section) and has garnered a Billboard Dance Top 10 for her remix work. Master of the Mix is the only reality-based competition show for the hottest and fastest-growing art form: deejaying. The show premieres on Monday, April 1st at 10p ET/PT on VH1.|The evening will also be celebrating two new documentary features from VH1’s Emmy Award-winning “Rock Docs” franchise, both having world premieres at this year’s SXSW Film Festival. “Downloaded,” (directed by Alex Winter and premiering Sunday, March 10 at the Paramount Theater) focuses on the advent of digital media sharing, including the rise of the game-changing company Napster and its controversial pioneers Shawn Fanning and Sean Parker. “Finding the Funk” (directed by Nelson George and premiering on Wednesday, March 13 at 1:30p.m. at the Alamo Ritz Theater) is a journey in search of the past, present and future of Funk music featuring interviews with legends Sly Stone, Bootsy Collins, George Clinton, Nona Hendryx, Maceo Parker, Bernie Worrell, Steve Arrington, Mike D, D’Angelo, Sheila E and Shock G. The film is narrated by Questlove of the Roots. This exclusive event is presented by VH1 and produced by BMF Media Group.
column14:
VH1 ANNOUNCES 2nd ANNUAL MUSIC + POP CULTURE EVENT DURING SXSW

FEATURING PERFORMANCES BY YOUNGBLOOD HAWKE,

ST. LUCIA AND DJ MIA MORETTI OF THE DOLLS

Exclusive Event To Be Held At The W Austin’s

Grand Ballroom and Balcony, March 13, 2013


VH1 is excited to announce the details for its 2nd annual music + pop culture event during SXSW, set to take place at the W Austin on Wednesday, March 13 at 9pm CT. The grand ballroom and balcony will host live sets by Youngblood Hawke and St. Lucia, along with DJ Mia Moretti of The Dolls. This event will be by invite only.


VH1 is showcasing an exciting lineup of artists, all with strong ties to the channel. LA-based indie pop outfit Youngblood Hawke, VH1’s March You Oughta Know artist, will headline the event. Launched in 2004, VH1’s You Oughta Know franchise introduces promising new artists on the rise to VH1’s base of music lovers. Youngblood Hawke is set to follow in the footsteps of You Oughta Know artists such as Adele, The Civil Wars, Mumford & Sons, The Lumineers, Gotye, Ed Sheeran, and many, many more. Sheeran, who performed at last year’s event at The W Austin, went on to be nominated for a GRAMMY® award this year.


The event kicks off with a performance by St. Lucia, whose music has been recently integrated in several VH1 programs. St. Lucia is the electro-dance-pop brainchild of Jean-Philip Grobler, a singer, musician and producer hailing from South Africa. St. Lucia has recently toured with Ellie Goulding in the US and will follow up their debut EP with a full-length album later this year.


After wrapping up a tour of high-profile Fashion Week events around the world, DJ Mia Moretti of The Dolls, one of the judges on the brand new season of VH1 and SMIRNOFF’s Master of the Mix, will spin and perform with electric violinist Caitlin Moe. As one of NYC's most sought-after DJs, Mia has been profiled in the New York Times ("The New Club Kids," Sunday Style Section) and has garnered a Billboard Dance Top 10 for her remix work. Master of the Mix is the only reality-based competition show for the hottest and fastest-growing art form: deejaying. The show premieres on Monday, April 1st at 10p ET/PT on VH1.


The evening will also be celebrating two new documentary features from VH1’s Emmy Award-winning “Rock Docs” franchise, both having world premieres at this year’s SXSW Film Festival. “Downloaded,” (directed by Alex Winter and premiering Sunday, March 10 at the Paramount Theater) focuses on the advent of digital media sharing, including the rise of the game-changing company Napster and its controversial pioneers Shawn Fanning and Sean Parker. “Finding the Funk” (directed by Nelson George and premiering on Wednesday, March 13 at 1:30p.m. at the Alamo Ritz Theater) is a journey in search of the past, present and future of Funk music featuring interviews with legends Sly Stone, Bootsy Collins, George Clinton, Nona Hendryx, Maceo Parker, Bernie Worrell, Steve Arrington, Mike D, D’Angelo, Sheila E and Shock G. The film is narrated by Questlove of the Roots.

This exclusive event is presented by VH1 and produced by BMF Media Group.

column14:
Artist rumored to be at SX. Do512 will update as soon as more details are available. To get the latest updates, be sure to follow "Sound City Players" on Do512!

via music-news.com:
"Dave Grohl has said in interviews that he will be showcasing his Sound City Players at SXSW next month and today John Fogerty let slip that he will be playing SXSW as well."
"A line at the end of a press release for the Fogerty album today mentioned 'John Fogerty will tour in 2013 and look for him to be at this year's SXSW in Austin (dates/events TBA).'"


via Brian Ives, Radio.com:
"Dave Grohl's Sound City Players blew the roof off of Park City Live in Utah earlier this month at the Sundance Film Festival (January 18), and they will rock the Hollywood Palladium after the film's L.A. premiere later this week. As of now, that is the only concert that the all-star group has on their schedule, but it looks like they might be hitting a few other locations, including New York and South by Southwest."

"If you’ve been under a rock for the past few weeks, the Sound City Players is a group put together by Grohl, and includes his fellow Foo Fighters, his Nirvana-mate Krist Novoselic, Corey Taylor, Rick Nielsen of Cheap Trick, Stevie Nicks, Rick Springfield and John Fogerty, among others. The huge collective are promoting Grohl’s film, Sound City, about the legendary Los Angeles recording studio. The film opens on Thursday (January 31) in select theaters, and will be available for download from iTunes on Friday (February 1). The soundtrack, which features collaborations between Grohl and a number of artists including Nicks, Springfield and Paul McCartney, will be available in March."



Article: kroq.cbslocal.com

column2: Fashionext.org presents: Fashionext Lounge
column13: Going to SxSW? Come out on Sunday March 10th to check out all the latest in tech and fashion, while enjoying a bite to eat and a drink on us! Taking place during the 2013 South by Southwest Conference (SxSW) in Austin, Texas, the Fashionext Lounge is a pioneering event that will provide a platform to exchange ideas on the future of fashion through the innovation lens.|On March 10, 2013, our event will bring together outstanding emerging designers, fashion tech startups, established brands, investors, fashion influencers and global customers at the SxSW Conference. Alongside traditional fashion designers showcasing at the lounge, our showcase will also include eco, sustainable, ethical and fair-trade designers who are reshaping the concept of consumerism. Our event will act as a catalyst in promoting innovation in fashion to a distinctive and large global film, music, and interactive technology audience.
column14:
Going to SxSW? Come out on Sunday March 10th to check out all the latest in tech and fashion, while enjoying a bite to eat and a drink on us!

Taking place during the 2013 South by Southwest Conference (SxSW) in Austin, Texas, the Fashionext Lounge is a pioneering event that will provide a platform to exchange ideas on the future of fashion through the innovation lens.


On March 10, 2013, our event will bring together outstanding emerging designers, fashion tech startups, established brands, investors, fashion influencers and global customers at the SxSW Conference. Alongside traditional fashion designers showcasing at the lounge, our showcase will also include eco, sustainable, ethical and fair-trade designers who are reshaping the concept of consumerism. Our event will act as a catalyst in promoting innovation in fashion to a distinctive and large global film, music, and interactive technology audience.

column2: THE Entrepreneur Experience at SXSW (+ Party List & ATC Services)
column6: 500 East Cesar Chavez Street, Austin, TX, 78701
column13: THE Entrepreneur Experience at SXSW The problem: You're at SXSW right now and have zero idea what to do or where to go next. Standing in line sucks - - you KNOW that you could be doing something better... but what?! The solution: Get in the know right now about the best entrepreneur events. You came to SXSW in the hopes of helping your business. You are asinine if you don't get a 10x ROI on your SXSW investment. Asse9, Austin Secret Society of Entrepreneurs, thinks it's asinine if you spend money without getting back your money ASAP. You're also dumb if you don't get access to awesome mentors via networking events. I talk about both mentors and networking in chapters five and four (respectively) of my book, "What They Don't Teach You At Stanford Business School". Last year, SXSW was a whirlwind of activities that had an entrepreneurial bent to them but many entrepreneurs were left in the cold. First timers have it the hardest. My goal is to be your ROI within 2 hours of handing over your hard earned cash. ************** "SXSW has one of the best tech conference bangs for the buck" - Larry Chiang ************** This SXSW Party list is just for entrepreneurs. It is party summary information on South by Southwest events that get delivered to you via a password locked file. If ROI is NOT your focus, leave now. If you don't trust this money-back-offer, leave NOW. If you can't read FINE PRINT THAT SAYS IT IS FREE IF YOU TAKE A PICTURE OF YOUR FACE NEXT TO YOUR BADGE, leave now. For a few of you that have an existing, VC funded company, read on... **The VIP SXSW Entrepreneurial Experience*** The VIP SXSW EE compiles the best of the best SXSW events for funded entrepreneurs. This VIP, SXSW-EE, offer includes: - Private, marquee networking events with VCs. - Multiple up to the second updates emailed or texted to your PDA / smart phone. - Confirmed RSVP to events (worth over $700 alone as of 11:11am Feb 10) - Names of event publicists, planners and hosts so you have a higher likelihood to successfully guestlist I have gathered host names, locations and party information of SXSW events and get them delivered to you via a password locked file. Yes, it has a money-back guarantee ************** "I love migrating myself from the waitlist to VIP. It's what they don't teach you in b-school" - Larry Chiang ************** If you'd like a discount code, tweet this NOW "Want the VIP experience @sxsw?! RT http://bit.ly/buster12" and follow @larrychiang. I will DM you the code via Twitter I enjoyed meeting you and mentoring you. I look forward to listening and learning from you and about you. Keep seeking out your ROI here at SXSW and I look forward to saying hi in person. Find me please! I am the 6' 5" Chinese dude sporting a tie and wearing outlet mall khakis. Tsia Jian y'all! Larry Chiang P.S. MBAs are welcome. I will single handedly get you ROI for one year's tuition with the MBA experience. Give me just two days at Austin and $189 of your moo-lah. P.P.S. MBAs only... here is a video for you http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fFt2cX99hiw P.P.P.S. And for reading all the way down a surprise bonus: Thirteen free support emails with Larry Chiang before SXSW even starts so you will absolutely ace 2013 SXSW

column14:
A Mid West Festival + Unofficial Showcase Event during SX in Austin, TX March 12th - 17th, 2013.

This is an Unofficial SXSW Event and brought to you by BSHR Entertainment and Sponsored by Music Saves Lives


THE VENUE

The Firehouse Lounge features classically prepared cocktails, delectable accompaniments, an inviting atmosphere, and a variety of live music. Elevate your experience at Downtown's NEWEST venue.


FEATURING. . .

The giftbags will be given out at the VIP Dinner Party and the Main Event. Mini Moo Business Cards will contain download codes for guests to return home and enter for more goodies!


Plus play the Indie Band Drinking Game + Sky Scavenger Hunt all week to win Sponsored Prize Packages!

THE [SOS] SCHEDULE of SHOWS

Tuesday 3/12 Welcome to Austin: A Singer/Songwriter Party + Evening Events


Wednesday 3/13 Rockin’ Zombie Luau Day Party + Evening Events


Thursday 3/14 The Calm Before the Storm Day Party and the VIP Dinner + Cocktail Party+ evening events.

Mini spa treatments, an art gala with VIP Dinner + Cocktail party.

Friday 3/15 Blue Sky on Broadway + The Indie Dance Party: Bring on the Weekend

The start of the Vinyl Record Club in Partnership with Broadway Recording Company.


Saturday 3/16 BSHR’s “Giant” Launch Party

The main event complete with miniature EVERYTHING. Guests receive The “Grow it @ Home” Giftbag. Raffles of various prizes and giveaways.


Sunday 3/17 The Green Giant Party + Closing events

column2: North of 41 Lounge
column13: The North of 41 Lounge is back for our annual event atSxSW Interactive. This year is going to be better than ever! We have a ton of activities that are planned for you in Austin on Saturday and Sunday March 9th & 10th, 2013. We are located at 309 E. 3rd St. @ Fogo de Chao (corner of 3rd and Trinity). We are 100 ft from the front doors of the convention center!!!We will be doing various product giveaways all weekend. We will be hosting a number of parties throughout the weekend. There will also be a couple of panel discussions taking place starting right after lunch on Sat., March 10th. Make sure to stop in at the North of 41 Lounge to charge up your laptop and grab a drink with friends. We have plenty of space for meetings and while you are in the venue, check out the companies who are displaying at the lounge. The North of 41 Lounge also has FREE WiFi access along with our VIP Blogger Lounge. When you need a spot to relax in between the panels, stop in and see us. Make sure to follow us on Twitter for the latest updates. @northof41 We look forward to seeing you in Austin at North of 41 . To contact us, email: info@northof41.org

column2: Nest Suomi@SXSW2013
column6: 500 East Cesar Chavez Street, Austin, TX, 78701
column13: Suomi goes to SXSW 2013 as NEST booth at the Trade Show. Join in to our merry crew of startup entrepreneurs. We have accommodation. We have Trade Show booth. We have Interactive or Platinum badges. We have Mobile Monday. We have tons of parties to go to. We have seminars. We have BBQ. We can have it all. The 2nd batch of SXSW registrations opened, open until Feb 8 (one month before the event) or until we run out of space at our ClubHouse and/or our booth. However, January 18th is the deadline for all the materials and participating company information under the Nest Helsinki booth, so if for Startup or Business pack, be sure to act before that! Questions - get in touch, details below! /Peter ***************************************************************************** SXSW®, South by Southwest®, is happening again in March, 2013 (8th-17th) in Austin, Texas Peter Green from MobileSensing/GreenFly Events is taking Finnish startups over to Austin again next year, for the fourth time. Double booth and accommodation for the first ones (approx 30 peeps) confirmed. Flights are not included, but pretty much everything else is. More to come when needed. Few words about the SXSW and then to the packages: (Note, if viewing this on iPad/mobile device, the price shown is with Finnish VAT included) SXSW® offers the unique convergence of original music, independent films, and emerging technologies. Fostering creative and professional growth alike, SXSW® is the premier destination for discovery. The SXSWi, South by Southwest Interactive, will be organized for 20th time (SXSW music festival for the 27th time). The Interactive part is between March 8-12 and Music between 12-17. Film goes on all the time. Earlier this year Peter Green (original FinnMobster since 2009) had over 20 startups going to the event of close to 50.000 attendees, with a SXSW Trade Show booth (among about 300 other exhibitors). Many of us were also staying at a group accommodation at the FinnMob Clubhouse. 2013 will be the fourth SXSW organized by Peter, this again bigger and better than before, in 2010 we had about 10 Finns over to SXSW, in 2011 about 50. This year there were close to 100 - and according to the booth pitch the aim in 2013 is 200 companies. So, we are doing a share towards that 200 right here! Join in to Suomi @SXSW2013 crew - let's make sure there will be the 200 Finns this time (and maybe few Swedes with us, too:) The packages are planned to suite well for start-ups, and includes either Interactive or Platinum (withMusic and Film) badge, Group accommodation in a SuomiSXSW Clubhouse (beers and breakfast available; B&B&B:), Trade Show booth/stand as a "homebase" during the Interactive part (Trade Show deom Sunday 10th until Wednesday 13th). Also various side events are being planned (with sponsorship and visibility for Startup packs and especially Business packs). For the Business Pack there is also possibility to use a local PR agency for press releases and press tours during the Trade Show as well as Promotions by a professional promotion company. These packs (and specific prices) will be specified later (sorry about that!) These package prices are valid until end of November (sorry, could not stretch the deadlines more) and there's a maximum quantity of 20 Evangelist-, 20 Startups- and 10 Business- packs at this stage. But yes, the aim is the 200, so this will be extendable, with more houses, RV's and extended booth space if demand exceeds the supply. The packages are explained underneath the selections above, please note that for the evangelist pack there's only one person per company allowed. Also, there is a good opportunity to make this SuomiSXSW 2013 event as part of TEM support (Finnish Ministry of Employment anf the Economy) program for Finnish export. If so, there will be an approximate 40-50% refund of all the event related travel- and marketing expenditures afterwards, including the package price, travel and other direct costs. Possible restrictions for companies enjoying some other benefits will be clarified asap. The accommodation will be available from Thursday March 7th until Sunday March 17th. The accommodations (beds) will be given out on a first come first in beds -basis. However the aim is to have a place to sleep, indoors, for everyone. The house is big, there's another one smaller on the same lot, and possibly space for 9 sleeper RV's (motorhomes) as well. The accommodation is on the 1st Street, about 5 Miles from downtown, with direct bus connection and about 10 mins, 10 $s taxi drive away. If you have either accommodation or badge sorted out, contact me and let's sort it out. Also, let's negotiate If you have both, but want to hang with our crew at the Trade Show and side events. In case of not getting enough participants (into this totally awesome event) we reserve the right to cancel the trip and reservations, and will return the paid amount in full (yes, covering the service fees too) /Peter peter.green(a)sensing.fi +358405707911 P.S. We are also looking for event partners, sponsors, with extra visibility in all materials and possibilities to involve audiences, both the event crew (Finnish startups) as well as other audiences. Please contact and let's be creative and plan ahead. Price for sponsoring is 3.500€, or supporting services for the SuomiSXSW crew for the value. Sponsoring includes a Platinum ticket and accommodation as well as logos in all the publications (so a little like Business Pack in a way).

column14:
Visit MadeinNYaustin.com for more details...

Made in NY: Austin, an event being presented by NY Tech Meetup, the City of New York, and Gust as well as a wide range of New York-based technology startups, will return to SXSW on Sunday, March 9, 2013, from 9 a.m. to 2 a.m. at the newly-remodeled AMOA-Arthouse at the Jones Center in Austin, Texas. The event, expected to attract over 2,000 attendees, will celebrate the vast resources, diverse talent, and unique cultural inspiration of New York tech, culture, food, film, art and music.


Jessica Lawrence, Managing Director of NY Tech Meetup said, “Last year’s event was such a huge success for the entire NYC start-up community and everyone who attended. We’re looking forward to expanding this showcase of the outstanding people and ideas that help make NYC one of the best places to start, build, and expand a business.”


Katherine Oliver, Commissioner of the Mayor’s Office of Media and Entertainment, said, “New York City is a thriving center of creativity, from the surge of films and television shows produced here to the growth of digital startups based in the City that are reinventing the way we live our lives. New York City has so much to offer, and we’re thrilled to be able to showcase the many talented New Yorkers who will be a part of Made in NY: Austin.”

Rachel Haot, Chief Digital Officer of New York City said, “The City of New York is home to not only the world’s most innovative tech minds and businesses but also those on the forefront of art, culture, and food. We’re ecstatic to work with NY Tech Meetup to make this a true New York experience in Austin, and it’s sure to be a blast.”


David Rose, CEO of Gust said: “It’s going to be great to be back in Austin to repeat the amazing showcase of New York’s tech industry that took place last year. Gust has continued to power deal flow management tools and investor relations for NYC-area startups, venture funds, and angel groups, and we can’t wait to do it again at Made in NY: Austin.”


Last year’s event, which featured more than 45 New York tech startups, received outstanding reviews from over 1,000 attendees (with another 2,000 on the waiting list). While sponsors for the event are still being confirmed, previous sponsors include Buddy Media, Wilson Sonsini Goodrich & Rosati, DFJ Gotham Ventures, Shapeways, Rapp, Etsy, and Tumblr.


The all-day and evening event will include interactive and experiential installations of New York’s best technology along with pitch sessions, workshops, and a high-tech, high-energy party to cap off the night. The state-of-the-art venue will also include the popular arts+tech interactive #FEED installations, powered by Twitter.


The event is free and open to the public but does require an RSVP. Sponsorship opportunities are available now. RSVPs for attendees will open in February. For additional event information, please visit www.nytm.org.


-- found online @http://nytm.org/blog/entry/13-17-2013/made-in-ny-austin-returns-to-sxsw-to-celebrate-nyc-tech-cultur...

RSVP

Fort Collins, Colorado, returns to SXSW with our annual SpokesBUZZ showcase at The 512, in the heart of the action on Austin’s Sixth Street. We’ll present the best Fort Collins bands – along with our guests from Denver, Boulder and Beyond – on two stages.

Continuous music, with complimentary New Belgium beer and Coyote Gold all-natural margaritas. Come see what the BUZZ is about at this multi-genre music bash featuring FoCo’s finest. Sponsored by New Belgium Brewing, Coyote Gold All-Natural Margaritas, Mishawaka Amphitheatre, Sweetwine Entertainment Group, Shaped Music and InTicketing.com.



Featuring:
• FREE New Belgium Beer
• FREE Coyote Gold Margaritas
• Fantastic Fort Collins bands on two stages, with a diverse range of genres, styles and sounds
• Our Colorado compatriots from Denver and Boulder

• PLUS: our 2012 SpokesBUZZ BandSwap collaborators from Lafayette, Louisiana, and our new friends from San Francisco, The Stone Foxes!

column13: HT Staffing|presents|First Annual Give-Back Party Benefiting Dress for Success Austin|It’s time for SXSW® again, and to celebrate we are throwing our first annual give-back party at Russian House of Austin, one on Austin's newest hot spots, on March 8 from 5:30pm to 7:30pm to benefit Dress for Success Austin. Come join us and the best of the best in the local HR and recruiting community to help a worthy cause—while networking and enjoying live music from The Flying Balalaika Brothers in one of Austin’s hot spots! Register today to attend, donate or sponsor! Two free drink tokens will be given to all registered attendees upon entry.|Established in 2003, Dress for Success Austin is a non-profit organization that promotes the economic independence of disadvantaged women by providing professional attire, a network of support and career development tools to help women thrive in work and in life. Dress for Success Austin has helped over 7,000 disadvantaged women get back on their feet and become productive members of society. This wonderful organization completely depends on voluntary donations from the community to make their work possible. All proceeds (100%) raised from HT Staffing through donations and sponsorships will be given to Dress for Success Austin. Suggested donations include cash, handbags, unopened makeup, or gift cards (MC/Visa, Amex, Target, Walmart, Marshall’s TJ Maxx, gas). Note: Donations are not required to attend, but are encouraged.|The Flying Balalaika Brothers formed by Russian-Ukrainian musicians who moved to the United States in 1994 and have toured America since 1996. Recently the FBB's have released a new CD called Op, Op, Romale, loosely translated as "Hey, Hey, Gypsy people". The album incorporates humor into a mix of Russian, Romani-Gypsy, and American music. Pair great music with the finest authentic dishes Russian House of Austin has to offer, prepared by the award- winning executive chef Vladimir Gribkov whose specialties include homemade classic Russian such as Pelmeni, soups as Borsch and Solyanka. Enjoy one of 25 different infused vodkas made with the finest Russian vodka. |If you are interested in becoming a sponsor, please call Mark Turpin at (512) 533-9700.
column14:
HT Staffing
presents
First Annual Give-Back Party Benefiting Dress for Success Austin


It’s time for SXSW® again, and to celebrate we are throwing our first annual give-back party at Russian House of Austin, one on Austin's newest hot spots, on March 8 from 5:30pm to 7:30pm to benefit Dress for Success Austin. Come join us and the best of the best in the local HR and recruiting community to help a worthy cause—while networking and enjoying live music from The Flying Balalaika Brothers in one of Austin’s hot spots! Register today to attend, donate or sponsor! Two free drink tokens will be given to all registered attendees upon entry.


Established in 2003, Dress for Success Austin is a non-profit organization that promotes the economic independence of disadvantaged women by providing professional attire, a network of support and career development tools to help women thrive in work and in life. Dress for Success Austin has helped over 7,000 disadvantaged women get back on their feet and become productive members of society. This wonderful organization completely depends on voluntary donations from the community to make their work possible. All proceeds (100%) raised from HT Staffing through donations and sponsorships will be given to Dress for Success Austin. Suggested donations include cash, handbags, unopened makeup, or gift cards (MC/Visa, Amex, Target, Walmart, Marshall’s TJ Maxx, gas). Note: Donations are not required to attend, but are encouraged.


The Flying Balalaika Brothers formed by Russian-Ukrainian musicians who moved to the United States in 1994 and have toured America since 1996. Recently the FBB's have released a new CD called Op, Op, Romale, loosely translated as "Hey, Hey, Gypsy people". The album incorporates humor into a mix of Russian, Romani-Gypsy, and American music. Pair great music with the finest authentic dishes Russian House of Austin has to offer, prepared by the award- winning executive chef Vladimir Gribkov whose specialties include homemade classic Russian such as Pelmeni, soups as Borsch and Solyanka. Enjoy one of 25 different infused vodkas made with the finest Russian vodka.


If you are interested in becoming a sponsor, please call Mark Turpin at (512) 533-9700.

column2: Innovation City: Tomorrow's Destination… Today! (#InnovationCity)

Experience the future and also FREE DRINKS with the Pittsburgh Technology Council and Carnegie Mellon University!



SATURDAY, MARCH 9, 2013 9PM-2AM


Carnegie Mellon University and the Pittsburgh Technology Council invite you to share in a vision of the future at Innovation City, an unforgettable SXSW 2013 party!

Featuring the time-traveling super DJ duo Tracksploitation, FREE drinks, and plenty of futuristic surprises, Innovation City promises to transport you to the world of tomorrow, where there’s a GyroCopter on every lawn and a computer chip in every brain! MARVEL at out-of-this-world student projects! ENJOY THE SPECTACLE of Pittsburgh tech firms and entertainment ventures! STAND IN AWEof our nexus of technology innovators! BE ASTOUNDED by killer giveaways, an open bar, and portals to other dimensions! EMBRACE THE FUTURE by dancing with robots and having your genetic code completely rewritten!

Doors open at 9 p.m., and the bar is OPEN all night.

PAWN TAKES KING 3

{an independent art and music festival with a focus on graffiti, hip hop, and electronic music}

METROPOLIS APARTMENTS
2200 S Pleasant Valley Rd
Austin, TX 78741

Saturday, March 16, 2013
From 3PM until the music stops, beer is gone, and the caps are clogged.

*2 stages of live hip hop and electronic music
*Live graffiti showcase
*Pool
*Hot tub
*Grills (BYOM)
*All ages /open to public

*FREE - we don't need no stinking badges!

Performances by:
Watsky + Open Mike Eagle + Nocando + Eureka the Butcher + VerBS + Child Actor + B Lewis + Sapient + Anthony Maintain + Grey Sky Appeal + Willie Green + Sean Anonymous + Ecid + Chief & TheDoomsdayDevice + Chisme + soundfounder + Lo Phi + Vegetable Kingdom + Mo Niklz + ESH + Trustwon + DJ Halo + Brzowski + PremRock + Eyenine + Homeroom + DJ Notion + Mine Us + Maggz + Very Special Guests

Art by:
Mez + Sloke + Sintex + Swan + Beks + Flip + Cevs + Taskam + GrimNasty

++++++++++++++++++++++++
POSTER DESIGN BY RECSPEC
++++++++++++++++++++++++

The Metropolis:
Metropolis is a really cool apartment complex in the East Riverside neighborhood of Austin. They cater to musicians and artist types and provide a chill atmosphere for people to live, create, and party. The show is in the center of the complex, where there is a pool and volleyball court. The pool area has a stage and some BBQ pits as well. The 2nd stage will be on the other side of the building, in a roped off parking lot. The volleyball court becomes our graffiti exhibition area.

THE PEOPLE OF METROPOLIS ARE KIND ENOUGH TO LET US DO THIS, SO PLEASE RESPECT THE PROPERTY AND DO NOT VANDALIZE ANYTHING. FEEL FREE TO BYOB, BUT NO GLASS CONTAINERS ALLOWED.

column14:
Connect with Austin's most successful entrepreneurs, most active angel investors, most experienced lawyers, and most prominent venture capitalists for another Epic Office Hours!

Interested in moving your startup to Austin?
This is your chance to meet the mover's and shakers of the Austin scene.


Interested in learning more about Capital Factory?
There will be many Capital Factory Mentors available to meet with and you can tour our incredible facilities.

How does it work?

  1. Register on Eventbrite
  2. A week before the event we will schedule your meetings
  3. During the event you will get 20 minutes with each Mentor

How can you make the most of your 20 minutes?

  • Don't spend more than 5 minutes introducing yourself and explaining your business
  • Give short, concise answers to the Mentor's questions
  • If you're doing all the talking, you're not learning anything
  • Come prepared - research who you are meeting with on LinkedIn and write down questions in advance
  • Send a 1 page overview of your company or <5 min video for the Mentor to review in advance
Who will be there?
Last time we had Mentors from:
  • Austin Technology Incubator (incubator)
  • Austin Ventures (vc)
  • Capital Factory Mentors (incubator)
  • Central Texas Angel Network (angel)
  • DreamIt Ventures (incubator)
  • G-51 (vc)
  • Kastner, Huggins, Reddien & Gravelle (legal)
  • Silverton Partners (vc)
  • TechStars Cloud (incubator)
  • and many more...

* this event is not affiliated with SXSW

column2: Carnegie Mellon University and the Pittsburgh Technology Council present: Pittsburgh Innovation Party
column13: Going to SXSW Interactive? So are we! Come out and join our party!The Pittsburgh Technology Council’s Creative Tech Network is seeking innovative projects, partners and sponsors for the 2013 Pittsburgh Innovation Party, an official SXSW event at SXSW Interactive +Film in downtown Austin, Texas.EVENT DATE: Saturday, March 9, 2013 8pm-2am|Presented by Carnegie Mellon University and the Pittsburgh Technology Council|Lead Sponsors: CMU’s Heinz College and Human Computer Interaction Institute|Supporting Sponsors: Alpha Lab, The Entertainment Technology Center, Steeltown Entertainment, CMU University Advancement|Supported by the Claude Worthington Benedum Foundation and the SPARK Kids & Creativity Network|An incubator of cutting-edge technologies, the SXSW Interactive and Film Festival features five days of presentations from the brightest minds in technology and scores of exciting networking events hosted by industry leaders. From creative workshops to big-picture analysis of the future, SXSW Interactive has become the place to experience a preview of what is unfolding in the world of innovation. The Pittsburgh Innovation Event will be an official SXSW-sponsored event, held in downtown Austin during SXSW Interactive + Film, in the heart of the SXSW conference. As an official SXSW event, our event will be promoted through SXSW official marketing channels to over 40,000 attendees.|The event, which will be open to all SXSW Interactive + Film badge-holders, event partners and VIPs, will feature a full evening of SXSW-style mixing and mingling including: an exclusive VIP pre-party with national investors, celebrities and Pittsburgh innovators; an interactive arcade with the newest projects from Pittsburgh companies and students; live VJ, with music and video remixes of Pittsburgh’s innovation successes, and a circulation of up to 30,000 national and international conference attendees. Because SXSW is the preeminent event for business and technology innovation, the conference is the ideal place to raise awareness of Pittsburgh’s innovation – and reinvention, as well as reinforce the opportunities which exist and are promulgating in this region. This year’s SXSW Film and Interactive event is slated to attract over 40,000 conference-goers.|There are many ways to get involved! If you are interested in joining the fun, email Kim Harvey at kharvey@pghtech.org by January 15.
column14:
Going to SXSW Interactive? So are we! Come out and join our party!

The Pittsburgh Technology Council’s Creative Tech Network is seeking innovative projects, partners and sponsors for the 2013 Pittsburgh Innovation Party, an official SXSW event at SXSW Interactive +Film in downtown Austin, Texas.

EVENT DATE: Saturday, March 9, 2013 8pm-2am

Presented by Carnegie Mellon University and the Pittsburgh Technology Council


Lead Sponsors: CMU’s Heinz College and Human Computer Interaction Institute


Supporting Sponsors: Alpha Lab, The Entertainment Technology Center, Steeltown Entertainment, CMU University Advancement


Supported by the Claude Worthington Benedum Foundation and the SPARK Kids & Creativity Network


An incubator of cutting-edge technologies, the SXSW Interactive and Film Festival features five days of presentations from the brightest minds in technology and scores of exciting networking events hosted by industry leaders. From creative workshops to big-picture analysis of the future, SXSW Interactive has become the place to experience a preview of what is unfolding in the world of innovation. The Pittsburgh Innovation Event will be an official SXSW-sponsored event, held in downtown Austin during SXSW Interactive + Film, in the heart of the SXSW conference. As an official SXSW event, our event will be promoted through SXSW official marketing channels to over 40,000 attendees.


The event, which will be open to all SXSW Interactive + Film badge-holders, event partners and VIPs, will feature a full evening of SXSW-style mixing and mingling including: an exclusive VIP pre-party with national investors, celebrities and Pittsburgh innovators; an interactive arcade with the newest projects from Pittsburgh companies and students; live VJ, with music and video remixes of Pittsburgh’s innovation successes, and a circulation of up to 30,000 national and international conference attendees. Because SXSW is the preeminent event for business and technology innovation, the conference is the ideal place to raise awareness of Pittsburgh’s innovation – and reinvention, as well as reinforce the opportunities which exist and are promulgating in this region. This year’s SXSW Film and Interactive event is slated to attract over 40,000 conference-goers.


There are many ways to get involved! If you are interested in joining the fun, email Kim Harvey at kharvey@pghtech.org by January 15.

column14:
Welcome to Austin and welcome to SXSW Interactive!


As the kick off event – the evening offers the perfect networking opportunity to renew connections and sync up itineraries for the weekend. We will have free-flowing libations and serve a Texas inspired hors d’ oeuvres menu.


The evening will also feature the presentation of the BiT Top Ten Innovator Awards recognizing the top ten African Americans who made the biggest impact in 2012. And you can’t experience the Live Music Capital Music of the World™ without live music – right? We’ll have a sizzling live soul auditory experience for your pleasure – along with DJ Phife spinning the best in eclectic neo-sounds.


This is a free event, no SXSW badge is required.



Click here for directions to the Carver Museum.


TheTop 10 Black Innovators of 2012 Awards will be presented as a component of the SXSW Interactive Festival on Friday, March 8, 2013 during the BiT Welcome Reception being held from 6 p.m. to 9 p.m. at The Carver Museum.

We are currently accepting nominees until Sunday, January 27th – stay tuned for the winners.



Last year's winners include:


Mario Armstrong

Angela Benton

B. Bonin Bough

Quincy Jones, III

Soledad O'Brien

Wayne Sutton

Marcia Wade Talbert

Baratunde Thurston

Tristan Walker

Clarence Wooten
