MEOW and WIMPS

cordially invite all professional women in music to attend an exclusive March event – our Second Annual:

High Tea Ladies Luncheon at SXSW

Friday, March 15, 2013

11:30 AM – 1:30 PM

Chateau Bellevue

708 San Antonio Street

Austin, TX 78701

$25 per person includes luncheon, dessert, beverages, tax and gratuity

Chateau Bellevue is an elegant Victorian mansion built in 1874 and a historic downtown Austin landmark. It is home to the Austin Women’s Club.

Wear something *sparkly* and bring your promo materials to pass around.

MEOW (Musicians for Equal Opportunities) is the brainchild of ROCKRGRL Magazine founder Carla Desantis Black. MEOW's mission is to "level the playing field" for women in music through networking, education and advocacy. www.meowonline.org

WIMPS (Women in Music Professional Society) is an informal monthly networking lunch group founded in 2007.


The Fine Print: You must RSVP and pay in advance by March first via Eventbrite and PayPal. No refunds. This luncheon is for ladies only and is not an official SXSW event.


SPONSORSHIP OPPORTUNITIES AVAILABLE


We will be giving away goodie bags to our 120 attendees. For $75 we will include your promo, CD, business card - whatever!


Need more information? E-mail info@meowonline.org or call 512.363.5345.

column2: Brooklyn Brewery presents NY Night Train Soul Clap & Dance Off
column13: DANCE CONTEST|Fri, March 8th|9:00pm - 11:30pm|755 Springdale Rd, Austin, TX|DJ Mr. Jonathan Toubin's Soul Clap and Dance-Off is North America's most popular soul party - by far playing to more people in more places and generating more capital than any of its contemporaries. Founded in New York City the concept is simple-all night dancing to the wild soul 45s of subterranean superstar DJ Mr. Jonathan Toubin and, in the middle, a $100 dance contest judged by a community panel. Cash is great. But so is a trip to Brooklyn for the dance-off championship at Brooklyn Bowl. Get your moves down cause the fine folks from Tumblr and Imgur will be judging the hell out of you from their perch on the dance contest panel.|Recession-friendly mass entertainment with a universally cheap door price, the dance party/spectacle not only sells beyond capacity at home, but has brought its excitement to domestic markets all the way from Portland, Oregon to Portland, Maine and internationally from Tel Aviv to Mexico City-including monthly residencies in New York, Chicago, LA, San Francisco, Oakland, and PDX. The Dance-Off portion features judges from every edge of music and culture from classic subcultural icons like Mike Watt and Jello Biafra, to rock stars Andrew Van Wyngarden (MGMT) and Nick Zinner (Yeah Yeah Yeahs), to interesting cultural figures like Karla LaVey (Satanic Priestess) and Matt Gonzalez (Green Party Vice Presidential Candidate) to your favorite neighborhood heroes. |Catch The Soul Clap!|via Brooklyn Brewery Mash
column14:
DANCE CONTEST



Fri, March 8th
9:00pm - 11:30pm
755 Springdale Rd, Austin, TX


DJ Mr. Jonathan Toubin's Soul Clap and Dance-Off is North America's most popular soul party - by far playing to more people in more places and generating more capital than any of its contemporaries. Founded in New York City the concept is simple-all night dancing to the wild soul 45s of subterranean superstar DJ Mr. Jonathan Toubin and, in the middle, a $100 dance contest judged by a community panel. Cash is great. But so is a trip to Brooklyn for the dance-off championship at Brooklyn Bowl. Get your moves down cause the fine folks from Tumblr and Imgur will be judging the hell out of you from their perch on the dance contest panel.



Recession-friendly mass entertainment with a universally cheap door price, the dance party/spectacle not only sells beyond capacity at home, but has brought its excitement to domestic markets all the way from Portland, Oregon to Portland, Maine and internationally from Tel Aviv to Mexico City-including monthly residencies in New York, Chicago, LA, San Francisco, Oakland, and PDX. The Dance-Off portion features judges from every edge of music and culture from classic subcultural icons like Mike Watt and Jello Biafra, to rock stars Andrew Van Wyngarden (MGMT) and Nick Zinner (Yeah Yeah Yeahs), to interesting cultural figures like Karla LaVey (Satanic Priestess) and Matt Gonzalez (Green Party Vice Presidential Candidate) to your favorite neighborhood heroes.



Catch The Soul Clap!


via Brooklyn Brewery Mash

column14:
Tech Career Expo is the premier job fair showcasing the best tech jobs and career opportunities available. This is the ideal place for you to meet with and discuss employment with top companies – from startups to large firms – in a casual, creative environment (Rivals Steakhouse).

Professionals involved in all aspects of technology (from engineering, programming and design, to marketing, sales, management and more) are welcome to participate.

Tech Career Expo is free to attend to both SXSW attendees and non-attendees. We are open from 11am to 5pm, Friday, March 8 and 11pm to 5pm on Saturday, March 9th.

We look forward to seeing you at the Rivals Steakhouse, on the corner of 5th and Trinity Street, one block from the Convention Center. Copyright © 2003-2012 Engage Digital. All rights reserved.

column2: The Lean Startup SXSW with 500 Startups & Eric Ries

column14:
Held in 2012 in front of a mad house of tech startups + enthusiasts, 500 Startups & Eric Ries have been asked to bring The Lean Startup SXSW to a larger venue for the 2013 Interactive lineup. The Lean Startup SXSW will take place on Saturday, March 9th from 9:30am - 6:00pm at the Downtown Hilton (across from the Convention Center), with the goal of providing attendees with pivotal insights and actionable frameworks for building better, faster, and smarter companies.

column14:
RSVP

schedule TBA
For a second year, the Spotify House (1010 E. Cesar Chavez) is opening its doors to celebrate SX! From March 11th through the 15th, our Big Green House will be your go-to venue to unwind, discover new music and see buzz-worthy up and coming bands.

Every day we’ll have two live performances from some of our favorite new artists, as well as a DJ to finish the day and start your night. We’ve got everything from food truck flavors, ping pong, a photo booth and more – so you won’t have a reason to leave the House all day!

Spotify Premium users get priority access to the House and free food and merchandise all week. If you haven’t got Premium already, sign up now!

We’ll also be hosting an extra special Spotify Live show from a secret location on Wednesday, March 13th.

To get on the guest-list for the Big Green House, just RSVP. You’ll also be entered to win an exclusive swag bag filled with SXSpotify goodies!

Follow us on Twitter @SXSpotify.

column2: Consequence of Sound and Shea Stadium Records present COS / Shea Stadium Showcase
column12: Roomrunner,Duologue,Kitty,So So Glos,Stagnant Pools,Diarrhea Planet
column13: THE LINEUP:|ROOMRUNNER|DUOLOGUE|DIARRHEA PLANET|SO SO GLOS|STAGNANT POOLS|KITTY|Consequence of Sound and Shea Stadium Records are proud to announce an official South by Southwest showcase for Wednesday, March 13th at The Palm Door (401 Sabine St).Daytona Beach rap sensation Kitty (FKA Kitty Pryde) and Indiana post-rockers Stagnant Pools lead the DIY bill alongside Brooklyn punk-rock band So So Glos, Nashville collective Diarrhea Planet, Baltimore sludge act Roomrunner, and London electronic outfit Duologue. For more information on set times and an accompanying playlist, scroll below.Badge and wristband holders will get priority access into this intimate concert, though there will also be tickets available at the door.Also don’t forget, only hours prior to the showcase, Consequence of Sound will host its second annual CoSigns day party at Austin’s The Parish, featuring Thurston Moore’s new band Chelsea Light Moving, The Thermals, Mac DeMarco, St. Lucia, Wampire, Jacco Gardner, Ex-Cops, White Lung, TEEN, Fort Lean, Hunters. CoSigned producer AbdeCaf will DJ between sets.|via Consequence of Sound
column14:
THE LINEUP:

ROOMRUNNER
DUOLOGUE
DIARRHEA PLANET
SO SO GLOS
STAGNANT POOLS
KITTY

Consequence of Sound and Shea Stadium Records are proud to announce an official South by Southwest showcase for Wednesday, March 13th at The Palm Door (401 Sabine St).

Daytona Beach rap sensation Kitty (FKA Kitty Pryde) and Indiana post-rockers Stagnant Pools lead the DIY bill alongside Brooklyn punk-rock band So So Glos, Nashville collective Diarrhea Planet, Baltimore sludge act Roomrunner, and London electronic outfit Duologue. For more information on set times and an accompanying playlist, scroll below.

Badge and wristband holders will get priority access into this intimate concert, though there will also be tickets available at the door.

Also don’t forget, only hours prior to the showcase, Consequence of Sound will host its second annual CoSigns day party at Austin’s The Parish, featuring Thurston Moore’s new band Chelsea Light Moving, The Thermals, Mac DeMarco, St. Lucia, Wampire, Jacco Gardner, Ex-Cops, White Lung, TEEN, Fort Lean, Hunters. CoSigned producer AbdeCaf will DJ between sets.


via Consequence of Sound

column2: SXSW Eco & Geostellar Launch Party
column13: Join SXSW Eco and Geostellar to celebrate the launch of two forward thinking enterprises! SXSW Eco is excited to launch our 2013 season and envision the future: moving beyond sustainability and pioneering deliberate, progressive, and restorative systems worldwide. Meet the Eco team, learn about our action oriented program and submit your ideas through our PanelPicker submission platform, now open! Help us launch tech startup Geostellar as they bring together communities to better understand the potential of renewable energy, and how to put it into action today. A company based on simplicity, science and success, Geostellar helps consumers understand the value of solar energy and empowers them to play a role in the clean tech economy.

Through hashtags, pixels, or live updates, these ambitious individuals have used social media to spread ideas, foster communities and inspire a worldwide audience into action. PREMIERING AS THE OFFICIAL LATINO EVENT AT SXSW INTERACTIVE, THE SOCIAL REVOLUCIÓN WILL RECOGNIZE AND CELEBRATE THESE ONLINE CRIES HAPPENING IN CURRENT CULTURAL SHIFTS AND TRENDS, INTERNATIONAL AND LOCAL CAUSES, AND THROUGH THE MONUMENTAL VISIONS OF INDIVIDUALS. So let it be heard, let it be no longer ignored - Oye el canto of The Social Revolución.

column14:
New for 2013, SXSW Film introduces the Come & Capture Film Factory, an event that allows participants to explore and interact with the newest tools for capturing and creating content. Each day will begin with panel discussions, workshops, and demos, and round out with the opportunity for registrants to tinker with a pavilion of products.


Registrants are encouraged to come in to sample a range of filmmaking products, go out each day and capture their experiences at SXSW. They can then share their finished work with the SXSW community through SXSW’s online channels, including here, on the official festival website.


The event takes place from Saturday, March 9 - Tuesday, March 12, 2013, at the InterContinental Stephen F. Austin Hotel, Capital Ballroom, Section B.


The daily schedule is as follows:

11:00 AM - Panel Discussion
12:30 PM - Workshop/Hands-on Session
2:00 PM-6:00 PM - Demo Pavilion


Programming details will follow, and will be announced on this page and at sxsw.com/film. To participate in the event, register for a badge now - head to sxsw.com/attend to find out how.


To learn more about opportunities to participate at Come & Capture Film Factory please contact Sara Barney at sara@sxsw.com.

column14:
&


presents

Doing Business in the USA

Friday 8th March - 9.30am - 5pm - Austin, Texas


Doing Business in the USA is the essential conference for Founders, CEOs and C-level executives planning to enter or expand their business in North America.

What’s in the Programme

  • Keynotes: leading experts’ give their take on the challenges and opportunities for international firms looking to crack the US market
  • Business Development - understanding US business culture, building relationships and business, from small firms to major corporates
  • Keeping legal and tax efficient - the run-down of IP, staffing, avoiding litigation, incorporation, shares and tax
  • Industry Trends - taken from a new business perspective, a run-down of the digital sector in the US with a look at potential opportunities and emerging trends
  • Immigration - understand the visa landscape, the options, costs, obligations and obstacles
  • Case Studies - the warts’n’all reality of setting up in the US, tips, tricks and workarounds, the pitfalls and possibilities
  • Geography Lessons - the US is a big place with lots of regional variation: gain insight on the digital scene in Silicon Valley, Silicon Alley and points inbetween
  • Investment - get the lowdown on what makes US VCs and angels tick, discover how US investors approach overseas investment

What You Will Learn

  • How to win new business
  • Understanding US business culture
  • Understanding and securing funding
  • Building partnerships, networks and connections
  • Staying legal and tax compliant
  • Protecting intellectual property
  • Hiring, firing and office logistics
  • Understand where to open an office
  • Discovering regional and state support and incentives
  • Meeting fellow international SXSW delegates
  • Networking with potential partners/collaborators

Get Involved

If you’re interested in speaking or exhibiting at the Doing Business in the USA event, please drop us a line with a little bio information and what topic you’d cover. Media partnerships are most welcome, please contact us for more information.


Questions Questions...

If you have any questions about the Doing Business in the USA Mastercalss please do get in touch...


Sam Michel

Email: sam@chinwag.com

Telephone: +44 20 7183 2925


Francesca Heath

Email: francesca@chinwag.com

Telephone: +44 20 7183 2922

column2: RUMOR - Eminem at SX 2013!
column13: It wouldn't be the first time that Eminem made a surprise appearance at a SX show... But we can think of a better reason why he'll show up this year...Skylar Grey will be headlining at R2RLive on the 16th at Brush Square Park -- Eminem executive produced Grey's forthcoming album Don't Look Down set to be released early this year. According to Grey, Eminem makes several appearances on the album, including on "C'mon Let Me Ride," the single released this past December. Eminem apparently devoted a lot of time & attention to Grey's development with this album -- Don't Look Down has been a long time coming. Wouldn't Eminem want to be there to support Grey as she headlines a major music festival, right before her debut album comes out? Especially with Diddy (who also collaborated with Grey on "Coming Home") hosting R2R... We can see the two of them up there with her!

The TalentNet Live! Conference will provide those attendees with a hands-on agenda focusing on emerging and established talent acquisition best practices, including content creation, talent technology, social recruiting, employer branding and workforce marketing.


The 2013 Speakers & Facilitators for the event are as follows:


Conference Emcee: Dwane Lay

Directly following the opening session, attendees will have the opportunity to learn how to conduct social brand & recruiting audits through hands-on workshops covering content, technology, popular social networking platforms, and more. Alternatively, participants can choose to listen & participate in ‘unconference-style’ topical sessions, where they have the opportunity to give feedback & ask questions during each session.

column14:
DC Tech + SXSW


Each year hundreds of DC area tech enthusiasts migrate to Austin for SXSW Interactive. And each year, someone organizes an informal DC Tech meetup so everyone can, well, get together in Austin.

This year the venue and drinks are on us!

Tech Cocktail is excited to host the DC Tech Meetup @ SXSW, sponsored by the Washington, DC Economic Partnership with support by the DC Government.



When: Saturday, March 9th, 2011 at 2:00pm - 4:00pm


Where: The Stage on Sixth, 508 East 6th Street, Austin, TX


Price: Free - please RSVP now (must be 21+ years old to drink)



Thank you to the Washington, DC Economic Partnership for supporting this event!


AND LATER IN THE EVENING....

Come back later in the evening for our Startup Celebration! RSVP Now!

Chances are, if you've been to SXSW in years' past, you're familiar with how we roll. In case you missed the previous festivities, check these links from SXSW 2012, SXSW 2011 and SXSW 2010.

Price: Free with a SXSW badge (must be 21+ years old to enter)

We have hosted large events in Chicago, D.C., NY, San Francisco, Boston, Boulder, San Diego, Detroit, Boise, Austin, Barcelona and more. Read more about Tech Cocktail.

column2: Anne Heller and Church of the Friendly Ghost Present Yeast by Sweet Beast Fest (Day Two)
column12: Smokey Emery,Zorch,Attic Ted,Rigid,Waco Girls,Odor Baby,Daze of Heaven,Muzak John,Night Viking,Greg Ginn and The Royal We
column13: Day Two: RSVP|t is time for the 13th annual Yeast by Sweet Beast Experimental Music Festival, an Austin tradition since the year 2000, which features the best experimental noise artists in America. Created and curated by Anne Heller of the band Aurora Plastics Company, with help from Church of the Friendly Ghost, Yeast by Sweet Beast 2013 is at the historic bear biker bar Chain Drive (504 Willow St., across from the Austin Convention Center) on Saturday March 9th from 2 pm to 10 pm, Sunday March 10th from 5 pm to 2 am and Monday March 11th from 5 pm to 2 am. This year features such sonic strangeness as the venerable Jerri Seinfeldt’s Atrophied Sac, Houston’s incomparable dance noise ensemble Future Blondes, the carnival stylings of Attic Ted, the art rock noise of Rigid, the all-out sonic attack of Pussy Violence and of course as always, the ever-changing shimmering organic-electronic soundtracks of Aurora Plastics Company. Video artists will present eye candy throughout the fest as well for a noisy psychedelic experience. Admission is only $5 per evening. column14:
Day Two: RSVP

t is time for the 13th annual Yeast by Sweet Beast Experimental Music Festival, an Austin tradition since the year 2000, which features the best experimental noise artists in America. Created and curated by Anne Heller of the band Aurora Plastics Company, with help from Church of the Friendly Ghost, Yeast by Sweet Beast 2013 is at the historic bear biker bar Chain Drive (504 Willow St., across from the Austin Convention Center) on Saturday March 9th from 2 pm to 10 pm, Sunday March 10th from 5 pm to 2 am and Monday March 11th from 5 pm to 2 am. This year features such sonic strangeness as the venerable Jerri Seinfeldt’s Atrophied Sac, Houston’s incomparable dance noise ensemble Future Blondes, the carnival stylings of Attic Ted, the art rock noise of Rigid, the all-out sonic attack of Pussy Violence and of course as always, the ever-changing shimmering organic-electronic soundtracks of Aurora Plastics Company. Video artists will present eye candy throughout the fest as well for a noisy psychedelic experience. Admission is only $5 per evening. Check out the Yeast by Sweet Beast Facebook page for all the latest updates and schedule.

at Whole Foods Market HQ
presents

NETWORKING PARTY IS MARCH 7TH (VENUE TBA)

TECHmunch, the food blogger conference sweeping North America, is returning to Austin during SXSW to serve up tasty strategies for food blogger success!

VISIT: techmunchtx.com for more info

This year's TECHmunch conference will inspire food bloggers of every level and provide the ingredients you need to succeed and pursue your passion.

Who should attend?

+ Food bloggers of every level - from hobbyists to media conglomerates and everything in between
+ Brands, PR and Marketing Pros that want to connect and form partnerships with food bloggers

If you're interested in hearing from some of the best and brightest in food and tech join us!

What you'll learn?

Topics include the latest tools and tactics to develop and optimize content, build buzz, grow an audience and profit financially from all the hard work. The focus is on practical, hands-on information that you can use from day-one to take your blog to the next level.

A lot of our chats will be focused on food content, but anyone interested in SEO, monetization, content creation and syndication will walk away from our event with useful information.

IMPORTANT TICKET INFO:

All conference ticket buyers will be invited to our networking mixer. However, additional tickets are available for the networking mixer only. Please purchase a ticket if you are expecting to join us at the conference.

Tickets may be purchased at the door for the amount listed above. We accept cash, credit card or check. Checks should be made out to BakeSpace, Inc.

TECHmunch Austin will feature an extraordinary lineup of experts in digital media publishing, food journalism, marketing and other key disciplines.

Visit techmunchtx.com for more info on our Austin event.
Visit techmunchconf.com to learn about our other cities.

Want to connect with food bloggers and social media leaders in Austin? Contact us at babette@bakespace.com or head over to techmunchconf.com and fill out our form.

column2: My Gold Mask Live at Midnight!
column12: My Gold Mask
column13: What began as a collaboration between longtime musical partners Gretta Rochelle and Jack Armondo (guitar), became less a means to an end, than the end itself. A deep wellspring of personal and musical experiences shaped their direction, and Chicago's My Gold Mask is a culmination, a fulfillment, of a long artistic road, that has lead them to their newest effort, Leave Me Midnight.|"Like Karen O, Gretta Rochelle runs on a rheostat, transitioning smoothly between low-wattage sultriness and floodlit blare" -Pitchfork|"My Gold Mask gets mega sounds and emotion out of two instruments, their tense guitar whorls and crackling warbles perfect for this rainy morning" -Fader
column14:
What began as a collaboration between longtime musical partners Gretta Rochelle and Jack Armondo (guitar), became less a means to an end, than the end itself. A deep wellspring of personal and musical experiences shaped their direction, and Chicago's My Gold Mask is a culmination, a fulfillment, of a long artistic road, that has lead them to their newest effort, Leave Me Midnight.

"Like Karen O, Gretta Rochelle runs on a rheostat, transitioning smoothly between low-wattage sultriness and floodlit blare" -Pitchfork


"My Gold Mask gets mega sounds and emotion out of two instruments, their tense guitar whorls and crackling warbles perfect for this rainy morning" -Fader

column14:
ComboPlate Booking Roster Party
SXSF - South By Soup Fest Benefit 2013

The roster party raises money for the Caritas of Austin Food Services programs, specifically the Caritas Community Kitchen and Food Pantry.

The event is hosted and promoted by ComboPlate Booking. Free and open to the public, live music will be provided by the artists on the ComboPlate Booking roster. Money will be raised by raffling off CDs from the artists and all band tips will go the Food Services programs. Gift certificates from local restaurants, coffeehouses and businesses will also be raffled with all proceeds also going to Caritas. Austinites who would like to help fight hunger in Austin - and hear some great live music while they are doing it - are encouraged to come to Gueros on March 13th. Again this year, we have included the option to donate on our online fundraising page: www.firstgiving.com/southbysoupfest

Not open to the public, but worth noting, ComboPlate Booking will also present a 3 day musical showcase this week, South By Soup Fest, exclusively for the clients of the Caritas Community Kitchen.

(M|O|D)Special Guests:Two FreshObey CityB.Lewis|via disco donnie
column14:
Founded by Roger Schami and Jesse Sappell in August of 2011, The Melt is a music collective, blog, and club night based out of Los Angeles, showcasing up and coming musicians from all over the world. The company has grown into a network of friends, working towards building momentum for a constantly evolving generation of artists.

Comprised of Arnold, REWROTE, LiL TExAS, C.Z., and Yung Satan, the underground collective known as M|O|D stands apart from many other up-and-coming electro-producers today. Though each member has their own distinct sound most of their productions border between electro house, ghetto-tech, trap, and UK’s flourishing bass genre. Check out what’s going on in the underground, with this official SXSW showcase at Republic Live on Saturday, March 16, 2013. Those with badges and wristbands will have priority entry.


Lineup:

  • Djemba Djemba (The Melt)
  • Arnold (M|O|D)
  • LiL TExAS (M|O|D)
  • Kloud (The Melt)
  • REWROTE (M|O|D)
  • FuzZ (The Melt)
  • Yung Satan (M|O|D)
  • C.Z. (M|O|D)
Special Guests:
  • Two Fresh
  • Obey City
  • B.Lewis

column2: Blacks in Tech and The Red Pump Project present: Rock The Red
column13: BiT and The Red Pump Project present Rock The Red|Every 47 minutes, a woman tests positive for HIV/AIDS in the United States. This is just one of many statistics which illustrate the growing impact of HIV/AIDS among women. It is also the reason why The Red Pump Project, a national HIV/AIDS awareness organization, was inspired to launch its fifth annual Rock the Red Pump® campaign.|BiT and The Red Pump Project invites you to join us as we Rock The Red on Sunday, March 10, 2013 from 4-6pm in the BiT House during SXSW. Join us for a fantastic afternoon where we bring together social justice and fashion to Rock the RED BOLDLY, FASHIONABLY while being AWAREof the impact of HIV/AIDS on our community. Red Pump will coordinate five simultaneous events around March 10 to commemorate NWGHAAD in Austin, Charlotte, Atlanta, New York, and Washington, D.C.|In Austin – we will be joined by the co-founder of the Red Pump Project, Luvvie Ajayi. ”Our goal is to normalize conversation about HIV/AIDS, and we choose to use red shoes to do it because they immediately grab your attention,” says Ajayi. “While we have people’s attention, let’s talk about AIDS!” Visit the Red Pump Project on Facebook for more information on how you can support and get involved in your area.
column14:
BiT and The Red Pump Project present Rock The Red


Every 47 minutes, a woman tests positive for HIV/AIDS in the United States. This is just one of many statistics which illustrate the growing impact of HIV/AIDS among women. It is also the reason why The Red Pump Project, a national HIV/AIDS awareness organization, was inspired to launch its fifth annual Rock the Red Pump® campaign.


BiT and The Red Pump Project invites you to join us as we Rock The Red on Sunday, March 10, 2013 from 4-6pm in the BiT House during SXSW. Join us for a fantastic afternoon where we bring together social justice and fashion to Rock the RED BOLDLY, FASHIONABLY while being AWAREof the impact of HIV/AIDS on our community. Red Pump will coordinate five simultaneous events around March 10 to commemorate NWGHAAD in Austin, Charlotte, Atlanta, New York, and Washington, D.C.


In Austin – we will be joined by the co-founder of the Red Pump Project, Luvvie Ajayi. ”Our goal is to normalize conversation about HIV/AIDS, and we choose to use red shoes to do it because they immediately grab your attention,” says Ajayi. “While we have people’s attention, let’s talk about AIDS!” Visit the Red Pump Project on Facebook for more information on how you can support and get involved in your area.

column14:
The producer of The Super Serious Show, CleftClips presents THE MISCHIEF, 2 days of diverse comedy programming at the 2013 SXSW festival.


Pulling from all the dark comedic arts - stand-up, improv, sketch, music and general self-loathing, an oddball group of comedians perform for the Twitter-addled masses in the middle of the world’s biggest tech and entertainment gathering.


​THE MISCHIEF will capture their attempts to embrace the exciting new era of comedy and its direct-to-the-people chaos. It’s an era where traditional shows, topics and approaches all break down. And the fun prevails.


ALL SHOWS OPEN TO ALL SXSW BADGE HOLDERS - GENERAL ADMISSION​


http://www.cleftclips.com/muchmischief-info

column2: Google+ Local @SXSW 2013
column13: When: March 10th & 11th, departing at 11am, 1pm and 3pm | Where: Departure Location at The Belmont (305 W. 6th St.) | Who: All SXSW attendees are welcome (no badge required), limited to the first 50 people per departure time. | What: This year at South By Southwest Interactive, Google+ Local and Field Trip are offering you a chance to see the REAL Austin. | We've partnered with Austin Duck Adventures to serve up six custom tours of Austin, such as the "Ultimate Food Lovers Guide to Austin, the "Dive Bar Tour of Austin," or the "Old-School Austin Tour," all while enjoying some refreshing (and FREE) beverages from Austin's original Deep Eddy Vodka and Honest Tea. | Even better, this isn't just a guided tour, it's a photo tour! We'll be teaching partygoers how to upload photos along the way to Google+ Local business listings, and giving away a brand new Nexus 7 Tablet to one lucky bus rider on EVERY tour. Combine that with some special surprises from the Field Trip team, and every tour promises to be a unique adventure you won't want to miss!
column14:
When: March 10th & 11th, departing at 11am, 1pm and 3pm


Where: Departure Location at The Belmont (305 W. 6th St.)


Who: All SXSW attendees are welcome (no badge required), limited to the first 50 people per departure time.


What: This year at South By Southwest Interactive, Google+ Local and Field Trip are offering you a chance to see the REAL Austin.


We've partnered with Austin Duck Adventures to serve up six custom tours of Austin, such as the "Ultimate Food Lovers Guide to Austin, the "Dive Bar Tour of Austin," or the "Old-School Austin Tour," all while enjoying some refreshing (and FREE) beverages from Austin's original Deep Eddy Vodka and Honest Tea.


Even better, this isn't just a guided tour, it's a photo tour! We'll be teaching partygoers how to upload photos along the way to Google+ Local business listings, and giving away a brand new Nexus 7 Tablet to one lucky bus rider on EVERY tour. column14:
The Ideas Are Worthless conference is a forum to connect, educate, and inspire every attendee towards execution. Hosted by Black Founders and BiTHouse, the Austin conference is the perfect way to kick off your trip to SXSW Interactive and for local Austin entrepreneurs to learn from their peers in the Austin entrepreneur community and beyond.

A limited number of free tickets will be available to SXSW badge holders.

The conference will bring together diverse perspectives on tech entrepreneurship, while providing a platform for emerging companies, entrepreneurs, and investors to connect and take action.

Watch this video from the NYC Conference to see what to expect for the Austin Conference.

The program will include panelists, (including investors, CEOs, entrepreneurs, engineers), sharing insights into startup fundraising, investment strategies, running a company, new startup trends, and finding technical talent for your startup. The following will also be a part of the conference.

Startup Clinic. The Startup Clinic will allow entrepreneurs to meet one on one with investors and prominent entrepreneurs to receive feedback on their startup and pitch. Access to signups for Startup Clinic will emailed with your eventbrite confirmation. First Come, First Served.

Pitch Competition. The pitch competition is an opporunity for you to pitch your company to investors and the general public. Five companies will be chosen to pitch their idea live during the conference.

Who should attend? Anyone working in technology, from early-stage startup to corporate to investments. Anyone who is thinking about starting a startup, or has a general interest in technology and innovation. This includes but is not limited to: engineers, entrepreneurs, designers, product managers, marketers, business development, and investors.


For more information, visit http://www.blackfoundersconference.com

column14:
DC Tech + SXSW


Each year hundreds of DC area tech enthusiasts migrate to Austin for SXSW Interactive. And each year, someone organizes an informal DC Tech meetup so everyone can, well, get together in Austin.

This year the venue and drinks are on us!

Tech Cocktail is excited to host the DC Tech Meetup @ SXSW, sponsored by the Washington, DC Economic Partnership with support by the DC Government.



When: Saturday, March 9th, 2011 at 2:00pm - 4:00pm


Where: The Stage on Sixth, 508 East 6th Street, Austin, TX


Price: Free - please RSVP now (must be 21+ years old to drink)



Thank you to the Washington, DC Economic Partnership for supporting this event!


AND LATER IN THE EVENING....

Come back later in the evening for our Startup Celebration! RSVP Now!

column14:
Register HERE - Free with Platinum, Gold or Interactive Badge & Registration

Your Brand Is Social. Now What?

OMMA Social at SXSW is a focused, half-day show incorporated into SXSW Interactive. It is designed to guide marketers and agency execs through the terrain of social media and how it relates to their brands and Web presence. This special edition aims to go beyond what might be called Social Marketing 1.0, by demonstrating, through keynotes, panels and case studies, how to engage social consumers beyond “Likes”, follows and simply buying ads on social platforms.

How can marketers use social to motivate audiences? Improve targeting using new tools such as Facebook Graph Search? How should social engagement be measured? Is it possible to integrate campaigns across differing social media channels? And can marketers and agencies combine paid and earned media into provocative social campaigns? OMMA Social at SXSW will grapple with those issues, and many more.


What To Expect

* Hear from the top names in social media as they share the secrets of connecting with consumers using
social media and marketing.

* Gain indispensable knowledge and insight into emerging social media and trends within the

* Discover today’s best practices for social marketing, going beyond the simple accumulation of brand
followers.

* Explore how individual brands are using social media through two focused case studies on state-of-the-art
social marketing.

* Learn about the newest social data tools, and how they can be used to reach customers.


Video from the last OMMA Social


OMMA Social Attendees include

  • BabyCenter, VP, Consumer Insights and Analytics
  • Bank of America, Vice President, Social Media Manager

column2: Official SXSW Geospatial Meetup 2013 (Badges Only)
column13: Join us for the Official SXSW 2013 Geospatial Meetup. LBS, GIS, SoLoMo and every other trade acronym (Good & Bad) for ambient technologies are on the rise and are here to stay. What are location-based services, geospatial information services, social-local-mobile, and ambient and why do we need to care? To learn how to apply and utilize these innovative technologies in the real world, engage users, and where the industry and technology is heading, come meet with experts ranging from F500 geospatial experts to innovative startup founders all looking to crack the code. Take this opportunity to network with like-minded individuals who are on the forefront of this rapidly evolving field within the mobile sector. We know that 11am after a fun-filled night at SXSW may sound early, but don't worry, we're tapping into our Texas roots and will have a Bloody Mary Bar plus breakfast tacos aplenty. Can't wait to see you at the Official SXSW Geospatial Meetup 2013! Must have a SXSW badge or day pass to attend. |More information here: http://schedule.sxsw.com/2013/events/event_IAP993349

column2: IEEE Standards Association presents: Digital Telepathy: When Every Thing Connects
column13: Once upon a time, our phone, the fridge and TV were distinct devices, manufactured in distinctly different environments. Not anymore. Today, our devices share technologies in an unprecedented manner. We can use our phone to watch on-demand programming.|When the power goes out, we may get a text notification from our fridge. If you're higher tech, the grocery list can transfer easily through your wireless network from your Smart Fridge to any device. Convergence and interconnection are the new name of the game, and along with apps and wireless networking, several revolutionary interconnection technologies will soon change every detail of our lives - forever.|This is the Internet of Things - a future where people and objects communicate in unprecedented ways. In this panel we'll explore the dynamics of interconnection and convergence and address the need for a more interdisciplinary approach to design, engineering, development, communication and privacy. Questions AnsweredIn real terms, what is the "Internet of Things" and is it just a buzzword?What are the big social changes we might predict as millions of users effectively imprint the Internet onto our physical environments?We can all see that more of our devices, tools and toys are becoming connected in ways we never imagined even 5 years ago. What benefits can connectivity and convergence bring to society and culture? How can these benefits support support developing countries and building a more sustainable world?As we move towards a world of very realistic interaction with physically remote experiences, what are the implications on our personal relationships, geography, careers, privacy and personal identity?Even with all this convergence and connection, there are moments where I want to be by myself, or just share with a couple of people. If I don’t want others to know what I am doing and where I am, how can I ensure the privacy and proper partitioning of my information? Will sharing be "the norm" or my choice?|Presented by:|Joe Weinman, Sr VP, Telx |Oleg Logvinov, Dir Market Dev Industrial & Power Conversion Division, STMicroelectronicsWael Diab, Sr Technical Dir, BroadcomKaren Bartleson, Sr. Director, Community Marketing, Synosys and IEEE-SA President|Hashtags:|#sxsw #DigTel|via Eventbrite
column14:
Once upon a time, our phone, the fridge and TV were distinct devices, manufactured in distinctly different environments. Not anymore. Today, our devices share technologies in an unprecedented manner. We can use our phone to watch on-demand programming.


When the power goes out, we may get a text notification from our fridge. If you're higher tech, the grocery list can transfer easily through your wireless network from your Smart Fridge to any device. Convergence and interconnection are the new name of the game, and along with apps and wireless networking, several revolutionary interconnection technologies will soon change every detail of our lives - forever.


This is the Internet of Things - a future where people and objects communicate in unprecedented ways. In this panel we'll explore the dynamics of interconnection and convergence and address the need for a more interdisciplinary approach to design, engineering, development, communication and privacy.

Questions Answered

  • In real terms, what is the "Internet of Things" and is it just a buzzword?
  • What are the big social changes we might predict as millions of users effectively imprint the Internet onto our physical environments?
  • We can all see that more of our devices, tools and toys are becoming connected in ways we never imagined even 5 years ago. What benefits can connectivity and convergence bring to society and culture? How can these benefits support support developing countries and building a more sustainable world?
  • As we move towards a world of very realistic interaction with physically remote experiences, what are the implications on our personal relationships, geography, careers, privacy and personal identity?
  • Even with all this convergence and connection, there are moments where I want to be by myself, or just share with a couple of people. If I don’t want others to know what I am doing and where I am, how can I ensure the privacy and proper partitioning of my information? Will sharing be "the norm" or my choice?


Presented by:


  • Joe Weinman, Sr VP, Telx
  • Oleg Logvinov, Dir Market Dev Industrial & Power Conversion Division, STMicroelectronics
  • Wael Diab, Sr Technical Dir, Broadcom
  • Karen Bartleson, Sr. Director, Community Marketing, Synosys and IEEE-SA President



Hashtags:


#sxsw #DigTel



via Eventbrite

column14:
The German SXSW delegation invites you to a relaxed meeting in the midst of the hubbub of 6th Street. A lively and delicious event-luncheon hosted by the Initiative Musik, including the creative cities of Berlin and Hamburg in cooperation with the Berlin Music Week. The chefs from German catering service Kochzeichen D will service delectable cuisine from the region, while Coma, Vimes, Kid Simius and Seams will work the turntables to provide the proper musical backdrop.

Definitely add this to your calendar for Thursday, March 14th from 12-4p.

You can hear a sampling of all the wonderful music that the German Initiativ Musik is bringing to Texas this year at their Soundcloud site:
https://soundcloud.com/wunderbar2013/sets/sxsw2013/s-Qh7kF

Beforehand
Brotzeit: German Bread, Lard And Bavarian Obazda / Iced Cucumber Yoghurt Soup / Rissole From Berlin And Stewed Cucumber / Pickled Egg And Pomeranian Potato Salad

Dished Up Largely
Fresh Made Bread Dumplings / Potato Turnip Ragout / Pineapple Sauerkraut / Roasted Brussels Sprouts And Glazed Button Champignons / Kassler-Smoked Pork Chop / Vegetable Wrap And Spinach Asparagus / Bean Sauce / Three Kinks Of Cabbage With Nuts And Breadcrumbs

Sweet Afters
Baked Apple And Vanilla Sauce / Bavarian Cream And Raspberries

Who doesn't enjoy a free meal, good company, and oh, yeah, music!

www.wunderbar-sxsw.de

In this session, they address the questions: Whom do we fear? Or hide from? Or scapegoat? How can we move
beyond assumptions and stereotypes about those who are different from us? They will explore these and similar questions through a variety of artistic media.
“Art and the Other” celebrates the power of words, music, and
images to reveal, connect, and transform.

Presenters: Katherine Lott, Paul Finley, Harriet Myrick

The protocol serves as a “message bus” for social applications, enabling apps developed by disparate vendors to communicate with each other in real-time, resulting in a seamless, unified user experience. In July 2012, the OpenID Foundation launched Backplane Protocol Working Group to solicit input from the global OpenID community on the standard. Backplane Protocol is currently in use by some of the largest media companies in the world, including ABC, ESPN, NBC Universal, Universal Music Group and WWE. App providers who support Backplane Protocol include 500 Friends, Arktan, Badgeville, BigDoor, CalmSea, Caterva, Chute, Disqus, Echo, Envolve, Janrain, JetJaw, Livefyre, Marketo, Realtidbits, Stocial, Tokbox, TurnTo, Umbel and Viafora.|via Eventbrite
column14:
RSVP


Echo and Janrain invite you to kick off SX2013 Interactive with a fun and informative networking event celebrating the incredible recent success of Backplane Protocol. What is Backplane Protocol? If you have to ask, you HAVE to be here! We'll serve you some tasty microbrews, deliver the inside skinny and give you ample time to chat with industry peers and big brands on what you've been missing so far. So why not stop by, grab a beer and learn something you can take back to your boss to help justify your Southby attendance!


Schedule:

2:30pm - 2:45pm Industry Meet-and-Greet & Beer Tasting
2:45pm - 3:00pm Introduction to Backplane Protocol
Khris Loux, Co-founder and CEO, Echo
3:00pm - 3:30pm Overview of the Technical Specification
3:30pm - 4:00pm Case Study: Universal Music Group Uses Backplane Protocol to Integrate
Best of Breed Apps, Reducing Cost and Time-to-Market
Lee Hammond, VP of Digital, Interscope Geffen A&M
4:00pm - 4:30pm Networking with App Developers and Brands

About Backplane Protocol


Backplane Protocol solves a key interoperability problem that emerged when brands started integrating multiple 3rd party web applications like real-time commenting, social login and game mechanics into their sites in order to provide web visitors with a modern, social user experience. The protocol serves as a “message bus” for social applications, enabling apps developed by disparate vendors to communicate with each other in real-time, resulting in a seamless, unified user experience. In July 2012, the OpenID Foundation launched Backplane Protocol Working Group to solicit input from the global OpenID community on the standard. Backplane Protocol is currently in use by some of the largest media companies in the world, including ABC, ESPN, NBC Universal, Universal Music Group and WWE. App providers who support Backplane Protocol include 500 Friends, Arktan, Badgeville, BigDoor, CalmSea, Caterva, Chute, Disqus, Echo, Envolve, Janrain, JetJaw, Livefyre, Marketo, Realtidbits, Stocial, Tokbox, TurnTo, Umbel and Viafora.


via Eventbrite

This 21+ event is FREE to attend, but entry will be available on a first-come, first-served basis.


For the last two years, Copyblogger Media has hosted one of the most talked-about parties at SX2013, and for our third annual bash, we're taking it to another level.


Meet up with your friends on Saturday night at Buffalo Billiards -- one of Austin's most legendary clubs -- for an exclusive event you won't forget.


A *free open bar* will be held from 9pm - 10pm, and plenty of surprises throughout the night are going to keep things... interesting.


NO SX badges are needed, so just bring your brains, your body, and your thirst.


Also, please note that our little parties usually grow a line that stretches around the block, so get there early if you want to join the fun.

column2: IEEE Standards Association presents: Omnipresent: When Virtual Meets Reality
column13: When the “virtual overlay” meets everyday life, everything changes, from the way we shop to the way we interact with the world around us. Today, augmented reality is moving beyond the virtual dimension to enhance real world experiences, meshing with and revolutionizing interactive training, real-world simulation, design, architecture, manufacturing, medicine and more. This panel explores new advancements in Virtual / Augmented Reality and the short and long-term impacts AR may carry. We'll also explore the not-so-distant future, highlighting the creative opportunities that exist for the development of new AR solutions, standards and enabling technologies. Questions AnsweredWhat are the most promising developments in computer vision that could take Augmented Reality (AR) to the next level or beyond?Having to use a phone or tablet for Augmented Reality limits the technology's vast potential. So, how will we be "seeing" AR in ten years?What kind of common infrastructure is needed to tie together the augmented world?Are synthetic and mixed environments the universal "next-generation interface"?What the heck is a spime and why should I care? What other new terminology should I be on the lookout for as reality shifts?|Presented by:|BC "Heavy" Biermann, Founder, The Heavy Projects Blair MacIntyre, Assoc Professor, Georgia Institute of TechnologyChristine Perey, Spime Wrangler, Perey Research & ConsultingJay Iorio, Technology Strategist, IEEE|Hashtags:|#sxsw #omnipres|View the event in the Official SXSW schedule
column14:
When the “virtual overlay” meets everyday life, everything changes, from the way we shop to the way we interact with the world around us. Today, augmented reality is moving beyond the virtual dimension to enhance real world experiences, meshing with and revolutionizing interactive training, real-world simulation, design, architecture, manufacturing, medicine and more. This panel explores new advancements in Virtual / Augmented Reality and the short and long-term impacts AR may carry. We'll also explore the not-so-distant future, highlighting the creative opportunities that exist for the development of new AR solutions, standards and enabling technologies.

Questions Answered

  • What are the most promising developments in computer vision that could take Augmented Reality (AR) to the next level or beyond?
  • Having to use a phone or tablet for Augmented Reality limits the technology's vast potential. So, how will we be "seeing" AR in ten years?
  • What kind of common infrastructure is needed to tie together the augmented world?
  • Are synthetic and mixed environments the universal "next-generation interface"?
  • What the heck is a spime and why should I care? What other new terminology should I be on the lookout for as reality shifts?


Presented by:

  • BC "Heavy" Biermann, Founder, The Heavy Projects
  • Blair MacIntyre, Assoc Professor, Georgia Institute of Technology
  • Christine Perey, Spime Wrangler, Perey Research & Consulting
  • Jay Iorio, Technology Strategist, IEEE



Hashtags:

#sxsw #omnipres

column14:
Over 600 punk and indie classics, we want you to sing 'em LOUD! As seen at Matador 21, Fun Fun Fun Fest, and featured in The Village Voice, The AV Club and more.

The Karaoke Underground is for punk and indie rock fans who love to scream, yelp, croon, bark and sometimes even sing their favorites from artists like Black Flag, Modest Mouse, the Misfits, Cat Power, the Pixies, Dead Kennedys, Sleater-Kinney, Pavement, Joy Division, Fugazi, Guided By Voices and many more. It's video karaoke with onscreen lyrics, a stage, you -- and the chance to sing great songs you just can't find anywhere else.

With an ever-expanding catalog of punk and indie classics, we've got your poison. From Wilco to Wire, from Belle & Sebastian to Big Black, you're sure to find something to put a microphone in your hand.

http://karaokeunderground.com/songlist.html

iRecords // Cromarti Records // Seta Label // Grouper Recordings

In the spirit of SXSW, you are bound to expect gigs by artists that are making a name for themselves, and Rishi K. is one we though you should get to know.

Rishi makes music that allows people to go deeper into themselves for a spiritual and healing experience, or simply to just have fun!

Based in San Francisco he has been producing and DJing deep and tech house since 2011. Since then he has been released on many well respected labels in deep house, and his productions are being supported by some of the top names in deep house today.

column13: The Austin Smoke Experiment|March 10th from 1-4pm|On the heels of a successful 15-city tour in 2012, the Food Experiments, the nation’s leading cook-off organization, is returning to Austin for the ultimate cookoff sponsored by Brooklyn Brewery.|Austin is one of our select cities we’ll be visiting in 2013. column14:
The Austin Smoke Experiment
March 10th from 1-4pm

On the heels of a successful 15-city tour in 2012, the Food Experiments, the nation’s leading cook-off organization, is returning to Austin for the ultimate cookoff sponsored by Brooklyn Brewery.

Austin is one of our select cities we’ll be visiting in 2013. This year, our theme revolves around one of Texas’ best local culinary traditions, SMOKE! Dishes will range from traditional smoked meats to, dare I say it, smoked vegetables or smoked ice cream!?


Anyone can compete! Anyone can attend! And anyone can win! Sharpen your knives, America! This is a call to all amateur chefs looking to be named the next cook-off king or queen of Austin.


Are you experimented…?


$1 of every ticket will be donated to SLOW FOOD AUSTIN

column2: DIRECTV's ROGUE Watch Party
column13: Be among the first people in the nation to watch the first episode of DIRECTV's new original series, ROGUE at the official Watch Party at SXSW. Free drink tickets provided to the first 100 guests. In Rogue, an undercover detective, obsessed with finding her son's killer, is driven into a secret partnership with an Oakland crime boss. Their alliance unearths information that threatens to destroy both their families. Truth has its consequences. Starring Thandie Newton, Marton Csokas, Joshua Sasse, Matthew Beard and Leah Gibson. Facebook.com/RogueDIRECTV

Barrientos Mexican American Cultural center is a free, two-day, all-embracing arts, entertainment, and educational event designed as a launching pad for creative discovery.|Pan Americana Festival fosters an appreciation of America’s diverse cultures and heritage by bringing together a multinational convergence of talent to collaborate, celebrate, and collectively promote their passions in pursuit of a new transnational cultural and artistic experience.Pan Americana Festival offers a series of distinctive experiences from music, dance, theatre, and film, to the visual, culinary, and literary arts, providing a positive multicultural encounter for the whole family.|For more info, visit: http://bellasartesalliance.org/pan-americana-festival/|Don't forget to check out Day Two of 2013 Pan Americana Festival
column14:
2013 Pan Americana Festival Day One - Friday, March 15

4PM - 11PM

Launched in 2011 to capacity audiences, the Pan Americana Festival produced by Bellas Artes Alliance in collaboration with the City of Austin and the Emma S. Barrientos Mexican American Cultural center is a free, two-day, all-embracing arts, entertainment, and educational event designed as a launching pad for creative discovery.


Pan Americana Festival fosters an appreciation of America’s diverse cultures and heritage by bringing together a multinational convergence of talent to collaborate, celebrate, and collectively promote their passions in pursuit of a new transnational cultural and artistic experience.

Pan Americana Festival offers a series of distinctive experiences from music, dance, theatre, and film, to the visual, culinary, and literary arts, providing a positive multicultural encounter for the whole family.


For more info, visit: http://bellasartesalliance.org/pan-americana-festival/


Don't forget to check out Day Two of 2013 Pan Americana Festival

Barrientos Mexican American Cultural center is a free, two-day, all-embracing arts, entertainment, and educational event designed as a launching pad for creative discovery.|Pan Americana Festival fosters an appreciation of America’s diverse cultures and heritage by bringing together a multinational convergence of talent to collaborate, celebrate, and collectively promote their passions in pursuit of a new transnational cultural and artistic experience.Pan Americana Festival offers a series of distinctive experiences from music, dance, theatre, and film, to the visual, culinary, and literary arts, providing a positive multicultural encounter for the whole family.|For more info, visit: http://bellasartesalliance.org/pan-americana-festival/|Don't forget to check out Day One of 2013 Pan Americana Festival
column14:
2013 Pan Americana Festival Day Two - Saturday, March 16

4PM - 11PM

Launched in 2011 to capacity audiences, the Pan Americana Festival produced by Bellas Artes Alliance in collaboration with the City of Austin and the Emma S. Barrientos Mexican American Cultural center is a free, two-day, all-embracing arts, entertainment, and educational event designed as a launching pad for creative discovery.


Pan Americana Festival fosters an appreciation of America’s diverse cultures and heritage by bringing together a multinational convergence of talent to collaborate, celebrate, and collectively promote their passions in pursuit of a new transnational cultural and artistic experience.

Pan Americana Festival offers a series of distinctive experiences from music, dance, theatre, and film, to the visual, culinary, and literary arts, providing a positive multicultural encounter for the whole family.


For more info, visit: http://bellasartesalliance.org/pan-americana-festival/


Don't forget to check out Day One of 2013 Pan Americana Festival

column14:
RSVP

Cirque du Soleil Casting Rendezvous is your chance to meet Talent Scouts Claude Vendette and Denis Cantin onsite at the Swan Dive to learn more about the original music of Cirque du Soleil, the challenge of live performance and the casting process.
It is a unique opportunity to discover the work of the Casting team as well as Cirque du Soleil creative and musical journey and the type of professional musicians they are looking for. Short videos and musical excerpts will be presented and of course Claude and Denis will be available to talk with instrumentalists and singers to answer all your questions.

Complimentary drinks will be offered at this event.

via facebook

column2: MOFILM — Beer and a Brief
column13: Like a beer? Like interesting briefs? Join the MOFILM Team for the "MOFILM Beer & Brief" event. They’d love to chat with you over a beer about their upcoming briefs for global brands such as Reebok, Chevrolet, AT&T, Coca-Cola and more… Through the MOFILM video contest model they provide filmmakers with production grants to help fund your films, you can win up to $8,000 in cash, PLUS the first prize winner and guest get flown to their events all around the globe! So if you fancy partying with them in Cannes, Beijing, Rio, London...come and see MOFILM at Fado's!

column2: When We Ruled H-Town - RxSM (FREE)
column6: 2015 E Riverside Dr, Plaza , Austin, TX, 78741
column13: RSVP for each day of RxSM Underground Film Festival at Emo's Plaza|Do512.com/RxSM|When We Ruled H-Town|Directed by Joseph Schneider, Brent Himes and Robbie Conley|Film Screening at RxSM - Day Seven|Thursday, March 14th - 10pm|Emo’s East Plaza|2015 E Riverside|(Between Emo’s East and the Beauty Ballroom)|Film Synopsis | A retrospective look at the 90's music scene in Houston, Texas, when a spark of energy and an insatiable curiosity brought musicians, artists, and fans together for a brief moment of musical greatness. Our F**** YOU! WE'RE FROM HOUSTON attitude drove the diverse sound of the underground scene, which captivated a generation of fans. Often out performing our national counterparts at area clubs, H-Town acts left a lasting impression on the city to this day. With a complete lack of commercial ambition, we didn't get the respect we deserved, WE DEMANDED IT...... This is the story of When We Ruled H-Town.
column14:
RSVP for each day of RxSM Underground Film Festival at Emo's Plaza
Do512.com/RxSM

When We Ruled H-Town
Directed by Joseph Schneider, Brent Himes and Robbie Conley

Film Screening at RxSM - Day Seven
Thursday, March 14th - 10pm

Emo’s East Plaza
2015 E Riverside
(Between Emo’s East and the Beauty Ballroom)

Film Synopsis | A retrospective look at the 90's music scene in Houston, Texas, when a spark of energy and an insatiable curiosity brought musicians, artists, and fans together for a brief moment of musical greatness. Our F**** YOU! WE'RE FROM HOUSTON attitude drove the diverse sound of the underground scene, which captivated a generation of fans. Often out performing our national counterparts at area clubs, H-Town acts left a lasting impression on the city to this day. With a complete lack of commercial ambition, we didn't get the respect we deserved, WE DEMANDED IT...... This is the story of When We Ruled H-Town.

column14:
For our first-ever SXSW we're joining forces with our friends at the Austin Poetry Slam for a full night of beats, thoughts, rhymes, and poetry.

We'll also be releasing our very first AMX Mixtape featuring local emcees who've been gracing the stage weekly at the Spider House Ballroom!

It all goes down like this:
7:30 PM: Doors
8:30 PM: Austin Poetry Slam Round 1
10 PM: AMX Mixtape Showcase
11 PM: Austin Poetry Slam Final Round
12 AM: Slam/Hip-Hop Open Mic

Come by and check out all the amazing poets from the Slam, then stick around for live performances from each artist on the AMX mixtape performing their selected track, followed by an open mic until bar close!

We WILL be charging $5 at the door for this one! If you're interested in hopping on the open mic just bring your beat on a flash drive, CD, or MP3-player! Full line-up of performing artists from the mixtape will be released soon!

column14:
RSVP by clicking here!


CHILL BEATS is a monthly dj event originating at Halcyon in Austin, TX in March 2011. Chill Beats focuses on downtempo, future jazz, trip-hop, lounge and ambient music.

SUN. March 10, 2013
10am - 4pm

resident dj:

DJALCHEMY
http://soundcloud.com/djalchemy
Future jazz and downtempo dj with roots in techno and trance dating back to 1991. 2003 is when the change in formats came about in his style after being inspired by a compilation called Chill Room released on his record label WE Records. Currently focused on bringing downtempo to a larger audience while still pushing the future jazz sound that continues to expand into the newest genres of EDM.

with guest DJs:

PARTTIME CHILLER (Los Angeles)
http://parttimechiller.com/
Residing in Los Angeles, CA he has been laying down eclectic abstract grooves drenched in disco, funk and soul for the past 15 years. From warehouse parties to art openings to farmer's markets, he is the vibe enhancer for any occasion. Download a free mixtape at http://parttimechiller.com/.


RICHARD HENRY
http://schedule.sxsw.com/2013/events/event_MS24174
Richard Henry is a dj with an ear for beats from all over the globe. He's been collecting tunes since an early age from Flea Markets to local record stores in search of a different sound adding to his large record collection. His multigenre sets range from 60s garage/funk/soul gems to Baile Funk to bass heavy beats from all corners of the globe. This lead him to quickly share the stage with the likes of Clipse, 2 Live Crew, Spank Rock, The John Spencer Blues Explosion to name a few. Currently working on a series of mixtapes and production work that will eventually see daylight.

DJ SHANI (Chicago)
http://soundcloud.com/dj-shani
Heavily influenced by the soul, funk & jazz scenes of Chicago’s south side, DJ Shani has always been involved in music. Shani created & produced a DEEP HOUSE radio show coined “The Groove Temple™” on WLUW-88.7FM that has hosted an impressive roster of guest DJs like Derrick Carter, DJ Touch (France), Lady D, Miguel Migs, DJ Heather & Ron Trent to name a few. “The Groove Temple™” will celebrate it’s 13th year this May.

MEYLO
http://soundcloud.com/meylo
A native of deep South Texas just miles away from the Mexican border, Meylo’s musical experiences date back to the summer of 1986 when he DJed a friend’s birthday party. By 1991 he was mixing records at night clubs and raves and DJing gigs as large as Lalapalooza. In 2007 he moved to Austin to further his career as an interactive designer, and that’s where he teamed up with his long time buddy Jose. Together they launched HopSonic Radio. Meylo’s musical tastes range from Singer/Songwriter, Folk and Country to Funk, Nu-soul, and of course, House.


NO COVER -- ALL AGES

HALCYON Lounge
218 West 4th Street
Austin, TX 78701
(512) 472-9637
http://www.halcyonaustin.com/

Add CHILL BEATS
http://www.facebook.com/ChillBeats
http://twitter.com/ChillBeatsATX

Tune in every Sunday morning from 6am - Noon CST for CHILL BEATS on http://www.HypersonicRadio.com/

WHAT: A big ol gay music festival in the woods of Austin, Texas. Gaybigaygay is in it's 8th(!!) year and we are excited to party with you back at our old location on Rogge Lane

WHEN: Always the last day of SXSW. Sunday, March 17th!! We start at NOON and end at MIDNIGHT!!

WHERE: 3506 ROGGE LANE. Just off of Springdale road. Follow the balloons, streamers, signs and gays to the spot.

WHO: Bands! Dj's! Lineup still in the works...
ALSO WHO: Merch area for band merch and gay bi shirts. A food trailer serving up goods and a beer station serving up suds.

Come all, enjoy a day of music, fun, food and drinks! The event is free but parking is not..(we have to rent the land..) Bring some dollars to park your car, buy merch, eat food and drink a beer. Bring a blanket and pack some snacks and stay the day. Please, carpool! Designate sober drivers. Be safe and have fun!!
FREE and ALL AGES

column2: Jamaican Queens Showcase
column12: Jamaican Queens
column13: Time of Show TBD|Detroit duo Jamaican Queens has offered an exclusive stream of their debut album, Wormfood, out March 5th on Notown, with the Hype Machine. Recently selling out their first New York show, the band is making their way down to SXSW, performing with Javelin, Dustin Wong and more, after releasing a series of unique music videos, including the band’s docu-style Detroit horror film for first single “Kids Get Away,” which has been played on KCRW, and received praised from NYLON, Noisey, Impose and FILTER among others, saying, “the trippy collaboration of upbeat guitar and synth provides some bone-chilling beats alongside Ryan Spencer’s expressive, shrieking vocals and creepy lyrics.” |The partnership of Jamaican Queens’ Ryan Spencer and producer Adam Pressley was conceived in late 2011. Pressley moved to Detroit to join Spencer in his former band Prussia, and shortly after his arrival the group dissolved. The two decided they worked better as a pair and spent that winter writing and recording Wormfood, which was mixed by High Bias Recordings engineer, Christopher Lazlo Koltay (Akron/Family, Dirtbombs). The fusion of Spencer’s melodies and Pressley’s knowledge of underground music and production gave birth to their unique “odd pop” or as it’s being called, “trap-pop.” Influenced by the southern rap beats of Three 6 Mafia, Gucci Mane, and Young Jeezy, as well as the experimentation of Brian Eno and Lee Scratch Perry, Wormfood draws from electronic, dub, downbeat, and folk influences, creating an erratic canvas overlaid with radiant pop hooks.
column14:
Time of Show TBD



Detroit duo Jamaican Queens has offered an exclusive stream of their debut album, Wormfood, out March 5th on Notown, with the Hype Machine. Recently selling out their first New York show, the band is making their way down to SXSW, performing with Javelin, Dustin Wong and more, after releasing a series of unique music videos, including the band’s docu-style Detroit horror film for first single “Kids Get Away,” which has been played on KCRW, and received praised from NYLON, Noisey, Impose and FILTER among others, saying, “the trippy collaboration of upbeat guitar and synth provides some bone-chilling beats alongside Ryan Spencer’s expressive, shrieking vocals and creepy lyrics.”


The partnership of Jamaican Queens’ Ryan Spencer and producer Adam Pressley was conceived in late 2011. Pressley moved to Detroit to join Spencer in his former band Prussia, and shortly after his arrival the group dissolved. The two decided they worked better as a pair and spent that winter writing and recording Wormfood, which was mixed by High Bias Recordings engineer, Christopher Lazlo Koltay (Akron/Family, Dirtbombs). The fusion of Spencer’s melodies and Pressley’s knowledge of underground music and production gave birth to their unique “odd pop” or as it’s being called, “trap-pop.” Influenced by the southern rap beats of Three 6 Mafia, Gucci Mane, and Young Jeezy, as well as the experimentation of Brian Eno and Lee Scratch Perry, Wormfood draws from electronic, dub, downbeat, and folk influences, creating an erratic canvas overlaid with radiant pop hooks.

column2: Vaudeville Smash
column12: Vaudeville Smash
column13: Vaudeville Smash are: brothers Marc Lucchesi, lead vocals, sax, flute; Dan Lucchesi, drums, vocals; and Luca Lucchesi, bass, vocals; plus Nic Lam, guitar, vocals; and James Bowers, keys, vocals.|In their native Australia, Vaudeville Smash have racked up reviews so effusive, they sound like they might have been written by groupies. Then again, it’s hard to imagine not becoming a groupie after hearing this Melbourne quintet’s dance pop. Named after a kiddie karaoke machine, Vaudeville Smash pour the soul of Fitz & the Tantrums, the ’80s infectiousness of Wham! and the pop sheen of Prince into an intoxicating musical cocktail that’ll hit your ears and slide straight to your groove thang... When Vaudeville Smash first performed at SXSW in 2011, the Huffington Post immediately labeled them a buzz band; Melbourne’s Beat magazine offers even stronger praise. One writer said, “I’ll be damned if Vaudeville Smash aren’t the most mind-blowingly refreshing live act to emerge from Melbourne since God knows when.” Another added, “Vaudeville Smash are exactly what live music is all about. If you don’t love them, you’re an idiot.” Listen for yourself. Here’s a Soundcloud link to some tunes, including their singles “Look at Me” and “Best Night."

column2: "Is Intuitive Marketing Dead?" - A Talk with Nate Silver
column13: Meet the future of marketing: Just as projecting election outcomes is all about the using the data, so is marketing. Hear statistician and author Nate Silver talk about data literacy, his techniques for using the data, the impact of data and how it is transforming people's lives – in everything from elections to healthcare to marketing and advertising. Book signing will immediately follow the presentation. Authentic Mexican cuisine and select local brews and vodkas will be served.|This invite-only event is co-sponsored by Adometry, Media6Degrees, Neustar/AdAdvisor and ThinkVine. SXSW attendees and local businesses that would like to attend can request an invite by emailing Melissa.Marbury@adometry.com.

column14:
Buffalo Lounge Teaser from Idea Collective on Vimeo.




The Buffalo Lounge Elevator Pitch Competition
Monday, March 11th - 9PM
512 Bar - 408 E. Sixth Street



The Buffalo Lounge Seeks Oklahoma’s Top Interactive Entrepreneurs

Oklahoma’s best elevator pitches from interactive entrepreneurs are sought for a $10,000, one-night pitch competition March 11 at the South By Southwest Conference & Festival in Austin, Texas.

Finalists, selected by a panel of entrepreneurs and angel investors from among 90-second video pitches submitted by Feb. 6, will pitch their business opportunities for a $5,000 grand prize in the Buffalo Lounge Elevator Pitch Competition for Oklahoma interactive companies.

The pitch competition will be conducted at 9 p.m. Monday, March 11, before a live audience at The 512 Bar on 6th, 408 E. Sixth Street in Austin. It is sponsored by the Office of Entrepreneurial Development, a partnership between i2E and the Greater Oklahoma City Chamber.

“We’re excited about showcasing Oklahoma talent before a SXSW audience that wants to see innovative, new concepts,” said Josh O’Brien, director of the Office of Entrepreneurial Development. “The Buffalo Lounge Elevator Pitch competition will put Oklahoma entrepreneurs in front of an audience that otherwise might never be exposed to the best that our state has to offer.”

The Buffalo Lounge is a collaborative effort to spotlight Oklahoma companies and innovators at the massive SXSW conference, which last year attracted more than 50,000 visitors in areas of film, music and interactive software. Several successful companies including Twitter, Foursquare, Phonebooth and Highlight were either introduced or spotlighted at SXSW.

Applicants submitting video pitches will be ranked against competing submissions based on angel investor interest level. Criteria may include the quality of the pitch, business viability, market opportunity, competitive advantage and management. Finalists will be announced Feb. 8.

To enter a video pitch, please go to http://www.i2E.org/ and click on the Buffalo Lounge logo.

The Buffalo Lounge began in 2010 when the Oklahoma Film & Music Office, the Idea Collective and the Greater Oklahoma City Chamber led an effort to create a collaborative effort to increase Oklahoma’s presence at the SXSW festival.

More than 30 Oklahoma companies, agencies and organizations have participated in numerous events held by The Buffalo Lounge at a local Austin venue. This year, The Buffalo Lounge will host four events at The 512, as well as a booth at the SXSW Exhibit Hall.

For more information or questions about The Buffalo Lounge Elevator Pitch competition, contact Josh O’Brien at jobrien@i2E.org or (405) 813-2412.

For more information about The Buffalo Lounge and other Oklahoma activities at the SXSW festival, please visit www.thebuffalolounge.com. For more information about SXSW, visit http://sxsw.com/.


via Facebook

column2: Fast Company Happy Hour (Day Four)
column13: Fast Company, in association with the BMF Media Group, will host the Fast Company Grill in Austin, Texas from March 8-12, 2013. The FastCompany Grill will feature an exclusive five-day restaurant, lounge, and arcade exclusive to artists, celebrities, media, VIPs and tastemakers. The Fast Company Grill will showcase exciting interactive activities daily from sponsors Lincoln, Target, Starbucks Doubleshot, and Evite. Through the selection of key Austin partners, The Lincoln Hello, Again experience will re-imagine the space into a blend of the city, through gaming and interactive technology. FastCompany will be interviewing top business, technology and media executives including Jonah Peretti, Jared Leto, Kevin Rose, Dennis Crowley, Troy Carter, Doug Ulman and Padma Warrior for its “Creative Conversations” video series. Fast Company aims to reveal the inner thoughts and ideas of unlikely business pairings as they share how they innovate and re-imagine their companies, products, media and technology with one another. Target and Fast Company are celebrating their first-ever partnership at the Fast Company Grill with four dedicated Happy Hours featuring notable co-hosts Cultivated Wit with Baratunde Thurston and Girls In Tech, along with a special performance by Glenn Tilbrook of Squeeze on Friday. Target is transforming a section of the Fast Company Grill to a “Tarcade” with refurbished retro video games, Minneapolis inspired cocktails, NFC Tarcade cards, and opportunities for guests to challenge each other throughout the week.

CONTEST DETAILS HERE: http://www.back2atx.com/

Local live music photo-sharing startup, Vivogig, has teamed up with music streaming service, rdio, and the Austin Tourism and Convention Bureau to put on a photo contest during SX. As fans shoot and share their gig pics through the vivogig iPhone app, other fans (and their friends and family) will be able to vote on their favorite photos. The pic with the most votes by the end of the month will win a stay in a luxury downtown hotel, an rdio subscription, concert tickets, restaurant and bar gift certificates and cool Austin-centric experiences such as an electric bicycle tour of music venues led by a local musician.



Lean more about the contest at http://www.back2atx.com/ and download the iPhone app to shoot and share your gig pics here:http://bit.ly/WnsMvK

More about vivogig:
After soft launching at SXSW last year and getting some great early press, fan photography app, vivogig, is back and better. Vivogig enables fans to more easily shoot and share their passion for their favorite bands, all while competing for prizes and powering fan engagement on band, venue and media partner websites.

During SX, vivogig is also throwing two parties, Music, Meet Tech ATX on Sunday the 10th at Bourbon Girl, headlined by The Octopus Project and the Vivogig Shindig on the 12th at Frank, headlined by rapper, Vinnie Cha$e, followed by a DJ set by Shiny Toy Guns.

Download the app!

column2: NASA Social @ SX2013 (REGISTRATION REQ)
column13: NASA will host a one-day event for 20 of its social media followers on March 10, 2013, as part of the week-long 2013 SXSW® Interactive Festival in Austin, Texas. The SXSW Interactive Festival features five days of compelling presentations from the brightest minds in emerging technology, scores of exciting networking events hosted by industry leaders, the SXSW Trade Show and a lineup of special programs showcasing the best new digital works, video games and innovative ideas the international community has to offer.|Participants will get special one-day access to NASA’s SXSW interactive panels and hear from and meet NASA scientists, engineers, astronauts, managers and the folks behind the agency’s social media efforts.|NASA Social participants will have the opportunity to:Take part on Sunday, March 10, in one of the most energetic, inspiring and creative events of the year.Learn about NASA’s James Webb Space Telescope, the most ambitious telescope ever constructed. Hubble’s tennis court-sized successor will be 100 times more powerful and orbit far beyond Earth’s Moon, where it will beam back images of the universe’s first galaxies as well as celestial objects hidden by clouds of cosmic dust.View the full-sized Webb telescope model outdoors, and then get an in-depth look at the perplexing questions the telescope is designed to answer: How did the universe form? Is our solar system unique? Are we alone in the cosmos?Visit the NASA Experience Tent, filled with displays, videos, multimedia products and hands-on activities. As part of the NASA tent, Microsoft Research will be running their World Wide Telescope on a 10’x20’ visualization wall that lets users fly through the universe and explore planets, stars, etc.Join Astronaut Ron Garan and others from NASA to socialize and discuss the latest innovations in space technology. Mingle with the pros and exchange stories about your favorite space mission.Meet the people behind NASA’s Mars Curiosity landing social media campaign, see what helped NASA capture the public's attention and what's in store for the mission.Meet NASA designers who want to share a little about the history of the user experience in space, check out state-of-the-art tools aboard the space station and learn how to use free online tools to engage with NASA missions.Attend a star party with speakers ranging from astrophysicists to astronauts to Nobel laureates.For more information about the SXSW Interactive Festival, visit: http://sxsw.com/interactiveWhat is a NASA Social?|A NASA Social is an informal meeting of people who use social networking sites such as Twitter, Facebook and Google+. Participants at this event will be provided a unique NASA in-person experience at SXSW, which they are encouraged to share with others through their favorite social network.|Guests will have an opportunity to see a life-sized model of the world's largest space telescope, NASA's James Webb Space Telescope, along with bigger-than-life exhibits, educational events, interactives, visualizations, scientists and much more at the South by Southwest (SXSW®) Festival. The NASA Social at SXSW® will be free. Registration badges are required for access to the SXSW Conference, Festival and Trade Show events. For more information about the festival, visit:http://sxsw.com/interactive|How do I register?|Registration opens at 10 a.m. EST on Tuesday, Feb. 19, 2013, and closes at 5 p.m. EST Thursday, Feb. 21. Participants will be randomly selected from qualified online registrations.
